1
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:06,710
Now, the elimination candidates
will be announced.

2
00:00:07,380 --> 00:00:10,510
The elimination candidate from
Team Challenger, which finished 3rd,

3
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:12,750
(Kim You Hyun)

4
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:15,480
is Kim You Hyun.

5
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:18,150
From the moment Round Two started,

6
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:21,220
I already thought there was over
a 90 percent chance it would be me.

7
00:00:21,790 --> 00:00:24,890
The elimination candidate from
Team Rookie, which finished 4th is...

8
00:00:26,230 --> 00:00:29,060
Lee Gwan Hee.

9
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:31,530
When my name popped up on the screen,

10
00:00:31,530 --> 00:00:33,070
my heart sank.

11
00:00:34,670 --> 00:00:37,070
My head was spinning.

12
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:40,410
There is one additional announcement.

13
00:00:41,340 --> 00:00:43,640
Last night, Pandora's Safe was opened,

14
00:00:43,850 --> 00:00:47,420
and the price of an extra vote ticket
has increased by 10,000 dollars.

15
00:00:47,420 --> 00:00:49,050
(Price increase in extra vote tickets)

16
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:50,950
Pandora's Safe was opened?

17
00:00:51,090 --> 00:00:54,060
An extra vote ticket
now costs 30,000 dollars...

18
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:56,890
and can only be traded in the Voting Room
during voting time.

19
00:00:58,430 --> 00:01:00,160
I was like, "Oh, someone opened the safe."

20
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:03,200
My team didn't need the extra vote ticket.

21
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,800
I can already hear
the other teams' funds...

22
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,570
shrinking.

23
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:09,770
Because of Pandora's Safe,

24
00:01:09,770 --> 00:01:11,070
the price was bumped up to 30,000 dollars.

25
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:12,270
I was like, "I'm in trouble."

26
00:01:12,270 --> 00:01:14,810
Voting will begin now.

27
00:01:15,740 --> 00:01:18,450
Voting will close in one hour.

28
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:29,420
- So we all get 1 vote ticket each?
- Yes, 1 each. So we have 5.

29
00:01:29,420 --> 00:01:32,290
- Everyone gets a ticket.
- It doesn't concern us.

30
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:37,130
Gosh, darn it.

31
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:41,970
Why are you upset?

32
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:43,640
I feel so bad.

33
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:49,540
(Sighing)

34
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:53,110
Gwan Hee and I had played basketball
together for a long time.

35
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:55,650
Gwan Hee and I talked a lot
while staying in the mansion.

36
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:56,980
I told him not to worry.

37
00:01:56,980 --> 00:01:58,790
I promised I'd help set the mood,

38
00:01:58,790 --> 00:02:01,090
so he wouldn't lose the vote
for the Deathmatch.

39
00:02:01,090 --> 00:02:02,220
I promised to help him.

40
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:03,290
Are you an elimination candidate?

41
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:05,090
It's probably going to be me.

42
00:02:05,830 --> 00:02:08,660
I'll talk to my team for you.
Don't worry about it, okay?

43
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:13,070
And Sung Joo asked us to vote
for an easy opponent for the Deathmatch...

44
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:14,340
before he left.

45
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:15,740
Whom should we vote for?

46
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:17,740
An easy opponent.

47
00:02:17,970 --> 00:02:19,210
- I see.
- An easy opponent?

48
00:02:19,510 --> 00:02:20,940
- Bye.
- Bye.

49
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:21,980
You got this.

50
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:25,410
I think Gwan Hee is closer
to an easy opponent...

51
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:28,080
Sung Joo would want than You Hyun.

52
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:31,720
If I were to push people to pick You Hyun
just to save Gwan Hee...

53
00:02:31,790 --> 00:02:33,150
I made a promise to Sung Joo.

54
00:02:38,030 --> 00:02:40,090
I treasure both of them dearly.

55
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:42,430
Sung Joo. Gwan Hee.

56
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,900
I had to pick one between them.

57
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:49,970
But I had reasons
to help both of them survive.

58
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:54,840
To vote for the sake of our team...

59
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,510
- But...
- Actually,

60
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:59,250
this won't help our team in any way.

61
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:01,680
Let's say Gwan Hee goes to the Deathmatch,

62
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,720
and Sung Joo beats him.

63
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,850
- Sung Joo won't be on our team anymore.
- Exactly.

64
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:07,290
To protect our team,
we have more reasons...

65
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:09,360
- to send You Hyun to the Deathmatch.
- Right.

66
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:10,830
Our answer is already set.

67
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:14,660
(If Gwan Hee of Team Rookie
were to get eliminated,)

68
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:18,930
(Sung Joo will be transferred to Team R,
given that he survives.)

69
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,500
Two scenarios could play out
if we choose Gwan Hee.

70
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,240
One, Sung Joo ends up going home.

71
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,170
Two, Sung Joo ends up on Team Rookie.

72
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:27,310
In both scenarios, we'd lose him.

73
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:29,380
If we vote for You Hyun,
and You Hyun wins the Deathmatch,

74
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:30,480
Sung Joo will end up going home.

75
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:33,580
If Sung Joo wins,
he will be able to come back to us.

76
00:03:34,050 --> 00:03:37,050
And if he wins,
their team will lose a key player.

77
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:39,390
Let me share where I stand.
I'll be honest.

78
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:42,290
Jin Hyeong wants to send You Hyun.

79
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:45,030
But personally,
I'm putting more importance...

80
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:47,800
- On his survival?
- on Sung Joo's survival.

81
00:03:48,130 --> 00:03:51,530
Here's why.
Even if he ends up on Team Rookie,

82
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:53,570
as long as he's there,

83
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,970
- we can...
- You'll have an inside man.

84
00:03:54,970 --> 00:03:57,070
Right. Anyway, we...

85
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,010
Here's what Jin Hyeong told me.

86
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:01,810
"This is a no-brainer.
We have to vote for You Hyun, right?"

87
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:05,280
But how could we go
against our beloved member,

88
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,280
Sung Joo?

89
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,620
We must give him an easier opponent.

90
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:10,320
Sung Joo would have
better odds of beating...

91
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,450
Gwan Hee.

92
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:14,760
Even if he ends up joining Team Rookie,

93
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:17,060
Sung Joo would still be in the game.

94
00:04:17,330 --> 00:04:21,360
In a way, Team P2 and Team Rookie
would have...

95
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,800
a rock-solid alliance.

96
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:27,030
YunB and Jin Hyeong began to disagree
on the matter.

97
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,940
Once they began to have disagreements,

98
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:30,570
it drove me crazy.

99
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:31,770
I was completely torn.

100
00:04:32,210 --> 00:04:34,540
(Team P2's room)

101
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,250
Gosh, this is so cruel.

102
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,320
I just didn't know what to do.

103
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:48,020
It was impossible for me
to find a middle ground.

104
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,360
Sang Min.

105
00:04:58,530 --> 00:05:00,200
So here's what's going on.

106
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,570
Those two teams made an alliance.

107
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:05,740
So I'm wondering whom you'll vote for...

108
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,380
and if you guys could buy...

109
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:09,580
one or two extra vote tickets.

110
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:11,950
- This is my first point.
- Okay.

111
00:05:12,810 --> 00:05:14,580
I don't have any intention
to help Team Rookie.

112
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,250
- Okay.
- Okay?

113
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:18,120
Yes. Here's my next question.
Would you be able to buy...

114
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,550
extra vote tickets even if it's just one?

115
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:21,460
Are you asking us for a favor?

116
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:23,760
- Right.
- We're open to the idea.

117
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:25,360
We can discuss that. So don't worry.

118
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,460
Okay.

119
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:29,460
I went to Sang Min,
thinking he would help me.

120
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:31,000
As expected, he was very willing.

121
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,070
"Of course. I'll help you."

122
00:05:33,070 --> 00:05:34,270
Hear me out.

123
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:36,240
Sang Min said he'd help me.

124
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,840
- But I don't know where you stand.
- I see.

125
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,070
If you can tell us where you stand...

126
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:41,280
- and if there's no hope for me,
- Okay.

127
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:42,880
I don't want to use my team fund then.

128
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:48,420
- Let's discuss it first.
- Okay.

129
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,620
I was lying to him
when I said I'd vote for Gwan Hee.

130
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:54,920
- I see.
- Of course, I know.

131
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,560
Here's what You Hyun said.

132
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,560
"If you won't vote in my favor,"

133
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,900
"I won't buy extra vote tickets."

134
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:04,400
"I'll go to the Deathmatch.
Just tell me that."

135
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,130
To be honest,
I was furious on my first day here.

136
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:10,340
You Hyun said, "Do you think
you can handle the consequences?"

137
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:12,310
That's what he said to Ji Hoo.

138
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:13,940
(You Hyun opposed the deal from Team P1.)

139
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:16,110
Do you think
you can handle the consequences?

140
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:18,950
I just couldn't let that go.

141
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:21,780
- All right. Starting now,
- Yes.

142
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:24,050
- I have no choice...
- Yes.

143
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:27,220
- but to be evil.
- Okay.

144
00:06:27,490 --> 00:06:29,960
Let's tell You Hyun we'll help him
and make him use up the team fund.

145
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,460
- Then we'll vote for him.
- Okay.

146
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:34,200
I wanted to send him to the Deathmatch.

147
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:37,330
"Don't worry. I'm going to vote for you."

148
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:40,400
That's what
I was telling myself in my head.

149
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:42,770
So spend all of your team fund, You Hyun.

150
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,070
(Gesturing)

151
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:49,140
Gwan Hee. Keun Woo...

152
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,550
We made our decision.
So we wanted to give you a heads-up.

153
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:53,550
Okay.

154
00:06:54,450 --> 00:06:57,450
(Team P1 pulls Gwan Hee aside in private.)

155
00:06:57,850 --> 00:07:00,420
We're not going to vote for you.

156
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,560
So tomorrow during the main match...

157
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:03,720
- Be serious.
- You don't have to help.

158
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,860
We can play together as a team.

159
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:06,660
Yes, I can get on board with that.

160
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,700
Putting everything side,
here's what I can promise for the future.

161
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:11,200
Once I'm indebted to someone,
I make sure...

162
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,270
- Right. We can totally trust you on that.
- I pay them back.

163
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:14,970
I'll pay you guys back no matter what.

164
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:17,040
So I have four votes in my favor?

165
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,040
- Four votes.
- Yes.

166
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,340
- We're not going to play you.
- There won't be any surprises.

167
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:21,340
- No surprises.
- Right.

168
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:23,010
- This is our final answer.
- We'll help you.

169
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:27,850
Gwan Hee highly values loyalty.

170
00:07:27,850 --> 00:07:30,680
I knew that
he would definitely return the favor...

171
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,520
if we were to help him at times like this.

172
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:34,460
I'll cast my vote.

173
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:42,900
(Lee Sang Min votes for Kim You Hyun.)

174
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:44,570
(Kim You Hyun)

175
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,670
(Park Ji Min votes for Kim You Hyun.)

176
00:07:46,670 --> 00:07:47,740
Thank you.

177
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,210
(Lee Tae Gyun votes for Kim You Hyun.)

178
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:56,310
(Jeong Keun Woo votes for Kim You Hyun.)

179
00:07:57,550 --> 00:08:00,280
(Seung Yong approaches Team P3.)

180
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:03,920
Hello.
Can I ask how you guys plan to vote?

181
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:06,190
So...

182
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:10,390
if Gwan Hee doesn't go, it's good news
since he'll still be on your team.

183
00:08:10,790 --> 00:08:13,630
In the worst-case scenario,
you guys will get one more player.

184
00:08:13,690 --> 00:08:16,130
For the sake of our team,
having the winner from the Deathmatch...

185
00:08:16,130 --> 00:08:17,160
will be great.

186
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:20,730
Then other teams might feel like
we're a threat.

187
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:23,570
Getting either Sung Joo or You Hyun
eliminated in the Deathmatch...

188
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,770
might be advantageous to all of us.

189
00:08:26,410 --> 00:08:27,580
That's just my opinion.

190
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:29,880
If Gwan Hee were to get eliminated,

191
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:32,480
and if one of them ends up on our team,

192
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,950
our team will be stronger.

193
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:36,780
So that won't be good news to other teams.

194
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:39,950
On that note, I said having You Hyun
and Sung Joo compete in the Deathmatch...

195
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:41,720
would be better for them too.

196
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:44,830
That was my reasoning
when I talked to them.

197
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:48,360
We already made a deal
before the game that...

198
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:50,030
we'd use an extra vote ticket for Team P2.

199
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,630
If you get first place,
the deal ends there.

200
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,930
If you don't...

201
00:08:53,930 --> 00:08:55,740
and get the chance to spend money,

202
00:08:55,740 --> 00:08:57,440
we'll support you financially up to
a certain amount.

203
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,640
(Team P3 promised to help Team P2.)

204
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:01,440
Including our vote tickets...

205
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,180
and the rest...

206
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:05,010
It wouldn't make sense
to help you blindly.

207
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:06,110
- Right. Of course.
- Okay.

208
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:08,550
Let us think about it.
We have a lot of time left.

209
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:09,750
- Okay.
- It's only been five minutes.

210
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,920
Gwan Hee.

211
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,820
How did it go?

212
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:17,690
Team P1 said they'd help me.

213
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,290
I need to hear what Team P3 is thinking.

214
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:22,400
Once they decide on what to do
with their four individual vote tickets,

215
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,470
not the extra vote ticket,

216
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:26,030
I won't have to buy an extra vote ticket.

217
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:28,340
I didn't want my team
to be short on money...

218
00:09:28,340 --> 00:09:31,270
during later challenges
because we spent it...

219
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:32,370
to save me.

220
00:09:32,370 --> 00:09:34,110
I think we should buy the ticket
just to be safe.

221
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:35,280
- I agree.
- That's my opinion.

222
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,710
- I think we should.
- We'll buy one each.

223
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:39,080
I'll cast my vote.

224
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:43,950
(Kwak Beom votes for Kim You Hyun.)

225
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:47,560
I'll buy the extra vote ticket.

226
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:53,830
Team Rookie, 30,000 dollars
have been deducted from your fund.

227
00:09:54,090 --> 00:09:58,200
(Kim You Hyun)

228
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:05,210
I'll buy the extra vote ticket.

229
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:08,480
Team Rookie, 30,000 dollars
have been deducted from your fund.

230
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:12,010
(Shin Seung Yong votes for Kim You Hyun.)

231
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:14,420
Thank you.

232
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:17,790
(Lee Gwan Hee votes for Kim You Hyun.)

233
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:23,820
(Team R casts 5 votes for Kim You Hyun.)

234
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,360
As soon as voting began,
the first thing that came to mind was...

235
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:30,630
that we didn't have a lot of money left
in our fund.

236
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:34,100
I wanted to save our team fund
if I had no hope.

237
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:37,000
That's why the 1st team
I approached Team P3.

238
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:40,070
You Hyun... I see. Okay.

239
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:44,380
I'm not flat-out asking you to help me.

240
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:46,710
Or can I? So...

241
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,580
I thought they were the swing votes.

242
00:10:48,580 --> 00:10:50,650
Their votes could go either way.

243
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,690
Xitsuh has to vote in favor of Team P2.

244
00:10:52,690 --> 00:10:54,390
And you guys have to vote in their favor
with an extra vote ticket.

245
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:55,660
- Yes, with the extra vote ticket.
- Right.

246
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:57,660
Do you think you can vote in my favor
with the rest?

247
00:10:58,230 --> 00:11:00,360
I'll be honest.

248
00:11:00,490 --> 00:11:03,660
- Hye Seon will try to save Gwan Hee.
- Right.

249
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:07,330
As long as we're on the same page,
Jin Ho and I...

250
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:08,840
can vote in your favor.

251
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,670
I know You Hyun on a personal level.

252
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:14,810
I've known him for a long time,
and he's also a poker player.

253
00:11:15,180 --> 00:11:17,280
He came to us and asked for help.

254
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,580
So I was tempted to help him.

255
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:20,150
I wondered if I should just help him.

256
00:11:20,610 --> 00:11:22,880
But it wasn't reasonable
if I helped him because we were friends.

257
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,220
Given the situation,

258
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:26,890
we should make a decision
that will be advantageous to our team.

259
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:28,620
- Let's...
- With 30,000 dollars.

260
00:11:28,620 --> 00:11:30,790
- tell him we'd do it for 20,000 dollars.
- Yes.

261
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:32,230
It'd be better to sell our votes
at a cheap price.

262
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:34,400
- Can I approach? Or should I stay here?
- You may approach.

263
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,430
- Really?
- Yes.

264
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:39,330
I have a question.
Will you guys buy extra vote tickets?

265
00:11:39,330 --> 00:11:40,630
- All of us will buy one.
- We'll all buy it.

266
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:42,740
But if there's no hope of winning,
we won't.

267
00:11:42,740 --> 00:11:43,740
Here's our deal.

268
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:45,670
We have two votes we can offer.

269
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:49,240
For 1 ticket,
you'd have to spend 30,000 dollars.

270
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:51,510
we'll sell our 2 votes for 40,000 dollars.

271
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,310
I see. You'll sell your votes?

272
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:56,650
My vote and Seong Beom's vote
can go either way.

273
00:11:56,920 --> 00:12:00,050
We're not committed.
But I don't think it's fair to use them...

274
00:12:00,090 --> 00:12:02,990
for you or Gwan Hee blindly
without a reason.

275
00:12:03,490 --> 00:12:06,490
The bottom line is that we must try
to gain an advantage with our votes.

276
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:08,400
Then can't you give us a discount?

277
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,730
But that's how the talk should go.

278
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:14,570
A big part of me wants to help you.

279
00:12:14,570 --> 00:12:16,540
Let's go with 30,000 dollars
for 2 votes then.

280
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:17,570
Okay.

281
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:20,570
It's like getting a half off
on the extra vote ticket.

282
00:12:20,570 --> 00:12:22,510
I thought their offer was reasonable.

283
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:24,340
Kim You Hyun of Team Challenger...

284
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:26,150
will transfer 30,000 dollars...

285
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:28,280
from the team fund
to Heo Seong Beom of Team P3.

286
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,320
(Heo Seong Beom votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

287
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:35,560
(Hong Jin Ho votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

288
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:42,230
How did it go? You talked to Team P3.

289
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:45,330
Well, they said they wouldn't vote for me.

290
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:47,430
And Team P2 also said
they wouldn't vote for me either.

291
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:50,400
I'll just accept the outcome
and go if I have to.

292
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,970
I don't want to talk to people
and ask for their help again.

293
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:55,980
I don't know where Team P3 stands either.

294
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,080
If you vote for me, I'll guess I'll go.
Or the other way around.

295
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,480
I mean...

296
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:03,050
But be honest. You don't want to go home.

297
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,820
No one does. I came here to win.

298
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,960
I'm not here to be anyone's filler.
You know?

299
00:13:09,660 --> 00:13:11,830
It's been a while since I saw him.

300
00:13:11,830 --> 00:13:13,830
I wanted us to play games together.

301
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:17,630
I thought it would be nice
if I ended up in a position...

302
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:20,830
where I could help him.

303
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:24,470
He kept finding himself in a position
where elimination was a possibility.

304
00:13:25,010 --> 00:13:26,410
I felt bad for him.

305
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:28,440
- Let's talk.
- You'll vote for him?

306
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:33,710
You know what? I want you...

307
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,280
to come to my team and ask for our help.
You can say, "You guys are loaded."

308
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:40,120
"Could you buy some extra vote tickets
for me?" I want you to be more proactive.

309
00:13:40,190 --> 00:13:42,860
That could work in your favor.

310
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:46,130
I'll talk to Jin Ho.

311
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:49,560
I'm going to ask him how he'll pay me back
for helping him with the ropes.

312
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:52,530
No, don't say that.
Mention that we have a lot of money.

313
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:55,100
Ask him to spend some money to save you.

314
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,640
That's the way to go.

315
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,870
Coming from you would be more persuasive.

316
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:00,410
(Sighing)

317
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,440
And...

318
00:14:02,510 --> 00:14:03,540
And...

319
00:14:04,980 --> 00:14:06,580
we have a lot to talk about.

320
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:10,250
Well, to do that, I have to survive first.

321
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:13,120
Exactly. It's too soon for you
to go to the Deathmatch.

322
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:15,220
Ask Jin Ho to come here.

323
00:14:15,490 --> 00:14:17,160
I need to talk to him.

324
00:14:17,620 --> 00:14:19,190
I'll see if he wants to pay me back.

325
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:21,930
Actually, I'd feel a bit better...

326
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:24,260
if Gwan Hee was never...

327
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:26,330
in this kind of situation.

328
00:14:26,470 --> 00:14:28,970
I was determined to help him.

329
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:31,510
Will you all vote for You Hyun?

330
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:34,310
Well, it's really complicated for us.

331
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,980
- Where does your team stand?
- Yes?

332
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:38,380
Did you vote?

333
00:14:38,810 --> 00:14:39,850
Yes. I did.

334
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,720
- Yes.
- You already voted?

335
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:42,850
- Yes.
- What about you?

336
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,250
How did it go?

337
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,560
She looks like she's working harder now
than when she was playing with us.

338
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:51,730
- Does this make sense?
- She's working harder now...

339
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:52,890
than during the Money Challenge.

340
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:54,630
- Gosh, my feelings are hurt.
- I'm disappointed.

341
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,370
Between You Hyun and Gwan Hee,

342
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:02,070
I want Gwan Hee to survive.

343
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:05,570
So I want You Hyun and Sung Joo
to compete in the Deathmatch.

344
00:15:06,170 --> 00:15:09,610
(Choi Hye Seon votes for Kim You Hyun.)

345
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:13,080
Well... Hold on. Here's what I think.

346
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:15,120
Team P2 is the casting vote.

347
00:15:15,350 --> 00:15:17,450
- No way. They'll vote for me for sure.
- Here's why.

348
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,690
No. There's a reason behind it.

349
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:21,290
- Listen.
- I know. If Sung Joo competes...

350
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:22,790
against the player from Team Rookie...

351
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:25,830
- and wins, he'll have to join them.
- I know that.

352
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:28,660
The overall consensus in the mansion
was that You Hyun would go.

353
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:30,300
I was like, "That serves you right."

354
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,330
"See you later, jerk."
That's what I was thinking.

355
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,740
Then I changed my mind.
"I should save him."

356
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:41,580
- Team P2 wants to help Sung Joo survive.
- Okay.

357
00:15:41,610 --> 00:15:43,440
They want to help him survive.

358
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:45,010
Of course, he's on their team.

359
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:46,610
Of course. So listen.

360
00:15:46,610 --> 00:15:48,880
The odds of his survival
when going up against you...

361
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:52,490
If You Hyun were to get eliminated,

362
00:15:52,590 --> 00:15:55,260
I would have to invest more of my time...

363
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:57,790
and end up using up a lot of my energy
since Nam Hee and Ji Hoo...

364
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,460
aren't the leader material.

365
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:04,260
So I thought it would be better
to keep him alive for now.

366
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:06,470
Afterward, I quickly decided on my stance.

367
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:09,040
I started to go around the room
and frantically persuaded people.

368
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,440
Whom will you vote for?

369
00:16:12,970 --> 00:16:14,340
Have you decided?

370
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,010
- We have.
- On whom?

371
00:16:16,310 --> 00:16:17,710
Once I decided to help him,

372
00:16:17,710 --> 00:16:20,150
I knew this was a game of politics
since votes were involved.

373
00:16:20,210 --> 00:16:22,180
It was important to persuade everyone.

374
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,720
Can't you vote for Gwan Hee?

375
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:25,720
What?

376
00:16:28,990 --> 00:16:30,960
Can't you vote in our favor?

377
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:33,660
I need to vote for the player
for the Deathmatch, right?

378
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:34,900
Yes. That's correct.

379
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:36,560
(Lee Gwan Hee)

380
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:40,000
(Kim Kyoung Hoon votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

381
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:43,200
(Lee Gwan Hee)

382
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,010
I feel bad.

383
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:46,940
But I must save my teammate.

384
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,380
(Lee Gwan Hee)

385
00:16:49,380 --> 00:16:52,180
(Kang Ji Hoo votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

386
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:56,250
(Kim You Hyun votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

387
00:16:58,090 --> 00:16:59,090
All done.

388
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,390
Well,

389
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:05,430
- I'll be honest with you.
- Yes, please be honest with us.

390
00:17:05,430 --> 00:17:06,690
Now... Gosh.

391
00:17:07,690 --> 00:17:09,960
- You Hyun might be our choice.
- You're leaning toward him?

392
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:12,570
This factor was also crucial.

393
00:17:12,570 --> 00:17:15,100
Seung Jin is in a tight spot too.

394
00:17:15,570 --> 00:17:18,170
Gwan Hee is his direct junior
in the basketball scene.

395
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:21,580
- We must respect his opinion too.
- That's true.

396
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:24,480
So he's leaning toward voting
for You Hyun?

397
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,980
- Is that it?
- We didn't talk about it openly.

398
00:17:25,980 --> 00:17:28,780
I haven't had the chance to talk to him
since he's feeling down.

399
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:30,280
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

400
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,450
It's not easy for him to hide
given his build.

401
00:17:32,620 --> 00:17:34,490
- Right. He must be somewhere.
- Is it in his room?

402
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:40,330
I was trying to figure out
what to do alone in my room.

403
00:17:40,930 --> 00:17:42,960
I realized that
I shouldn't just sit there and space out.

404
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,280
My head is about to explode.

405
00:18:05,650 --> 00:18:08,090
Out of all my time from the second season
and this season,

406
00:18:08,460 --> 00:18:12,390
my heart was the heaviest when I walked
into the Voting Room that day.

407
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:19,670
(Sighing)

408
00:18:21,470 --> 00:18:22,740
(Kim You Hyun, Lee Gwan Hee)

409
00:18:40,690 --> 00:18:45,790
(Ha Seung Jin finishes casting his vote.)

410
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:53,200
(YunB finishes casting his vote.)

411
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:00,110
(Lee Jin Hyeong votes for Kim You Hyun.)

412
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:03,810
Did you buy extra vote tickets?

413
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:05,980
- What?
- Did you buy extra vote tickets?

414
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:07,250
How many tickets?

415
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:09,650
We were told
we could withdraw cash from outside.

416
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:13,150
Gwan Hee quickly ran to the ATM.

417
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,160
- He withdrew 600,000 dollars.
- He got 600,000 dollars?

418
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,820
- How many tickets then? Twenty tickets.
- Is that his annual salary?

419
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:17,960
Twenty tickets?

420
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:22,460
My attempt to persuade them
didn't seem to work.

421
00:19:23,130 --> 00:19:24,300
So I did some thinking.

422
00:19:24,630 --> 00:19:27,370
How many extra vote tickets should we buy?

423
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,340
Let's go all-in.
Let's play without any team funds.

424
00:19:30,570 --> 00:19:31,640
- It will be fun.
- But...

425
00:19:32,170 --> 00:19:33,670
Even if we do,
I don't think we can win this.

426
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,840
It's either we still won't win the vote
or the money will be wasted.

427
00:19:39,110 --> 00:19:40,780
Let's buy some. It's not real money.

428
00:19:42,650 --> 00:19:44,520
- No?
- I would if we could win the vote.

429
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:48,460
"It's not real money. Let's spend it."
That's what he said.

430
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:50,220
He didn't even calculate the numbers.

431
00:19:50,220 --> 00:19:52,560
No. I got it.

432
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:54,460
- Hey, we don't have time.
- Let's make a decision. Right.

433
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,430
You Hyun. Gosh.

434
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:58,030
- I think I lost the vote.
- What?

435
00:19:58,100 --> 00:20:00,800
- But... My gosh. This is crazy.
- You don't know that. Wait.

436
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,970
- Your opinion matters the most.
- What?

437
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:04,140
Your opinion matters the most.

438
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:05,840
We have 20 seconds left.

439
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:10,310
- Time's up. Don't buy them.
- What do we do? But...

440
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:13,180
- No.
- It's over.

441
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:15,520
It's over.

442
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:19,020
Kyoung Hoon had this sense of urgency
and asked me...

443
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:20,690
"Come on. What are we going to do?"

444
00:20:21,190 --> 00:20:22,560
I can just go and beat him.

445
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,190
I was up against Sung Joo.

446
00:20:26,530 --> 00:20:28,560
I was confident enough to beat him.

447
00:20:30,230 --> 00:20:31,970
Voting has ended.

448
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:39,740
The results of the vote will be announced.

449
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:42,410
The player heading to the Deathmatch is...

450
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:49,680
Lee Gwan Hee.

451
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:58,630
I was furious.

452
00:20:59,290 --> 00:21:02,830
The sense of betrayal filled me
from head to toe.

453
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:12,270
After seeing the results,

454
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:14,570
I thought
everyone in the room was a traitor.

455
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:17,380
If I were to report them,
they would've been arrested.

456
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:23,980
I mean, he agreed to be on the show.

457
00:21:23,980 --> 00:21:27,850
If he's going to fault you
and resent you for this after the show...

458
00:21:27,850 --> 00:21:29,190
- He'll just delete your number.
- Right.

459
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:30,920
If he's going to do that,
he shouldn't be on the show.

460
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:35,030
Sung Joo... Let's protect him.
It's a survival, after all.

461
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:37,260
Darn it. What do I do?

462
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:39,070
- Seriously.
- No one's going to criticize you.

463
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,570
But you can't help both of them.

464
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:48,380
For the sake of Sung Joo and our team,
we should go with that.

465
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:50,740
Strategically, this is the right call.

466
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:54,150
No one's going to criticize you.

467
00:21:56,420 --> 00:21:57,920
- Okay. Then...
- Yes.

468
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:00,520
let's go with your idea
and be more strategic.

469
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,620
- Thank you.
- Let's do that.

470
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:04,190
If only one of them could survive...

471
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:06,830
I thought, "Okay. That's not the point."

472
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:10,730
Putting everything aside,
I only wanted to focus...

473
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,430
on our strategy in the long run.

474
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,730
I felt so bad for Gwan Hee.

475
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:18,970
But I had no choice but to vote for him.

476
00:22:20,810 --> 00:22:25,550
(Ha Seung Jin votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

477
00:22:26,150 --> 00:22:28,720
It was the first time
the Voting Room felt so cruel.

478
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:32,020
I'll use the extra vote ticket
Team P3 has.

479
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:39,060
(Xitsuh of Team P3 uses
the extra vote ticket.)

480
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:42,400
(Xitsuh votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

481
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:45,100
(Lee Gwan Hee)

482
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,570
If we had openly supported...

483
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:53,170
Gwan Hee, at that very moment,

484
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:55,040
we would've looked like fools.

485
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,380
we would've been idiots.

486
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:59,480
If we were to support Gwan Hee openly,

487
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:02,050
they wouldn't spend money.

488
00:23:02,780 --> 00:23:04,580
So we should pretend...

489
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:07,290
that we'll vote for You Hyun.

490
00:23:07,550 --> 00:23:09,690
But we should vote for Gwan Hee instead.

491
00:23:10,090 --> 00:23:12,960
It's a chance to make Team C
spend the team fund.

492
00:23:13,090 --> 00:23:15,400
Trying to persuade Seung Jin...

493
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,430
was a genuine attempt. I wasn't faking it.

494
00:23:17,430 --> 00:23:19,330
I bet they felt the threat was stronger.

495
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:22,440
I decided to win this vote.

496
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:24,870
As for me,
during that one hour for the vote,

497
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:27,110
I was playing a game of whether or not...

498
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:28,810
I could turn the tables around.

499
00:23:28,810 --> 00:23:30,840
We should all buy an extra vote ticket.

500
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:33,210
I think it will work. Let's try it.

501
00:23:33,710 --> 00:23:35,750
Here's our tactic.

502
00:23:36,580 --> 00:23:38,080
We'll say since there's no way we'll win,

503
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:40,350
we won't buy the ticket.
But we'll actually buy a ticket each.

504
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:42,560
- I see.
- What do you think?

505
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:44,290
I'll buy an extra vote ticket.

506
00:23:45,290 --> 00:23:46,990
(Kyoung Hoon bought 2 extra vote tickets.)

507
00:23:46,990 --> 00:23:49,360
(Kyoung Hoon bought 3 extra vote tickets.)

508
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:51,630
(Kyoung Hoon bought 4 extra vote tickets.)

509
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:54,870
Team Challenger, 120,000 dollars
have been deducted from your team fund.

510
00:23:54,870 --> 00:23:56,940
(Team Challenger, 120,000 dollars
have been deducted from your team fund.)

511
00:23:56,940 --> 00:24:01,170
(Kim Kyoung Hoon votes for Lee Gwan Hee.)

512
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:03,810
Survival instincts kick in...

513
00:24:03,810 --> 00:24:05,450
during the Deathmatch.

514
00:24:07,210 --> 00:24:08,520
(Lee Gwan Hee: 14 votes,
Seung Jin, Jin Ho, Seong Beom,)

515
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,720
(Nam Hee, Kyoung Hoon, YunB,
Xitsuh, You Hyun, Ji Hoo)

516
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:10,920
(Kim You Hyun: 11 votes,
Sang Min, Ji Min, Jin Hyeong, Beom,)

517
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,150
(Gwan Hee, Keun Woo, Tae Gyun,
Hye Seon, Seung Yong)

518
00:24:12,650 --> 00:24:14,490
I felt humiliated and embarrassed
for my actions.

519
00:24:15,020 --> 00:24:16,260
I felt guilty toward Gwan Hee.

520
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:20,660
Seung Jin couldn't meet my eyes...

521
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:23,160
and had his head down. When I saw him,

522
00:24:23,530 --> 00:24:24,630
I was furious.

523
00:24:25,060 --> 00:24:27,770
Seung Jin and I used to
play basketball together.

524
00:24:27,930 --> 00:24:30,970
We've been through thick and thin
together. He's my senior.

525
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:32,270
How could he betray me?

526
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:35,280
These traitors said this to our faces.

527
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:36,980
"I'm going to vote for You Hyun."

528
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:38,310
Toward the end, I even thought...

529
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,780
we might not need to buy
the extra vote tickets.

530
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:42,580
Gwan Hee might survive and win the vote
even without the extra vote tickets.

531
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:44,880
But this was Bloody Game X, after all.

532
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,720
It was a game of traitors.

533
00:24:47,050 --> 00:24:49,320
Gwan Hee, leave the mansion immediately...

534
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:51,120
and get ready for the Deathmatch.

535
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:54,960
Good luck!

536
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,370
- My gosh.
- I've been betrayed.

537
00:25:03,370 --> 00:25:06,010
No matter who my opponent is,
I'm determined to win.

538
00:25:06,340 --> 00:25:08,440
The Deathmatch? It's not a problem.

539
00:25:09,980 --> 00:25:12,210
The lowest-ranking team
of the Money Game, Team P2,

540
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:15,520
head to the outdoor survival grounds
immediately.

541
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:19,590
Let's come back with vengeance.

542
00:25:19,590 --> 00:25:20,590
Let's go.

543
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:23,490
Let's kill it in the next main match.

544
00:25:23,790 --> 00:25:24,960
Let's play dirty.

545
00:25:25,660 --> 00:25:26,960
We'll crush everyone.

546
00:25:33,730 --> 00:25:37,140
Players of today's Deathmatch,
please enter the main hall.

547
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:44,110
Everyone here is a strong opponent.

548
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,780
There should be...

549
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:47,880
at least one easy target in every team.
But none of them look easy.

550
00:25:48,110 --> 00:25:50,820
You Hyun is the strongest opponent
out of everyone there.

551
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:53,620
I don't want a strong opponent
like You Hyun.

552
00:25:59,630 --> 00:26:03,860
(His opponent of the Deathmatch,
Lee Gwan Hee)

553
00:26:06,470 --> 00:26:07,570
I avoided the worst of it.

554
00:26:07,570 --> 00:26:09,100
It felt like Korea dodged Brazil.

555
00:26:09,470 --> 00:26:11,870
Well, he's a basketball player.

556
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:12,940
I felt relieved.

557
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:14,540
They won't make me do free throws.

558
00:26:14,710 --> 00:26:15,810
I think I can beat him.

559
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:18,950
- I have a reason to go back now.
- Yes.

560
00:26:18,950 --> 00:26:20,310
I guess you need to get even with someone.

561
00:26:21,010 --> 00:26:22,580
"How am I going to finish them
once I win?"

562
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:25,120
"How will I crush that stupid team?"
That was the only thing I was thinking.

563
00:26:25,390 --> 00:26:27,820
I wanted to destroy Team P2 myself.

564
00:26:31,060 --> 00:26:32,090
Lee Gwan Hee.

565
00:26:32,690 --> 00:26:33,730
Hyun Sung Joo.

566
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:37,030
You must play a 1-on-1 Deathmatch.

567
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,070
Here's today's Deathmatch.

568
00:26:41,630 --> 00:26:43,300
(3-Story Gomoku)

569
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:44,870
It's called Three-Story Gomoku.

570
00:26:46,140 --> 00:26:47,340
In Three-story Gomoku,

571
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:50,240
you can stack up the stones up
to three levels.

572
00:26:50,710 --> 00:26:52,950
Through your memorization skills
and strategic thinking skills,

573
00:26:53,150 --> 00:26:55,580
you must find the ways to win.

574
00:26:56,980 --> 00:27:00,550
The game will be played out on a board
made of a triangular grid.

575
00:27:01,190 --> 00:27:05,560
Each player will be given 25 stones.

576
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:10,130
Once the game begins,
you'll proceed with the basic arrangement.

577
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:13,800
The starting player will put down a stone.

578
00:27:14,230 --> 00:27:15,670
Afterward, the players will alternate...

579
00:27:15,870 --> 00:27:19,540
and put down 2 stones, 2 stones,
and 1 stone respectively.

580
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:23,810
During the basic arrangement,
you can't put down your stones...

581
00:27:24,210 --> 00:27:26,110
in the center spot...

582
00:27:26,110 --> 00:27:28,880
or next to your own stones.

583
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:31,880
Once the basic arrangement is over,

584
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,750
the players will alternate.

585
00:27:35,390 --> 00:27:38,860
They can choose 1 of these 2 actions
during their turn.

586
00:27:39,530 --> 00:27:41,830
The first action is putting down a stone.

587
00:27:42,460 --> 00:27:44,930
They can put down a new stone...

588
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:47,470
in any empty spot they want on the board.

589
00:27:48,330 --> 00:27:50,640
The second action is moving the stone.

590
00:27:51,370 --> 00:27:53,270
Players can move...

591
00:27:53,270 --> 00:27:56,680
one of their stones on the board
to a spot adjacent to their own stones.

592
00:27:57,380 --> 00:28:00,880
In this action, players are allowed
to stack up their stone on another stone.

593
00:28:01,710 --> 00:28:05,080
However,
the pile can only go up to three levels.

594
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:06,420
(Moving the stone)

595
00:28:06,420 --> 00:28:07,920
The stones...

596
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:11,490
can't move to a higher level
than where they started.

597
00:28:12,660 --> 00:28:14,990
There are three requirements
to win the game.

598
00:28:15,630 --> 00:28:17,860
The first one is completing the line.

599
00:28:18,700 --> 00:28:20,300
In the aerial view of the board,

600
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:24,040
a player that puts five consecutive stones
in a straight line wins the game.

601
00:28:24,900 --> 00:28:27,340
However, if there are six stones or more
in the line,

602
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:29,680
the line won't be considered complete.

603
00:28:30,380 --> 00:28:33,780
The 2nd requirement is
having 5 stones on the 3rd level.

604
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,050
Regardless of the location on the board,

605
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:39,920
a player with 5 stones
on the 3rd level wins the game.

606
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,050
(Victory)

607
00:28:41,050 --> 00:28:44,790
The 3rd requirement is
having 3 adjacent stones on the 3rd level.

608
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:47,460
A player with three adjacent stones...

609
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:49,560
on the third level wins the game.

610
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:50,560
(Victory)

611
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:54,300
If the players complete the requirements
at the same time,

612
00:28:54,730 --> 00:28:57,340
the player of that turn wins the game.

613
00:28:57,340 --> 00:28:58,440
(Victory)

614
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:00,540
The game consists of three rounds.

615
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:03,040
The player with two winning rounds...

616
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:05,240
will be the survivor of the Deathmatch.

617
00:29:05,510 --> 00:29:08,650
Three-Story Gomoku will begin shortly.

618
00:29:11,450 --> 00:29:12,520
I thought it was winnable.

619
00:29:12,650 --> 00:29:15,390
I had neither a big advantage
or a big disadvantage. It was winnable.

620
00:29:15,390 --> 00:29:16,360
That's how I felt.

621
00:29:16,620 --> 00:29:19,830
As for me, I practiced playing janggi,

622
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:22,560
gomoku, and Color Turn quite a lot.

623
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:24,030
When I saw the word, "gomoku,"

624
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:26,100
I thought I was going to win.

625
00:29:28,230 --> 00:29:31,070
The player who was voted
as the elimination candidate,

626
00:29:31,740 --> 00:29:33,810
Lee Gwan Hee, will decide
whether to go 1st or 2nd.

627
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,180
I'll go first.

628
00:29:36,710 --> 00:29:38,910
The starting player of Round One
will be Lee Gwan Hee.

629
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:41,350
Hyun Sung Joo will go second.

630
00:29:41,610 --> 00:29:43,850
Round One will begin now.

631
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:47,790
Gwan Hee, place a stone on the game board.

632
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:52,390
Sung Joo,
place two stones on the game board.

633
00:29:56,530 --> 00:29:57,630
Take your time.

634
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:13,780
Gwan Hee,
place two stones on the game board.

635
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:19,720
Like an actual game of gomoku,

636
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:21,120
I put my stones between his.

637
00:30:21,390 --> 00:30:23,720
I used the alternating-stone strategy.

638
00:30:25,860 --> 00:30:27,390
There were three ways
I could win this game.

639
00:30:27,830 --> 00:30:31,100
My strategy was to complete the line.

640
00:30:31,260 --> 00:30:33,230
I wanted to finish the game
within ten moves...

641
00:30:33,230 --> 00:30:34,570
before I began.

642
00:30:36,870 --> 00:30:39,770
Sung Joo,
place one stone on the game board.

643
00:30:43,780 --> 00:30:45,340
For regular gomoku,

644
00:30:45,340 --> 00:30:47,250
by expanding into and conquering areas
advantageous to you,

645
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:49,620
you end up winning the games
even when you don't have to try so hard.

646
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:51,320
I wasn't sure which was more important.

647
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:53,150
Expanding or stacking up the stones.

648
00:30:53,150 --> 00:30:54,320
It was hard to tell.

649
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:01,290
The basic arrangement is over.

650
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:03,860
Gwan Hee, you will begin.

651
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,810
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

652
00:31:14,010 --> 00:31:15,370
It's Sung Joo's turn.

653
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:21,280
Sung Joo put down a stone.

654
00:31:22,580 --> 00:31:23,950
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

655
00:31:29,990 --> 00:31:31,860
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

656
00:31:32,930 --> 00:31:34,890
My belief is offense is the best defense.

657
00:31:34,890 --> 00:31:37,160
That's what I believe in.

658
00:31:37,330 --> 00:31:40,430
I wanted to see his reaction
when I made a move.

659
00:31:40,570 --> 00:31:43,900
Setting the tone early on
is the most important.

660
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,580
He had four stones in a line.

661
00:31:54,980 --> 00:31:57,580
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

662
00:31:57,950 --> 00:31:59,820
I can just stack up my stone
in the middle.

663
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:01,420
I stacked it up with my gut instinct.

664
00:32:01,550 --> 00:32:03,390
I had no choice but to do that.

665
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:08,330
That was when I first realize
the power of stacking up the stones.

666
00:32:08,330 --> 00:32:09,530
The first time I stacked my stone on his.

667
00:32:09,830 --> 00:32:13,070
I realized it at that moment that
stacking up was the key to this game.

668
00:32:13,830 --> 00:32:15,100
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

669
00:32:20,210 --> 00:32:22,210
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

670
00:32:23,340 --> 00:32:24,810
It's Sung Joo's turn.

671
00:32:27,010 --> 00:32:29,280
(Nodding)

672
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:34,750
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

673
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,830
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

674
00:32:54,910 --> 00:32:57,580
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

675
00:32:57,910 --> 00:32:59,080
Once I started stacking them up,

676
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:01,080
I liked the view from above.

677
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:03,080
Once I stack it up,
he can't put his stone on mine...

678
00:33:03,350 --> 00:33:05,150
when I can go down to get in his way.

679
00:33:09,190 --> 00:33:11,820
I kept putting down my stones
on the first level.

680
00:33:12,290 --> 00:33:14,460
At one point,

681
00:33:14,460 --> 00:33:17,000
Sung Joo's stones were on top of mine.

682
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:19,770
To complete his line with five stones,

683
00:33:20,230 --> 00:33:23,240
I assumed that he would have to
bring down his stones at some point.

684
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:25,970
When he didn't bring down his stones,

685
00:33:26,210 --> 00:33:28,980
I sensed that I was in trouble.

686
00:33:34,310 --> 00:33:37,250
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

687
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:48,730
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the third level.

688
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:50,860
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

689
00:33:51,630 --> 00:33:53,570
Once I moved my stones on top of his,

690
00:33:53,570 --> 00:33:55,500
things got out of hand.

691
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:57,540
He didn't know what to do.

692
00:34:03,410 --> 00:34:05,540
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

693
00:34:06,710 --> 00:34:09,180
When kids in middle school
play gomoku on a notebook,

694
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:11,080
they keep trying to make a line...

695
00:34:11,080 --> 00:34:12,720
with four stones.

696
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:13,750
They keep expanding.

697
00:34:13,750 --> 00:34:15,590
But it looked like he was trying
to expand on the first level.

698
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:17,290
Well, I was grateful either way.

699
00:34:22,530 --> 00:34:25,330
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

700
00:34:31,140 --> 00:34:33,610
He kept blocking me
and then stacking up his stone on mine.

701
00:34:33,610 --> 00:34:37,680
Then I couldn't move my stones anywhere.

702
00:34:39,410 --> 00:34:42,550
(He can't move his stones
from the 1st level to the 3rd.)

703
00:34:47,750 --> 00:34:50,490
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

704
00:34:50,690 --> 00:34:52,860
When I stacked up my stones,
my opponent's options...

705
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:54,130
become very limited.

706
00:34:54,130 --> 00:34:55,560
But my options weren't limited at all.

707
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:57,900
My opponent didn't have a clear strategy
afterward.

708
00:35:04,540 --> 00:35:07,410
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the third level.

709
00:35:08,110 --> 00:35:09,880
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

710
00:35:10,510 --> 00:35:13,180
It felt like my heart was going to
jump out of my chest,

711
00:35:13,310 --> 00:35:15,180
so I could dribble with it.

712
00:35:15,650 --> 00:35:17,350
My heart was racing so fast then.

713
00:35:37,770 --> 00:35:40,670
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the first level.

714
00:35:44,740 --> 00:35:46,880
Sung Joo put down a stone.

715
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,720
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

716
00:36:00,460 --> 00:36:03,500
(If there's another black stone
on the 3rd level around his other stones,)

717
00:36:03,500 --> 00:36:04,530
(Sung Joo will win the game.)

718
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:11,440
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

719
00:36:11,500 --> 00:36:13,310
It's Sung Joo's turn.

720
00:36:28,150 --> 00:36:30,990
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

721
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:41,530
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

722
00:36:47,740 --> 00:36:49,040
Good work.

723
00:36:56,980 --> 00:36:58,750
It's Sung Joo's turn.

724
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:04,960
Sung Joo's three adjacent stones
are on the third level.

725
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,690
Round One goes to him.

726
00:37:06,690 --> 00:37:08,190
(Sung Joo wins Round 1 of 3-Story Gomoku.)

727
00:37:08,190 --> 00:37:09,760
I was bound to win.

728
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,700
It was guaranteed that I'd win Round One.

729
00:37:12,870 --> 00:37:14,730
As for the first round,

730
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:18,140
I underestimated Sung Joo.

731
00:37:18,170 --> 00:37:20,740
Pushing through the first round...

732
00:37:20,740 --> 00:37:23,980
with my initial strategy
was the reason of my defeat.

733
00:37:23,980 --> 00:37:27,450
I realized that I shouldn't think
of this game too simply.

734
00:37:27,450 --> 00:37:29,320
It felt like getting punched
by a hammer.

735
00:37:30,180 --> 00:37:32,820
Round Two will begin.

736
00:37:32,890 --> 00:37:34,450
The loser of the first round,

737
00:37:34,450 --> 00:37:37,620
Lee Gwan Hee, will decide who goes first.

738
00:37:37,620 --> 00:37:38,960
Okay. I'll go first.

739
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:41,560
You will proceed
with the basic arrangement.

740
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:44,560
Gwan Hee, place one stone on the board.

741
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:47,000
(Placing 1 white stone on the board)

742
00:37:47,230 --> 00:37:50,500
Sung Joo, place two stones on the board.

743
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:55,240
For the first round, I placed my stones...

744
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:57,740
around his stones for a zone defense.

745
00:38:01,810 --> 00:38:03,680
During the second round,
we were both focused...

746
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:04,820
on stacking up our stones.

747
00:38:04,820 --> 00:38:06,890
I didn't want to give him that chance.

748
00:38:06,890 --> 00:38:08,390
So I placed my stones
one spot away from his stone.

749
00:38:08,390 --> 00:38:10,860
(Placing his stones away
from the white stone)

750
00:38:10,860 --> 00:38:13,960
Gwan Hee, place two stones on the board.

751
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:24,740
Sung Joo, place one stone on the board.

752
00:38:29,310 --> 00:38:31,310
The basic arrangement is over.

753
00:38:31,380 --> 00:38:33,950
Gwan Hee, you will begin.

754
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:41,490
Gwan Hee put down a stone.

755
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:43,290
It's Sung Joo's turn.

756
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:54,000
Sung Joo put down a stone.

757
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:56,340
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

758
00:38:58,900 --> 00:39:01,810
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

759
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:03,810
After losing the first round,

760
00:39:03,810 --> 00:39:05,410
I changed my strategy right away.

761
00:39:05,410 --> 00:39:07,350
"I have to stack up my stones."

762
00:39:07,350 --> 00:39:11,120
I thought dominating the second level
was the most important move.

763
00:39:18,790 --> 00:39:21,660
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

764
00:39:22,430 --> 00:39:23,460
It was annoying.

765
00:39:23,460 --> 00:39:25,430
I could tell that
he took a page from my playbook.

766
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,530
I was determined...

767
00:39:27,530 --> 00:39:29,940
to stack my stone to the second level
when his stone was near mine.

768
00:39:29,940 --> 00:39:31,770
After I stacked them up 1 or 2 times,

769
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:34,640
Sung Joo stopped putting
his stone next to mine...

770
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:36,710
with the anticipation that
I'd stack my stone on his.

771
00:39:41,610 --> 00:39:43,350
(Stopping)

772
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,590
"What if he stacks his stone on mine
when I place it there?"

773
00:39:48,550 --> 00:39:50,660
Sung Joo put down a stone.

774
00:39:50,690 --> 00:39:52,660
I wanted to limit...

775
00:39:52,660 --> 00:39:55,060
the area of his expansion on the board.

776
00:39:55,230 --> 00:39:57,100
I made sure while closing in on his area,

777
00:39:57,100 --> 00:39:58,700
he wouldn't be able to take my stones.

778
00:39:58,700 --> 00:40:00,800
That was the strategy I went with.

779
00:40:01,570 --> 00:40:03,300
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

780
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,240
Unlike the first round,

781
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:07,910
he didn't put his stones between mine.

782
00:40:07,910 --> 00:40:09,480
He put down his stones far from mine.

783
00:40:09,580 --> 00:40:10,680
So...

784
00:40:14,780 --> 00:40:17,720
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

785
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:21,120
I placed 4 stones on the 2nd level,

786
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:24,020
so I could have four stones in a line.

787
00:40:24,390 --> 00:40:26,230
It's Sung Joo's turn.

788
00:40:29,700 --> 00:40:32,930
Stacking up the stones was the way to go
in order to win.

789
00:40:32,930 --> 00:40:33,970
Putting myself...

790
00:40:33,970 --> 00:40:36,740
in a more advantageous position
by stacking up was important.

791
00:40:40,670 --> 00:40:42,710
Sung Joo put down a stone.

792
00:40:42,710 --> 00:40:43,840
(Sung Joo is targeting the white stone
on the 1st level.)

793
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:45,710
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

794
00:40:55,590 --> 00:40:58,520
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

795
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:03,000
When we began the round,
he stacked his stone on mine.

796
00:41:03,300 --> 00:41:06,200
(1 of his black stones had been taken
in the beginning.)

797
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:07,500
That was...

798
00:41:07,500 --> 00:41:08,530
It felt like a huge loss.

799
00:41:08,530 --> 00:41:11,470
It made me wonder
if going first was crucial for this game.

800
00:41:11,470 --> 00:41:14,070
Once he ended up with several stones
on the second level in the middle,

801
00:41:14,070 --> 00:41:16,310
I hoped I could get lucky
while playing defense.

802
00:41:16,310 --> 00:41:18,080
I was focused on getting in his way.

803
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:20,250
Sung Joo put down a stone.

804
00:41:20,780 --> 00:41:23,120
I saw it with my own eyes
that my initial strategy...

805
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,550
was wrong.

806
00:41:24,550 --> 00:41:28,190
I thought I should think more carefully
for each move I made.

807
00:41:28,190 --> 00:41:29,990
I thought very carefully
before putting down my stone.

808
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:31,920
(Gwan Hee plays defense again.)

809
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:34,560
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

810
00:41:45,700 --> 00:41:48,010
You must play your turn within 30 seconds.

811
00:41:49,810 --> 00:41:51,310
I thought this round was over.

812
00:41:51,410 --> 00:41:53,010
I didn't see any way to win this.

813
00:41:53,380 --> 00:41:55,580
It didn't matter where I placed my stones.

814
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:57,180
Gwan Hee could place his white stone...

815
00:41:57,180 --> 00:42:00,250
in the empty spot on the far right.

816
00:42:00,350 --> 00:42:02,250
Once he had four stones in a line,
it was over.

817
00:42:02,590 --> 00:42:04,320
Even if I put down a stone
on the far left,

818
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:06,090
he could move his stone down
to the first level.

819
00:42:07,330 --> 00:42:09,290
Even if I stacked my stone on top of his,

820
00:42:09,290 --> 00:42:12,100
since he had a pile of two white stones
next to mine,

821
00:42:12,100 --> 00:42:13,470
he could stack up his stone
to the third level.

822
00:42:13,470 --> 00:42:16,440
I was bound to lose in a few moves.

823
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:18,340
In the end, the round was over.

824
00:42:18,340 --> 00:42:20,770
I should have folded there
if I was up against a high-level player.

825
00:42:27,610 --> 00:42:30,080
Sung Joo put down a stone.

826
00:42:30,650 --> 00:42:32,050
I put down my stone there for a reason.

827
00:42:32,150 --> 00:42:33,250
I was baiting him.

828
00:42:33,250 --> 00:42:34,850
If he stacked up his stone on mine...

829
00:42:34,850 --> 00:42:36,490
and moved his stone from the second level,

830
00:42:36,490 --> 00:42:38,560
I would be able to prolong the round.

831
00:42:39,020 --> 00:42:40,490
I threw him some bait...

832
00:42:40,490 --> 00:42:41,560
because...

833
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:43,400
it's possible that he missed it.
We're all human.

834
00:42:43,500 --> 00:42:45,130
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

835
00:42:53,940 --> 00:42:58,040
(Once Gwan Hee has 4 stones in a line,
he will win the round.)

836
00:43:01,850 --> 00:43:04,680
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

837
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:06,890
It's Sung Joo's turn.

838
00:43:07,890 --> 00:43:09,590
He missed the opportunity.

839
00:43:09,590 --> 00:43:11,260
He could have easily secured the area.

840
00:43:11,260 --> 00:43:13,790
He suddenly moved his stone
to the second level...

841
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:17,660
Sung Joo put down a stone.

842
00:43:21,530 --> 00:43:25,670
I kept trying to line up four stones
on the bottom.

843
00:43:25,670 --> 00:43:27,740
In case he'd move his stone
to the second level,

844
00:43:27,740 --> 00:43:30,940
I made a different move
than making a four-stone line.

845
00:43:30,940 --> 00:43:34,510
Then completing four stones in a line
became harder for me.

846
00:43:36,150 --> 00:43:39,690
(Sung Joo's bait became a threat.)

847
00:43:42,020 --> 00:43:45,120
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

848
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:52,360
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

849
00:43:52,560 --> 00:43:54,470
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

850
00:43:59,270 --> 00:44:02,240
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the third level.

851
00:44:07,380 --> 00:44:08,510
It was a mistake on his part.

852
00:44:08,510 --> 00:44:11,180
But I did think that he could make
that mistake when we were playing.

853
00:44:12,820 --> 00:44:14,750
I mean, he could have taken my stones.

854
00:44:14,750 --> 00:44:16,920
But he kept trying to pile up
his stones instead.

855
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:20,890
He must've been too focused
on stacking up his stones.

856
00:44:20,890 --> 00:44:23,500
His strategy wasn't that effective.

857
00:44:23,500 --> 00:44:24,560
(Gwan Hee stacked up
only on his own stones.)

858
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:25,560
After I saw him make a mistake,

859
00:44:25,560 --> 00:44:27,570
I was hoping he would make another one...

860
00:44:27,670 --> 00:44:29,000
when we were playing.

861
00:44:31,870 --> 00:44:34,340
(Sung Joo is waiting for Gwan Hee
to make a mistake.)

862
00:44:43,920 --> 00:44:45,880
Sung Joo has put down a stone.

863
00:44:50,490 --> 00:44:51,520
It was such a shame.

864
00:44:51,520 --> 00:44:55,290
The stones that were spread out...

865
00:44:55,290 --> 00:44:56,530
have found a line.

866
00:45:09,170 --> 00:45:10,980
Gwan Hee has put down a stone.

867
00:45:12,210 --> 00:45:13,810
It's Sung Joo's turn.

868
00:45:27,560 --> 00:45:30,260
Sung Joo moved his stone
to the second level.

869
00:45:30,960 --> 00:45:32,560
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

870
00:45:40,010 --> 00:45:42,840
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the second level.

871
00:45:43,480 --> 00:45:45,080
It's Sung Joo's turn.

872
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:51,580
Gwan Hee moved his stone
to the third level.

873
00:45:52,380 --> 00:45:53,920
It's Gwan Hee's turn.

874
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:10,170
Sung Joo has put down a stone.

875
00:46:10,170 --> 00:46:11,700
(Sung Joo completed
five stones in a line.)

876
00:46:11,940 --> 00:46:13,810
Sung Joo completed five stones in a line.

877
00:46:13,810 --> 00:46:15,270
Round Two goes to him.

878
00:46:15,270 --> 00:46:16,270
(Sung Joo wins Round 2 of 3-Story Gomoku.)

879
00:46:17,910 --> 00:46:20,480
The final winner is Sung Joo.

880
00:46:21,250 --> 00:46:22,780
The game has ended.

881
00:46:23,180 --> 00:46:24,620
There's this saying in poker.

882
00:46:24,620 --> 00:46:25,620
"No matter how much you think about it,"

883
00:46:25,620 --> 00:46:29,150
"that first gut feeling you had
is probably the most accurate."

884
00:46:29,390 --> 00:46:31,090
I knew I was bound to win.

885
00:46:35,330 --> 00:46:36,730
I'm really sad.

886
00:46:36,730 --> 00:46:37,800
Good game.

887
00:46:38,260 --> 00:46:39,730
- It was an honor.
- No, it was mine.

888
00:46:44,300 --> 00:46:46,270
I was really upset,

889
00:46:46,270 --> 00:46:47,670
and I thought, "This is all I got?"

890
00:46:47,910 --> 00:46:49,640
"Was my strategy wrong?"

891
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,080
I tried reviewing it many times,

892
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:53,450
and I concluded
that I met a strong opponent...

893
00:46:53,450 --> 00:46:54,580
despite doing the best I could.

894
00:46:54,710 --> 00:46:56,850
The Deathmatch has come to an end.

895
00:46:57,150 --> 00:46:58,920
Please gather in the main hall.

896
00:47:00,490 --> 00:47:01,890
I wonder who won.

897
00:47:02,390 --> 00:47:03,660
The result...

898
00:47:08,190 --> 00:47:09,900
Gosh, someone's coming.

899
00:47:11,330 --> 00:47:13,370
- Great job.
- Well done.

900
00:47:14,070 --> 00:47:15,070
Gosh.

901
00:47:16,230 --> 00:47:17,770
Welcome.

902
00:47:18,300 --> 00:47:19,300
Welcome.

903
00:47:19,300 --> 00:47:21,110
- Good.
- Great work.

904
00:47:22,070 --> 00:47:23,780
Gosh, this isn't easy.

905
00:47:26,810 --> 00:47:29,210
I'll announce the results
of the Deathmatch.

906
00:47:30,050 --> 00:47:32,920
The second player to get eliminated
from Bloody Game X is...

907
00:47:34,120 --> 00:47:35,190
(Lee Gwan Hee)

908
00:47:35,190 --> 00:47:37,860
It's Lee Gwan Hee.

909
00:47:45,700 --> 00:47:47,830
Lee Gwan Hee, pack up your belongings...

910
00:47:47,830 --> 00:47:50,140
and leave the Bloody Mansion now.

911
00:47:55,110 --> 00:47:56,440
- Survive until the end.
- The eliminated member...

912
00:47:56,440 --> 00:47:59,780
may never return to Bloody Game X.

913
00:48:01,450 --> 00:48:02,450
Great job.

914
00:48:02,450 --> 00:48:03,850
Good work!

915
00:48:09,090 --> 00:48:10,960
It's really disappointing.

916
00:48:11,990 --> 00:48:15,360
Bloody Game is a ruthless program.

917
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:18,130
I thought it suited me really well.

918
00:48:18,130 --> 00:48:21,570
Actually, we can't form a strong bond
over just two days.

919
00:48:21,570 --> 00:48:22,830
Gosh, it's really cold.

920
00:48:22,970 --> 00:48:24,100
Thank you.

921
00:48:27,170 --> 00:48:28,770
I told you it'd work!

922
00:48:29,940 --> 00:48:33,350
- I told you it'd work! Gosh.
- I can't believe that worked.

923
00:48:33,350 --> 00:48:34,450
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

924
00:48:34,450 --> 00:48:36,080
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!

925
00:48:36,310 --> 00:48:37,320
Okay.

926
00:48:37,520 --> 00:48:38,820
But being here,

927
00:48:39,320 --> 00:48:42,120
I was really sad to see
Yeon Cheong leave...

928
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:43,760
when I spent only a day with her.

929
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:46,560
I felt really bad for my teammates,

930
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:48,730
Still, it was fun.

931
00:48:49,060 --> 00:48:53,200
Also, I got to appear on the show
that I really love,

932
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:55,700
so I crossed an item off my bucket list.

933
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:07,050
Darn it.

934
00:49:07,450 --> 00:49:09,450
What do I do? I feel so bad for Gwan Hee.

935
00:49:09,450 --> 00:49:10,880
I felt really bad.

936
00:49:12,680 --> 00:49:15,250
I don't understand
why I keep doing things...

937
00:49:15,250 --> 00:49:16,920
I'd regret later
whenever I'm on Bloody Game.

938
00:49:19,160 --> 00:49:20,160
I feel like an idiot.

939
00:49:21,660 --> 00:49:23,260
I felt bad.

940
00:49:23,260 --> 00:49:26,460
We didn't get to play
a proper game together,

941
00:49:26,460 --> 00:49:27,570
so it was really disappointing.

942
00:49:27,570 --> 00:49:30,170
Let's play a game together next time
when we get a chance.

943
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:33,740
How mean.

944
00:49:36,110 --> 00:49:38,440
I wished Gwan Hee would survive.

945
00:49:38,910 --> 00:49:40,780
I wanted to play a game with him
just one more time.

946
00:49:41,280 --> 00:49:43,720
More than anything, I felt sorry.

947
00:49:43,720 --> 00:49:46,280
If we played well in the first place,

948
00:49:46,280 --> 00:49:48,520
this wouldn't have happened.

949
00:49:48,850 --> 00:49:50,920
I resented Team P2 a bit.

950
00:49:51,760 --> 00:49:53,960
I didn't really feel good about it.

951
00:50:02,230 --> 00:50:03,340
As a result of the Deathmatch,

952
00:50:03,540 --> 00:50:05,900
Team Rookie lost a player
due to an elimination.

953
00:50:07,040 --> 00:50:09,610
Sung Joo,
who survived from the Deathmatch,

954
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:11,510
will follow the rule...

955
00:50:11,510 --> 00:50:13,910
and join Team Rookie.

956
00:50:15,010 --> 00:50:18,850
Team P2's Sung Joo, please move your seat.

957
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:21,090
What, you're a rookie now?

958
00:50:21,090 --> 00:50:22,090
He's a rookie!

959
00:50:22,090 --> 00:50:23,090
A new rookie.

960
00:50:23,090 --> 00:50:24,520
Please take good care of me.

961
00:50:24,620 --> 00:50:25,620
Hello.

962
00:50:28,890 --> 00:50:29,930
It's for the best.

963
00:50:29,930 --> 00:50:31,660
- Yes.
- It's for the best.

964
00:50:31,660 --> 00:50:32,760
As long as he survived.

965
00:50:33,160 --> 00:50:35,170
I sent Gwan Hee away with regret,

966
00:50:35,170 --> 00:50:37,170
but we managed to keep Sung Joo alive.

967
00:50:37,170 --> 00:50:40,110
There's a possibility Team C
used up their funds a lot.

968
00:50:40,410 --> 00:50:42,470
Team Rookie has Sung Joo.

969
00:50:43,140 --> 00:50:45,640
If us three teams unite,

970
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:47,510
we could be stronger.

971
00:50:47,650 --> 00:50:49,680
I'm okay as long as Sung Joo survives.

972
00:50:49,810 --> 00:50:53,120
Welcome Sung Joo as the national treasure.

973
00:50:53,350 --> 00:50:54,650
Form a strong bond,

974
00:50:55,090 --> 00:50:56,390
Sung Joo and Team Rookie.

975
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:57,760
I'll pull the weight of two people.

976
00:50:59,660 --> 00:51:00,960
You suit our team.

977
00:51:01,490 --> 00:51:03,130
Do you think so?

978
00:51:04,030 --> 00:51:05,560
I was happy inside.

979
00:51:07,170 --> 00:51:08,170
Is this all right?

980
00:51:08,870 --> 00:51:10,540
The gap is huge.

981
00:51:10,540 --> 00:51:14,110
Having a person you can't trust
on the team is a big thing.

982
00:51:14,110 --> 00:51:17,410
I wanted to go to a team
I could devote myself to.

983
00:51:17,510 --> 00:51:19,640
And everyone on Team Rookie was likeable.

984
00:51:21,050 --> 00:51:23,310
Here's our conflicting interests.

985
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:25,780
Team P3 got the money,

986
00:51:25,980 --> 00:51:27,590
but they sold two votes at half price.

987
00:51:27,590 --> 00:51:28,820
- That's right.
- Two votes.

988
00:51:28,820 --> 00:51:30,990
I owe every team,

989
00:51:30,990 --> 00:51:31,990
whether it's big or small.

990
00:51:32,620 --> 00:51:34,430
And I owe you guys the most.

991
00:51:34,560 --> 00:51:37,060
So, the basic direction would be...

992
00:51:37,430 --> 00:51:40,470
teaming up with P1
if other teams form an alliance.

993
00:51:40,470 --> 00:51:43,000
If it becomes iffy,

994
00:51:43,470 --> 00:51:46,740
I'll be the worst jerk ever.

995
00:51:47,370 --> 00:51:49,640
The thought that occurred to me
after surviving...

996
00:51:49,640 --> 00:51:52,080
was how surprised and grateful I was...

997
00:51:52,080 --> 00:51:54,210
to Kyoung Hoon for what he did.

998
00:51:54,350 --> 00:51:56,310
I had to pay it back, no matter what.

999
00:51:56,410 --> 00:51:59,880
I have conflicting interests
with everyone, and I owe them all.

1000
00:52:00,590 --> 00:52:03,790
I'll pretend to help them
since they helped me,

1001
00:52:04,720 --> 00:52:06,620
and I'll just lie to everyone.

1002
00:52:06,620 --> 00:52:08,360
- Oh, you will...
- Yes.

1003
00:52:08,490 --> 00:52:11,030
I'll lie to the people who helped me,

1004
00:52:11,030 --> 00:52:14,430
and I'll share false information
with them.

1005
00:52:14,430 --> 00:52:15,970
So that our team wouldn't be confused,

1006
00:52:15,970 --> 00:52:17,940
make sure of where you stand.

1007
00:52:18,300 --> 00:52:20,370
I'm good at going along with it slyly,

1008
00:52:20,570 --> 00:52:22,040
- So...
- Yes, I'm good at it.

1009
00:52:22,270 --> 00:52:23,810
- I'll go stir things around.
- Okay.

1010
00:52:29,210 --> 00:52:32,320
Please gather in the main hall.

1011
00:52:34,250 --> 00:52:37,120
We will now begin today's Money Challenge.

1012
00:52:38,120 --> 00:52:40,560
Depending on the results
of today's Money Challenge,

1013
00:52:41,430 --> 00:52:42,660
everyone...

1014
00:52:45,730 --> 00:52:47,400
on one team will be eliminated.

1015
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:48,770
- Gosh.
- Gosh.

1016
00:52:48,770 --> 00:52:49,870
Goodness.

1017
00:52:50,370 --> 00:52:51,570
Gosh.

1018
00:52:52,240 --> 00:52:53,510
So it's true
that a whole team will be gone.

1019
00:52:54,010 --> 00:52:55,270
We started the show...

1020
00:52:55,540 --> 00:52:58,640
with 20 people, unlike previous seasons.

1021
00:52:59,240 --> 00:53:01,310
And only two people got eliminated.

1022
00:53:02,050 --> 00:53:03,050
I thought it was too slow.

1023
00:53:03,180 --> 00:53:04,620
Soon, or tomorrow,

1024
00:53:05,020 --> 00:53:06,280
a whole team could get eliminated.

1025
00:53:06,620 --> 00:53:07,620
We talked about that.

1026
00:53:08,020 --> 00:53:09,920
As soon as we talked about that,
it was announced.

1027
00:53:09,920 --> 00:53:11,020
A whole team elimination?

1028
00:53:13,020 --> 00:53:15,160
It's brutal.
It means a whole team will be gone.

1029
00:53:15,160 --> 00:53:16,160
Gosh.

1030
00:53:18,360 --> 00:53:19,730
We must win, no matter what.

1031
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:22,130
It's not just about my elimination.

1032
00:53:22,130 --> 00:53:23,570
Our team's elimination...

1033
00:53:24,770 --> 00:53:27,210
is too much pressure and responsibility.

1034
00:53:27,810 --> 00:53:28,870
Let's win, no matter what.

1035
00:53:29,170 --> 00:53:31,710
So many people...

1036
00:53:32,710 --> 00:53:33,950
are getting eliminated in earnest.

1037
00:53:33,950 --> 00:53:35,810
What matters is what happens from now.

1038
00:53:35,810 --> 00:53:37,480
In case more people get eliminated
toward the end,

1039
00:53:37,480 --> 00:53:39,650
it'll be important
to form good relationships...

1040
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:41,650
so I could do well.

1041
00:53:42,320 --> 00:53:44,890
I thought the advice
from the other guys was right.

1042
00:53:45,520 --> 00:53:47,260
The winning team
of today's Money Challenge...

1043
00:53:47,660 --> 00:53:49,560
will get 50,000 dollars.

1044
00:53:50,230 --> 00:53:52,530
The teams that end up in
4th and 5th place...

1045
00:53:52,530 --> 00:53:54,830
will automatically have a team Deathmatch.

1046
00:53:55,930 --> 00:53:58,500
The losing team's members
will all be eliminated,

1047
00:53:59,040 --> 00:54:01,370
and the winning team
will leave the mansion...

1048
00:54:01,370 --> 00:54:03,410
and move to the outdoor survival grounds.

1049
00:54:03,410 --> 00:54:04,540
The team in fourth place
will go to the outdoor survival grounds?

1050
00:54:05,340 --> 00:54:06,410
The team in fourth place has to leave too?

1051
00:54:06,410 --> 00:54:07,580
Before the game begins,

1052
00:54:07,580 --> 00:54:09,350
there's one more announcement.

1053
00:54:10,150 --> 00:54:12,750
Last night, the Pandora's Safe was opened,

1054
00:54:12,750 --> 00:54:16,290
so every game item's price doubled.

1055
00:54:18,160 --> 00:54:19,390
Someone must've opened it.

1056
00:54:20,360 --> 00:54:22,760
A regular item is 20,000 dollars.

1057
00:54:23,290 --> 00:54:26,100
A hidden item is 40,000 dollars.

1058
00:54:26,970 --> 00:54:29,070
I thought we had the Pandora's Safe again,

1059
00:54:29,370 --> 00:54:31,570
but to our team, it was good news.

1060
00:54:31,940 --> 00:54:33,040
We're rich.

1061
00:54:33,370 --> 00:54:34,910
We have a lot of money anyway.

1062
00:54:35,340 --> 00:54:36,570
The price could go higher,

1063
00:54:36,940 --> 00:54:38,580
so the other teams couldn't buy any items.

1064
00:54:38,580 --> 00:54:41,650
Now, today's Money Challenge
will be revealed.

1065
00:54:42,710 --> 00:54:44,280
Today's Money Challenge...

1066
00:54:45,480 --> 00:54:47,050
(Blind Auction)

1067
00:54:47,050 --> 00:54:49,590
is Blind Auction.

1068
00:54:49,590 --> 00:54:50,620
(Blind Auction)

1069
00:54:51,060 --> 00:54:54,760
Blind Auction will be a team game
among five teams.

1070
00:54:55,230 --> 00:54:58,860
You must predict the worth of
an item card whose price isn't revealed.

1071
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:00,970
Through a strategic auction,

1072
00:55:00,970 --> 00:55:04,070
you must secure an item
that has a higher worth.

1073
00:55:05,300 --> 00:55:07,840
Each team will receive
11 numbered cubes...

1074
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:10,040
with different par values.

1075
00:55:10,410 --> 00:55:14,110
The cubes will be used
to win listing cards from the bids.

1076
00:55:14,580 --> 00:55:17,550
Listing cards compose of 22 item cards...

1077
00:55:17,550 --> 00:55:20,420
and eight special cards.

1078
00:55:21,020 --> 00:55:22,320
When the game begins,

1079
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:25,490
the total amount
of the 22 listing cards...

1080
00:55:25,490 --> 00:55:27,060
will be revealed.

1081
00:55:27,860 --> 00:55:30,090
In a round,
there will be a strategy meeting...

1082
00:55:30,090 --> 00:55:32,130
and listing bidding.

1083
00:55:32,560 --> 00:55:33,900
When a bidding starts,

1084
00:55:33,900 --> 00:55:36,900
one member from each team
will participate.

1085
00:55:37,940 --> 00:55:39,500
Among 30 listing cards,

1086
00:55:39,500 --> 00:55:41,770
a random card will be chosen.

1087
00:55:41,940 --> 00:55:43,570
That's when the bidding starts.

1088
00:55:44,710 --> 00:55:47,650
Here's how listing card bidding
will proceed.

1089
00:55:48,680 --> 00:55:51,720
The first player could submit a bid,

1090
00:55:51,980 --> 00:55:53,750
or they could give up on bidding.

1091
00:55:54,320 --> 00:55:56,820
The next player must make a bigger bid...

1092
00:55:56,820 --> 00:55:58,990
than the previous player,

1093
00:55:59,160 --> 00:56:00,990
or they could give up on bidding.

1094
00:56:01,490 --> 00:56:04,630
You can submit various combinations
of cubes,

1095
00:56:05,030 --> 00:56:06,660
but you can't retrieve...

1096
00:56:06,660 --> 00:56:10,200
the cubes you submitted
until you give up on bidding.

1097
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:12,870
If everyone else except for one player...

1098
00:56:12,870 --> 00:56:15,110
gives up on bidding,

1099
00:56:15,270 --> 00:56:18,540
the remaining player
will win the item card.

1100
00:56:18,680 --> 00:56:21,010
The player who won the item card...

1101
00:56:21,010 --> 00:56:24,280
can check how much the item card is worth.

1102
00:56:25,150 --> 00:56:28,390
Here's how the special card bidding
will proceed.

1103
00:56:28,890 --> 00:56:31,790
Special cards compose of
four profit cards...

1104
00:56:31,790 --> 00:56:34,160
and four loss cards.

1105
00:56:34,360 --> 00:56:37,700
The power of the card will be
revealed before the bidding starts.

1106
00:56:38,300 --> 00:56:41,230
The first player submits cubes
without revealing them...

1107
00:56:41,230 --> 00:56:42,430
and does bidding.

1108
00:56:42,930 --> 00:56:47,070
Every player must submit
at least one cube.

1109
00:56:47,810 --> 00:56:49,610
Once every team is done bidding,

1110
00:56:49,610 --> 00:56:52,040
the team that won the card
will be revealed.

1111
00:56:52,540 --> 00:56:53,980
If it's a profit card,

1112
00:56:53,980 --> 00:56:57,520
the team with the highest bid will win it.

1113
00:56:58,020 --> 00:56:59,480
If it's a loss card,

1114
00:56:59,480 --> 00:57:01,790
the team with the lowest bid...

1115
00:57:01,790 --> 00:57:03,420
will win it.

1116
00:57:04,090 --> 00:57:05,560
As for the special card bidding,

1117
00:57:05,560 --> 00:57:08,130
the amount that each team bid
won't be revealed.

1118
00:57:08,130 --> 00:57:11,100
Regardless of winning the bid or not,

1119
00:57:11,100 --> 00:57:12,300
the cubes you submitted
cannot be retrieved.

1120
00:57:12,760 --> 00:57:15,830
If more than two teams won the bid,

1121
00:57:16,100 --> 00:57:18,570
the teams that won the bid will bid again.

1122
00:57:18,770 --> 00:57:22,070
If there are more than two teams
that won after rebidding,

1123
00:57:22,070 --> 00:57:23,740
the profit card will become invalid,

1124
00:57:23,840 --> 00:57:27,580
and the power of the loss card
will take effect on all winning teams.

1125
00:57:28,750 --> 00:57:31,320
Once the first special card bidding ends,

1126
00:57:31,650 --> 00:57:33,250
the hidden item will be revealed.

1127
00:57:33,790 --> 00:57:36,120
Once the second special card bidding ends,

1128
00:57:36,650 --> 00:57:39,520
the ranks of the total price
of the item cards each team has...

1129
00:57:39,520 --> 00:57:40,560
will be revealed.

1130
00:57:40,790 --> 00:57:43,460
Once the third special card
is revealed on listing,

1131
00:57:44,000 --> 00:57:45,960
there will be no bidding,

1132
00:57:45,960 --> 00:57:47,970
and the game
will come to an end immediately.

1133
00:57:48,570 --> 00:57:51,500
Once the game ends,
the total price of the item cards...

1134
00:57:51,500 --> 00:57:53,870
that the teams have will be added,

1135
00:57:53,870 --> 00:57:55,340
and the ranks will be decided accordingly.

1136
00:57:55,810 --> 00:58:00,080
The team with the lowest total par value
of the cubes...

1137
00:58:00,380 --> 00:58:02,580
will lose 50 percent of the total price...

1138
00:58:02,580 --> 00:58:04,880
of the item cards they own as a penalty.

1139
00:58:05,350 --> 00:58:08,190
The teams in 4th and 5th places...

1140
00:58:08,190 --> 00:58:10,390
will have a team Deathmatch.

1141
00:58:11,690 --> 00:58:15,260
If there's a team that uses up
all the cubes,

1142
00:58:15,430 --> 00:58:18,460
that team will end up at the bottom.

1143
00:58:19,000 --> 00:58:22,570
There are three kinds of items
in Blind Auction.

1144
00:58:22,830 --> 00:58:26,400
The first item is a cube numbered five.

1145
00:58:27,100 --> 00:58:29,770
You can use this when bidding.

1146
00:58:30,810 --> 00:58:34,680
The second item is
median value check coupon.

1147
00:58:35,480 --> 00:58:37,350
Among the 22 item cards,

1148
00:58:37,620 --> 00:58:40,520
you can check the name...

1149
00:58:40,520 --> 00:58:42,750
and the value of the item card
in 11th place.

1150
00:58:43,520 --> 00:58:46,060
The third item is a hidden item.

1151
00:58:46,490 --> 00:58:49,860
It'll be revealed
after the first special card bidding.

1152
00:58:50,900 --> 00:58:54,570
Soon, Blind Auction will begin.

1153
00:58:54,970 --> 00:58:57,130
There are 8 special cards among 30.

1154
00:58:57,270 --> 00:59:00,400
The possibility of getting
the three cards randomly...

1155
00:59:00,400 --> 00:59:01,510
is...

1156
00:59:01,510 --> 00:59:03,570
The possibility of finishing it
within 10 rounds is 40-something percent.

1157
00:59:03,570 --> 00:59:05,910
The possibility of finishing it
within 11 rounds is 50-something percent.

1158
00:59:05,910 --> 00:59:08,110
The possibility of finishing it
within 12 rounds is 60-something percent.

1159
00:59:08,110 --> 00:59:10,950
The possibility of finishing it
within 13 or 14 rounds is...

1160
00:59:10,950 --> 00:59:12,020
70 or 80-something percent.

1161
00:59:12,180 --> 00:59:15,920
Usually, it'd end within ten rounds.

1162
00:59:15,950 --> 00:59:18,820
What's important is how we use the cubes.

1163
00:59:19,020 --> 00:59:21,990
If we lack
cubes with smaller numbers later,

1164
00:59:21,990 --> 00:59:24,360
we will have to
raise our stakes significantly.

1165
00:59:24,500 --> 00:59:26,530
But the interesting part...

1166
00:59:26,730 --> 00:59:30,670
is that the listings are introduced
according to actual prices.

1167
00:59:30,670 --> 00:59:32,300
Those who only studied...

1168
00:59:33,240 --> 00:59:35,340
don't know how much watches are worth.

1169
00:59:35,940 --> 00:59:40,080
They don't know much
a recently released car is worth.

1170
00:59:40,080 --> 00:59:42,510
They don't know how much apartments
of a certain size are sold for...

1171
00:59:42,510 --> 00:59:43,880
in different neighborhoods.

1172
00:59:43,880 --> 00:59:46,380
Or how much a certain stock is.

1173
00:59:46,380 --> 00:59:48,590
There's a high possibility
that they're not interested in them.

1174
00:59:48,590 --> 00:59:50,220
This game could work to my advantage.

1175
00:59:51,090 --> 00:59:54,790
Before the game begins,
a representative from each team...

1176
00:59:54,790 --> 00:59:58,830
will enter the Voting Room
to draw the auction order.

1177
00:59:59,560 --> 01:00:00,830
I choose this.

1178
01:00:02,830 --> 01:00:04,640
Team P1 is going 1st.

1179
01:00:05,370 --> 01:00:06,900
I have terrible luck.

1180
01:00:07,470 --> 01:00:09,770
The order has been decided.

1181
01:00:10,610 --> 01:00:13,080
Team P1, Team P2,

1182
01:00:13,340 --> 01:00:15,880
Team P3, Team Rookie,

1183
01:00:16,080 --> 01:00:17,580
and Team Challenger.

1184
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:19,950
The first round of the auction
will go in this order.

1185
01:00:20,890 --> 01:00:24,820
The total price of the 22 item cards
will be revealed.

1186
01:00:25,290 --> 01:00:26,490
- Okay.
- How much?

1187
01:00:27,360 --> 01:00:30,560
(Total price of the items:
181.87 million dollars)

1188
01:00:30,930 --> 01:00:31,960
- Gosh, that's huge.
- Gosh, what?

1189
01:00:31,960 --> 01:00:36,400
Total price of the item cards
is 181.87 million dollars.

1190
01:00:37,070 --> 01:00:38,270
- What?
- That's too big.

1191
01:00:38,270 --> 01:00:39,300
- What?
- What are we supposed to do?

1192
01:00:39,540 --> 01:00:41,110
Is a building one of the items?

1193
01:00:41,940 --> 01:00:45,610
Gosh, there must be items
that are hard to predict.

1194
01:00:45,840 --> 01:00:48,750
The total price is 181.8 million dollars,

1195
01:00:48,750 --> 01:00:50,210
but there are only 22 items.

1196
01:00:50,210 --> 01:00:52,450
That means the average price...

1197
01:00:52,450 --> 01:00:53,880
is roughly nine million dollars.

1198
01:00:54,490 --> 01:00:57,390
And that means we don't need to buy
anything cheaper than that.

1199
01:00:57,390 --> 01:00:59,490
We need to buy items
that are more expensive than that.

1200
01:00:59,490 --> 01:01:01,930
In the end,

1201
01:01:01,930 --> 01:01:05,000
there could be really cheap items,

1202
01:01:05,000 --> 01:01:08,330
but the expensive items
could lead this game.

1203
01:01:09,000 --> 01:01:10,970
Before the game starts,

1204
01:01:10,970 --> 01:01:13,170
you may have 30 minutes
to plan your strategy.

1205
01:01:16,970 --> 01:01:17,980
Shall we go up?

1206
01:01:18,940 --> 01:01:20,710
- Where?
- We're all staying on the third floor.

1207
01:01:21,380 --> 01:01:22,580
You want to do this in the room?

1208
01:01:22,810 --> 01:01:24,980
- No, the strategy plan.
- Oh, the strategy plan?

1209
01:01:25,780 --> 01:01:27,690
Let's go up. We can smoke too.

1210
01:01:28,850 --> 01:01:31,260
YunB, we'll follow you.

1211
01:01:31,260 --> 01:01:32,390
- With her too?
- Yes.

1212
01:01:32,390 --> 01:01:33,890
I have to wait for Beom.

1213
01:01:33,890 --> 01:01:35,290
- What?
- I have to wait for Beom.

1214
01:01:35,830 --> 01:01:37,290
- I have to wait for Beom.
- Is that so?

1215
01:01:37,460 --> 01:01:38,530
Hey.

1216
01:01:38,630 --> 01:01:41,500
Even if Sung Joo joins another team,

1217
01:01:42,430 --> 01:01:44,870
even if he gets absorbed into Team Rookie,

1218
01:01:45,000 --> 01:01:48,270
I expected we could stay like family,

1219
01:01:48,310 --> 01:01:50,410
like a member of Team P2.

1220
01:01:51,910 --> 01:01:57,450
(YunB and Seung Jin head to
Team Rookie's room.)

1221
01:01:58,880 --> 01:01:59,950
Can I go in for a second?

1222
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:01,590
We don't have much time.

1223
01:02:01,590 --> 01:02:03,850
Can we tell you
after we talk for five more minutes?

1224
01:02:03,850 --> 01:02:04,860
Okay.

1225
01:02:13,400 --> 01:02:15,170
Since we have Sung Joo...

1226
01:02:21,240 --> 01:02:22,270
Where is Jin Hyeong?

1227
01:02:22,510 --> 01:02:25,640
Jin Hyeong is talking with Tae Gyun.

1228
01:02:27,880 --> 01:02:29,250
- With Team P1.
- Nice.

1229
01:02:29,350 --> 01:02:31,180
We can just be in charge of this team.

1230
01:02:32,080 --> 01:02:33,320
Wouldn't it be enough to just share...

1231
01:02:33,320 --> 01:02:34,550
- the cubes we have?
- The cubes?

1232
01:02:34,790 --> 01:02:36,320
Wouldn't that be sharing a lot?

1233
01:02:36,320 --> 01:02:37,620
But the cubes can be shared with everyone.

1234
01:02:38,720 --> 01:02:41,430
- When they're not revealed.
- That much would be okay.

1235
01:02:41,430 --> 01:02:44,060
What else shall we do
to form an alliance on top of that?

1236
01:02:44,060 --> 01:02:46,060
In any case,

1237
01:02:46,060 --> 01:02:49,570
let's promise to keep Team P3 in check.

1238
01:02:49,670 --> 01:02:51,040
- Okay.
- Tae Gyun wants to...

1239
01:02:51,040 --> 01:02:52,170
keep joining forces with me.

1240
01:02:52,470 --> 01:02:55,570
Let's take down Team P3 at least once.

1241
01:02:55,640 --> 01:02:58,040
I want to know what you guys talked about.

1242
01:02:58,040 --> 01:02:59,540
- To Ji Min,
- Yes.

1243
01:02:59,540 --> 01:03:02,410
I said the best scenario
for both of our teams would be...

1244
01:03:03,250 --> 01:03:05,350
(YunB talked with Ji Min first.)

1245
01:03:05,350 --> 01:03:06,720
The Pandora's Safe is open,

1246
01:03:07,490 --> 01:03:09,590
and we know how much everyone has.

1247
01:03:09,920 --> 01:03:13,760
- Oh, how much each team has?
- Yes, the team's fund.

1248
01:03:14,190 --> 01:03:16,330
I'll tell you straightforwardly
since we don't have much time.

1249
01:03:16,690 --> 01:03:19,900
I want Team P3 and Team Challenger
to be at the bottom.

1250
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:21,570
Why Team Challenger?

1251
01:03:21,570 --> 01:03:22,570
Sung Joo...

1252
01:03:23,030 --> 01:03:24,900
- Oh, because he's in Team Rookie?
- Yes.

1253
01:03:25,100 --> 01:03:26,470
That'd be the best scenario.

1254
01:03:26,640 --> 01:03:28,440
Okay. I'll talk with them.

1255
01:03:33,080 --> 01:03:36,350
Before Blind Auction started,

1256
01:03:36,350 --> 01:03:39,450
I brought something
to the negotiating table.

1257
01:03:42,290 --> 01:03:43,290
Let's see.

1258
01:03:43,290 --> 01:03:45,060
(The Pandora's Safe was opened
on the outdoor survival grounds.)

1259
01:03:46,090 --> 01:03:47,260
What is it?

1260
01:03:50,560 --> 01:03:52,560
Revealing every team's fund.

1261
01:03:53,030 --> 01:03:54,270
Bad.

1262
01:03:54,270 --> 01:03:56,170
Doubling every item's price.

1263
01:03:56,970 --> 01:03:58,100
Revealing every team's?

1264
01:03:58,240 --> 01:04:01,370
Team P3 is on another level
with this much fund.

1265
01:04:01,370 --> 01:04:02,440
They have 340,000 dollars?

1266
01:04:02,440 --> 01:04:03,670
(P1: 190,000, P2: 170,000, P3: 340,000,
Team C: 20,000, Team R: 80,000)

1267
01:04:03,670 --> 01:04:05,010
I should use this fact...

1268
01:04:05,210 --> 01:04:08,510
as means of politics and negotiations.

1269
01:04:08,850 --> 01:04:11,450
I thought Team P3 would become
the public enemy.

1270
01:04:11,680 --> 01:04:13,250
Hey, we can't miss the chance...

1271
01:04:13,250 --> 01:04:16,090
to talk with Team Rookie
while staying in here.

1272
01:04:17,090 --> 01:04:23,930
(Team P2 heads
to Team Rookie's room again.)

1273
01:04:35,670 --> 01:04:37,040
Anybody here?

1274
01:04:37,040 --> 01:04:38,240
No one's here?

1275
01:04:38,340 --> 01:04:41,480
- What?
- They must be in the main hall.

1276
01:04:41,850 --> 01:04:43,110
Beom hasn't come out yet.

1277
01:04:45,580 --> 01:04:51,690
(Team P2 heads to the main hall.)

1278
01:04:57,490 --> 01:04:58,730
- They're not there, right?
- They're not.

1279
01:04:58,930 --> 01:05:01,470
- This is driving me crazy.
- They must be with Team P1.

1280
01:05:11,340 --> 01:05:12,780
I'll take a look first.

1281
01:05:20,480 --> 01:05:21,720
Is this a residents' meeting or what?

1282
01:05:21,890 --> 01:05:23,490
Is it okay if we come in?

1283
01:05:23,750 --> 01:05:25,260
- Give us a second.
- Okay.

1284
01:05:25,390 --> 01:05:26,860
We'll talk among ourselves first.

1285
01:05:26,860 --> 01:05:30,960
(Team P1, Team Rookie, and Team Challenger
are all gathered.)

1286
01:05:41,410 --> 01:05:42,540
This isn't going smoothly.

1287
01:05:43,270 --> 01:05:45,140
Team C, Team R, and Team P1...

1288
01:05:45,880 --> 01:05:47,710
sat closely together...

1289
01:05:48,180 --> 01:05:50,780
and were planning a strategy...

1290
01:05:51,220 --> 01:05:52,720
as though they were in the Pentagon.

1291
01:05:52,950 --> 01:05:56,150
I felt something was off then.

1292
01:05:56,320 --> 01:05:58,460
That's when I thought, "No way."

1293
01:05:59,220 --> 01:06:03,190
(Team P2 is waiting outside.)

1294
01:06:04,230 --> 01:06:05,300
What's taking them so long?

1295
01:06:05,960 --> 01:06:07,360
With 22 items...

1296
01:06:07,360 --> 01:06:08,370
They were all in there?

1297
01:06:08,370 --> 01:06:10,330
Yes, everyone except Team P3 was in there.

1298
01:06:12,170 --> 01:06:13,870
Are they trying to isolate us and Team P3?

1299
01:06:13,870 --> 01:06:16,470
They could be trying to make us...

1300
01:06:16,470 --> 01:06:18,240
end up in 4th or 5th place.

1301
01:06:18,940 --> 01:06:20,710
In any case,

1302
01:06:20,710 --> 01:06:23,810
since Sung Joo is one of us,
I'll put my trust in him.

1303
01:06:24,780 --> 01:06:26,750
Even if he's with them...

1304
01:06:36,730 --> 01:06:37,930
This round won't be easy.

1305
01:06:38,660 --> 01:06:40,400
Sang Min suddenly opened the door...

1306
01:06:40,730 --> 01:06:42,670
and came out.

1307
01:06:42,800 --> 01:06:44,770
Our eyes met then.

1308
01:06:45,240 --> 01:06:46,570
But he went back inside
and closed the door.

1309
01:06:46,570 --> 01:06:47,710
That's when I thought,

1310
01:06:48,210 --> 01:06:51,110
"At this rate,"

1311
01:06:51,110 --> 01:06:54,650
"they're not even thinking
of talking to us."

1312
01:06:55,050 --> 01:06:56,350
That occurred to me suddenly.

1313
01:06:57,650 --> 01:06:59,250
Even so, I had to talk to them.

1314
01:06:59,350 --> 01:07:02,720
What's up with them closing the door
right in front of us?

1315
01:07:10,530 --> 01:07:12,700
The game is about to start.

1316
01:07:12,700 --> 01:07:14,830
- Everyone is here.
- What...

1317
01:07:15,270 --> 01:07:16,930
- Talk.
- Okay.

1318
01:07:17,030 --> 01:07:19,700
- Are you three teaming up?
- Yes.

1319
01:07:20,100 --> 01:07:21,240
That's how it turned out.

1320
01:07:23,040 --> 01:07:24,070
I see.

1321
01:07:24,510 --> 01:07:25,780
I'll tell you this.

1322
01:07:26,640 --> 01:07:28,880
You're not our target.

1323
01:07:29,950 --> 01:07:32,550
- We don't have...
- You three teaming up means...

1324
01:07:32,550 --> 01:07:34,820
you'll make us and Team P3...

1325
01:07:35,550 --> 01:07:37,590
come in 4th and 5th place.

1326
01:07:37,590 --> 01:07:39,260
- Yes. Here's the thing.
- Okay.

1327
01:07:39,660 --> 01:07:41,560
You could team up with Team P3.

1328
01:07:43,030 --> 01:07:47,200
But if you play solo without teaming up...

1329
01:07:47,800 --> 01:07:49,770
with Team P3,

1330
01:07:50,330 --> 01:07:52,000
we will support you...

1331
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:55,040
as much as we can in the Deathmatch.

1332
01:07:57,110 --> 01:07:59,980
- What kind of support is there?
- The...

1333
01:08:00,080 --> 01:08:04,580
For example, You Hyun choosing Gwan Hee.
Either way...

1334
01:08:05,080 --> 01:08:08,590
- Let's talk about that in private.
- Okay.

1335
01:08:08,720 --> 01:08:09,950
- Fine.
- I'll explain.

1336
01:08:11,020 --> 01:08:12,860
Ji Min, earlier...

1337
01:08:13,090 --> 01:08:15,360
Yes, I brought it up but got turned down.

1338
01:08:17,660 --> 01:08:20,560
May I ask how all of this happened?

1339
01:08:20,700 --> 01:08:23,900
Our target is Team P3.

1340
01:08:24,000 --> 01:08:25,470
From our stance...

1341
01:08:25,670 --> 01:08:27,710
- I like you.
- Right.

1342
01:08:27,870 --> 01:08:30,670
I like you,
but it's your team that's the problem.

1343
01:08:33,580 --> 01:08:34,610
Your team is the problem.

1344
01:08:35,710 --> 01:08:39,120
What's more... Who was it again?
The one who played in the Deathmatch.

1345
01:08:39,450 --> 01:08:41,350
- Jin Hyeong?
- The thing is,

1346
01:08:41,350 --> 01:08:44,220
- today's game...
- Seriously.

1347
01:08:49,560 --> 01:08:51,500
This is so frustrating.

1348
01:08:52,660 --> 01:08:54,400
What are these guys doing?

1349
01:08:55,370 --> 01:08:56,370
What...

1350
01:08:58,500 --> 01:08:59,670
What are they trying to do?

1351
01:09:00,100 --> 01:09:01,240
Ji Min.

1352
01:09:02,710 --> 01:09:03,740
Sung Joo.

1353
01:09:04,940 --> 01:09:06,210
They agreed to talk about it.

1354
01:09:07,310 --> 01:09:08,350
You Hyun.

1355
01:09:09,350 --> 01:09:10,750
He promised to help.

1356
01:09:11,150 --> 01:09:14,820
We dropped by
after being offered some help.

1357
01:09:14,950 --> 01:09:17,590
But they were already in Team P1's room.

1358
01:09:17,920 --> 01:09:18,990
Team Rookie.

1359
01:09:20,020 --> 01:09:21,560
We promised to talk in five minutes,

1360
01:09:21,760 --> 01:09:23,360
but they were in Team P1's room.

1361
01:09:23,890 --> 01:09:26,730
Right. So they already formed a union.

1362
01:09:27,430 --> 01:09:30,330
We were excluded from this round
from the start.

1363
01:09:30,570 --> 01:09:31,700
That was what I thought.

1364
01:09:31,900 --> 01:09:32,900
I...

1365
01:09:34,270 --> 01:09:38,110
was most disappointed...

1366
01:09:39,410 --> 01:09:42,110
in Teams C and Rookie.

1367
01:09:43,480 --> 01:09:44,680
What's going on?

1368
01:09:44,680 --> 01:09:48,590
I believed we were a family.

1369
01:09:48,690 --> 01:09:51,290
I'm in no place to choose.
You get the situation, right?

1370
01:09:51,460 --> 01:09:53,660
I can't betray my team
or drag my team out,

1371
01:09:53,660 --> 01:09:56,160
- asking them to team up with Team P2.
- Here's my logic.

1372
01:09:56,160 --> 01:09:59,100
The best decision you two can make...

1373
01:09:59,330 --> 01:10:00,700
- It's true that we owe you one.
- Right?

1374
01:10:00,700 --> 01:10:02,400
So why team up with them?

1375
01:10:02,830 --> 01:10:05,300
Isn't it better to team up with us?

1376
01:10:06,840 --> 01:10:09,440
Honestly, Team P2 makes me uncomfortable.

1377
01:10:09,510 --> 01:10:11,580
I'm new to Team R.

1378
01:10:11,910 --> 01:10:13,680
There's not even enough time...

1379
01:10:14,040 --> 01:10:17,450
for me to become one with this team.

1380
01:10:17,680 --> 01:10:19,520
But to tell my team, "I was in Team P2."

1381
01:10:19,520 --> 01:10:20,780
"Screw everything.
Let's team up with them."

1382
01:10:21,620 --> 01:10:23,850
I have no good reason to do that.

1383
01:10:24,760 --> 01:10:27,290
What's more,
I don't want to follow Team P2.

1384
01:10:27,360 --> 01:10:28,830
Honestly, I had no hard feelings.

1385
01:10:28,830 --> 01:10:32,930
Team P2 chose Gwan Hee, not me,

1386
01:10:33,330 --> 01:10:35,270
because it wasn't to save me.

1387
01:10:35,270 --> 01:10:38,500
I simply ended up getting the benefit.

1388
01:10:39,170 --> 01:10:41,440
It wasn't a decision made for me.

1389
01:10:41,570 --> 01:10:44,540
I don't really owe anything to them.

1390
01:10:45,110 --> 01:10:46,280
What's the use...

1391
01:10:47,810 --> 01:10:50,050
of getting upset
and regretting things here?

1392
01:10:50,510 --> 01:10:54,790
To be frank, there's definitely merit
in allying.

1393
01:10:54,990 --> 01:10:56,690
But I think...

1394
01:10:57,050 --> 01:11:00,460
if we do it at our discretion
as opportunity allows,

1395
01:11:00,620 --> 01:11:02,730
we could achieve decent results.

1396
01:11:03,990 --> 01:11:05,100
It's inevitable.

1397
01:11:05,560 --> 01:11:06,660
- He can get mad,
- Of course.

1398
01:11:06,660 --> 01:11:07,760
- but it's inevitable.
- Exactly.

1399
01:11:07,930 --> 01:11:10,970
Teams P2 and P3 looked too solid.

1400
01:11:11,170 --> 01:11:13,500
The members have great teamwork.

1401
01:11:14,340 --> 01:11:16,340
To bring about an elimination candidate,

1402
01:11:16,340 --> 01:11:20,080
we had to break the alliance
between Teams P2 and P3.

1403
01:11:20,210 --> 01:11:24,620
With that, an alliance
with many teams was needed.

1404
01:11:25,080 --> 01:11:27,550
Can't we make a team come in last?

1405
01:11:28,250 --> 01:11:29,320
Of course.

1406
01:11:29,320 --> 01:11:30,850
If possible,
which team are you thinking of?

1407
01:11:30,850 --> 01:11:31,860
Team P3 or Team P2?

1408
01:11:32,490 --> 01:11:34,760
We have to make two teams come in last.

1409
01:11:34,760 --> 01:11:36,290
In short, keep both in check?

1410
01:11:37,530 --> 01:11:38,560
Yes.

1411
01:11:38,760 --> 01:11:40,900
If three teams work together,
the other two will be in a pinch.

1412
01:11:41,900 --> 01:11:42,930
Let's do it.

1413
01:11:43,470 --> 01:11:44,770
Beom.

1414
01:11:45,370 --> 01:11:49,770
(Approaching Team R
after teaming up with Team C)

1415
01:11:50,210 --> 01:11:51,540
I'll be honest with you.

1416
01:11:51,740 --> 01:11:53,640
This game will practically kill
the 4th-place and 5th-place teams.

1417
01:11:53,980 --> 01:11:56,550
If four teams work together,
it'd be amazing.

1418
01:11:57,080 --> 01:11:58,450
But three teams are more than enough...

1419
01:11:58,450 --> 01:11:59,480
because if you come in 3rd,

1420
01:11:59,480 --> 01:12:00,720
the 4th-place and 5th-place teams
would play in the Deathmatch.

1421
01:12:01,350 --> 01:12:03,890
As I kept saying,
Teams P2 and P3 have great teamwork.

1422
01:12:04,090 --> 01:12:05,120
That's why I want to work with...

1423
01:12:06,090 --> 01:12:07,390
Teams C and R today.

1424
01:12:07,520 --> 01:12:10,760
We were supposed to work with Team P2.

1425
01:12:10,760 --> 01:12:13,100
But after seeing the voting result,

1426
01:12:13,100 --> 01:12:14,700
I was disappointed in them.

1427
01:12:14,970 --> 01:12:17,300
But for 3 out of 5 teams to unite?

1428
01:12:18,070 --> 01:12:20,900
Why choose to work with 1 team
when you can choose 2 teams?

1429
01:12:21,040 --> 01:12:24,680
The 3-team alliance was formed about
30 seconds after the game was revealed.

1430
01:12:25,640 --> 01:12:30,980
(The alliance team has gathered
in Team P1's room.)

1431
01:12:31,980 --> 01:12:34,050
- Hey.
- Hi.

1432
01:12:34,050 --> 01:12:35,850
- Can you shut the door completely?
- Sure.

1433
01:12:36,120 --> 01:12:39,790
As the whole team
will get eliminated today,

1434
01:12:39,990 --> 01:12:42,130
we're forming a multiple-team alliance.

1435
01:12:42,390 --> 01:12:44,830
Three teams will work together today.

1436
01:12:45,160 --> 01:12:46,760
- May I say a word?
- Go ahead.

1437
01:12:46,760 --> 01:12:49,830
I did a bit of thinking,

1438
01:12:50,730 --> 01:12:53,570
and the game will most likely end
in Round 10 or 11.

1439
01:12:53,800 --> 01:12:56,240
I bet it'll end before Round 13 or 14.

1440
01:12:56,510 --> 01:13:00,540
Not letting the other teams win
even one round is what we should aim for.

1441
01:13:01,750 --> 01:13:03,380
That's impossible.

1442
01:13:03,750 --> 01:13:05,620
- But...
- It's possible.

1443
01:13:05,620 --> 01:13:07,850
- Yes, it is.
- Yes, only if we share the wins.

1444
01:13:07,850 --> 01:13:11,390
- If we continue to split wins.
- There are 36 cubes, correct?

1445
01:13:11,390 --> 01:13:13,860
We need to win 10 to 11.

1446
01:13:13,860 --> 01:13:16,130
Each team...

1447
01:13:16,760 --> 01:13:18,530
has 12 cubes, so the total would be 36.

1448
01:13:18,700 --> 01:13:22,800
The game will end with us all surviving
with those 36.

1449
01:13:23,000 --> 01:13:25,200
The probability is 80 to 90 percent,

1450
01:13:25,300 --> 01:13:26,500
so it's possible for us all to survive.

1451
01:13:26,500 --> 01:13:27,740
That is our winning strategy.

1452
01:13:27,840 --> 01:13:30,510
Just as Ji Hoo mentioned,

1453
01:13:30,710 --> 01:13:33,310
- I think we should win...
- Yes.

1454
01:13:33,310 --> 01:13:35,080
- as many rounds as possible.
- Right.

1455
01:13:35,080 --> 01:13:38,120
In Round One, start with something...

1456
01:13:38,220 --> 01:13:40,220
that would get us a low number,
like eight.

1457
01:13:40,420 --> 01:13:42,890
After seeing the move
Teams P2 and P3 will make,

1458
01:13:42,950 --> 01:13:46,290
- I'll decide whether to join or not.
- Okay.

1459
01:13:46,290 --> 01:13:48,990
After that, Team C should win
by raising the number.

1460
01:13:48,990 --> 01:13:50,830
I'll start with either 6 or 8,

1461
01:13:50,830 --> 01:13:52,660
so that Team C can...

1462
01:13:52,660 --> 01:13:54,030
- win.
- Got it.

1463
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:55,770
Could this happen?

1464
01:13:55,770 --> 01:13:57,000
Could the other teams be like,
for example,

1465
01:13:57,000 --> 01:13:59,300
"I don't care about the cubes."

1466
01:13:59,440 --> 01:14:01,710
"Just tell me the price you just won."

1467
01:14:02,040 --> 01:14:03,670
Is there a possibility
they'd make such a deal?

1468
01:14:04,540 --> 01:14:06,040
Yes, there is.

1469
01:14:06,640 --> 01:14:09,550
Or something like,
"Let's not attack each other."

1470
01:14:09,880 --> 01:14:13,380
"Let's share..."

1471
01:14:13,380 --> 01:14:16,320
"what we just won."
Those could be possible.

1472
01:14:16,620 --> 01:14:18,020
I'm going to drop by Team C.

1473
01:14:21,290 --> 01:14:26,260
(Seong Beom heads over to Team C's room.)

1474
01:14:26,560 --> 01:14:29,070
I opened Team C's room
before the game to check out...

1475
01:14:29,070 --> 01:14:30,570
who was working with whom.

1476
01:14:35,840 --> 01:14:36,870
For real?

1477
01:14:37,170 --> 01:14:39,310
Nobody was there.

1478
01:14:39,780 --> 01:14:42,050
I had my doubts,

1479
01:14:42,050 --> 01:14:45,180
but I knocked on the door
of Team P1's noisy room...

1480
01:14:45,280 --> 01:14:47,280
and asked if Jin Ho was in there.

1481
01:14:49,220 --> 01:14:50,690
Is Jin Ho in here?

1482
01:14:51,120 --> 01:14:52,120
(Everyone is in Team P1's room.)

1483
01:14:52,120 --> 01:14:54,120
- No, he's not. Sorry.
- He's not here.

1484
01:14:55,090 --> 01:14:57,360
Teams P1, R, and C...

1485
01:14:57,360 --> 01:14:59,330
were all in there.

1486
01:15:01,670 --> 01:15:03,100
- This is crazy.
- What is it?

1487
01:15:03,100 --> 01:15:05,000
Everyone is in Team P1's room.

1488
01:15:05,570 --> 01:15:07,500
- What?
- We're going to get beaten up.

1489
01:15:08,470 --> 01:15:10,810
But can we even get beaten up
in this game?

1490
01:15:13,110 --> 01:15:15,850
I doubt that alliance will be easy.

1491
01:15:16,080 --> 01:15:17,480
The moment you go downstairs,

1492
01:15:17,650 --> 01:15:19,520
the player has to guess
the value of the item...

1493
01:15:19,520 --> 01:15:21,080
- and play a mind game.
- Right.

1494
01:15:21,080 --> 01:15:22,590
Looks like the alliance is already over.

1495
01:15:22,990 --> 01:15:24,490
YunB was furious.

1496
01:15:24,490 --> 01:15:25,820
- What?
- YunB was enraged.

1497
01:15:25,820 --> 01:15:27,460
- Did you not hear him throw things?
- No.

1498
01:15:27,460 --> 01:15:28,930
YunB just threw something.

1499
01:15:29,260 --> 01:15:31,360
- How funny.
- Jin Hyeong was...

1500
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:33,130
Jin Hyeong was...

1501
01:15:33,300 --> 01:15:35,230
- In the hallway?
- Yes, just out front.

1502
01:15:35,530 --> 01:15:37,570
For an alliance to work out,

1503
01:15:37,570 --> 01:15:40,700
- someone has to suffer a serious loss.
- Make a sacrifice.

1504
01:15:41,140 --> 01:15:43,040
- But that's hard to accept.
- Totally.

1505
01:15:43,210 --> 01:15:44,940
We might end up benefiting from them,

1506
01:15:44,940 --> 01:15:46,580
so let's not let the pressure get to us.

1507
01:15:46,580 --> 01:15:49,110
Let's say they use special cards,

1508
01:15:49,110 --> 01:15:50,850
so we couldn't win any items and lost.

1509
01:15:50,850 --> 01:15:53,020
Then it was meant to be.
We were meant to lose.

1510
01:15:53,120 --> 01:15:56,950
The more pressure you feel,
the less likely you'll win in this game.

1511
01:15:56,950 --> 01:16:00,090
Xitsuh's amazing hair today
suggests he'll be on a roll.

1512
01:16:00,320 --> 01:16:02,360
His hair got electrocuted...

1513
01:16:02,360 --> 01:16:03,960
- from using his brain too much.
- Exactly.

1514
01:16:04,160 --> 01:16:05,730
- He's receiving the universe's power...
- His hair looks like antennas.

1515
01:16:05,730 --> 01:16:07,160
through signals from outer space.

1516
01:16:07,160 --> 01:16:10,030
Xitsuh is becoming a crazy scientist.
He's becoming Orbit.

1517
01:16:10,900 --> 01:16:12,340
When you go downstairs to play the game,

1518
01:16:12,970 --> 01:16:15,840
don't waver because of the opponent.

1519
01:16:16,170 --> 01:16:17,740
As I also felt like...

1520
01:16:18,110 --> 01:16:20,310
this game was better played solo...

1521
01:16:20,310 --> 01:16:21,810
than as an alliance,

1522
01:16:21,910 --> 01:16:23,580
I was confident we'd do well.

1523
01:16:23,680 --> 01:16:25,020
The total is 180 million dollars.

1524
01:16:25,020 --> 01:16:27,020
From what I see,
its value is ten million dollars.

1525
01:16:27,320 --> 01:16:28,890
No, let's say the value
is 20 million dollars.

1526
01:16:28,950 --> 01:16:31,190
If it's 20 million dollars,
it'll be in the top 5.

1527
01:16:31,290 --> 01:16:32,290
- Twenty billion dollars?
- Yes.

1528
01:16:32,290 --> 01:16:33,560
What's the most ideal price?

1529
01:16:34,020 --> 01:16:36,290
So that it's easy for Xitsuh to calculate,

1530
01:16:36,490 --> 01:16:39,800
what should the number be...

1531
01:16:39,800 --> 01:16:42,670
for every ten million dollars of value?

1532
01:16:42,670 --> 01:16:44,130
- Four.
- Four cubes.

1533
01:16:44,130 --> 01:16:46,270
- Four cubes? Four for ten million?
- Why?

1534
01:16:46,370 --> 01:16:47,670
I simply divided 180 million.

1535
01:16:47,670 --> 01:16:50,310
I got the number,
thinking we could use 71 cubes.

1536
01:16:50,310 --> 01:16:52,080
I left out about 40 cubes...

1537
01:16:52,080 --> 01:16:54,340
and the special cards.

1538
01:16:54,480 --> 01:16:57,050
If we were to use 71 cubes
to make the bid,

1539
01:16:57,050 --> 01:17:00,120
it'd get us 2.5 million per cube.

1540
01:17:00,380 --> 01:17:02,450
But objectively speaking,

1541
01:17:02,690 --> 01:17:05,460
this is only if we can see all the items.

1542
01:17:05,760 --> 01:17:08,160
I personally think
we should triple this...

1543
01:17:08,160 --> 01:17:09,790
if we also consider the competitiveness.

1544
01:17:09,790 --> 01:17:12,960
That's why I think it's necessary...

1545
01:17:13,360 --> 01:17:15,430
to use 12 cubes per 10 million dollars.

1546
01:17:15,430 --> 01:17:17,770
So 12 cubes
per 10 million dollars of value.

1547
01:17:18,130 --> 01:17:20,140
It's not as if we could win every item,

1548
01:17:20,140 --> 01:17:22,370
and who knows how many rounds we'll play.

1549
01:17:22,810 --> 01:17:26,040
There's no need to go hard from the start.
Let's go with optimization mode.

1550
01:17:26,980 --> 01:17:29,310
The preparatory meeting session is over.

1551
01:17:30,380 --> 01:17:32,980
Please submit your lineup
in the order of participation.

1552
01:17:33,720 --> 01:17:34,780
(Blind Auction Lineup)

1553
01:17:34,780 --> 01:17:35,790
(Team P1: Lee Tae Gyun, Park Ji Min,
Jeong Keun Woo, Lee Sang Min)

1554
01:17:35,790 --> 01:17:36,890
(Team P2:
Lee Jin Hyeong, YunB, Ha Seung Jin)

1555
01:17:36,890 --> 01:17:37,920
(Team P3: Heo Seong Beom,
Hong Jin Ho, Xitsuh, Choi Hye Seon)

1556
01:17:37,920 --> 01:17:38,890
(Team R: Shin Seung Yong,
Hyun Sung Joo, Kwak Beom)

1557
01:17:38,890 --> 01:17:39,990
(Team C: Kim Nam Hee, Kim Kyoung Hoon,
Kim You Hyun, Kang Ji Hoo)

1558
01:17:40,560 --> 01:17:43,090
The auction for Round One will now begin.

1559
01:17:43,090 --> 01:17:45,060
(Blind Auction Round 1)

1560
01:17:45,400 --> 01:17:47,700
Team P1, select the item.

1561
01:17:48,930 --> 01:17:50,000
Number one, please.

1562
01:17:50,730 --> 01:17:52,770
Item number one has been selected.

1563
01:17:56,940 --> 01:18:01,240
(The jacket Michael Jackson wore)

1564
01:18:02,910 --> 01:18:04,010
Michael Jackson?

1565
01:18:04,710 --> 01:18:08,220
An item card.
It's a jacket Michael Jackson wore.

1566
01:18:08,520 --> 01:18:10,250
It was won at an auction...

1567
01:18:10,250 --> 01:18:13,190
held by Propstore in London, UK,
in November 2023.

1568
01:18:13,720 --> 01:18:16,160
Michael Jackson wore the jacket...

1569
01:18:16,160 --> 01:18:19,330
for a Pepsi commercial in 1984.

1570
01:18:22,530 --> 01:18:26,300
Even if you're interested
in current events and the economy,

1571
01:18:26,840 --> 01:18:29,170
the topic was very random,

1572
01:18:29,170 --> 01:18:34,140
covering areas
you might have zero knowledge of.

1573
01:18:34,580 --> 01:18:36,110
I was quite taken aback.

1574
01:18:36,210 --> 01:18:39,080
It's a very famous commercial
with a very famous person in it.

1575
01:18:39,380 --> 01:18:42,650
But the problem is that
I'm not into collectibles and such.

1576
01:18:42,890 --> 01:18:46,290
I couldn't even guess
how much it would be.

1577
01:18:46,690 --> 01:18:47,820
How about we go outside...

1578
01:18:47,820 --> 01:18:50,560
and check if the other teams
are still discussing it?

1579
01:18:51,060 --> 01:18:53,330
- Shall we?
- Are they still talking?

1580
01:18:53,330 --> 01:18:57,830
(Jin Ho and Xitsuh
head to Team P1's room.)

1581
01:19:00,500 --> 01:19:01,810
- Can we go in?
- Yes.

1582
01:19:02,140 --> 01:19:04,040
- Everyone's here.
- Team P3...

1583
01:19:04,240 --> 01:19:07,180
has visited our room for the first time.

1584
01:19:09,380 --> 01:19:10,880
It's not our first time. I came by once.

1585
01:19:11,010 --> 01:19:12,220
- Welcome.
- You rarely came over.

1586
01:19:12,220 --> 01:19:13,750
Jin Ho, sit in the front.

1587
01:19:13,750 --> 01:19:14,920
Little did I imagine...

1588
01:19:15,120 --> 01:19:17,850
Team P3 would come to our room.

1589
01:19:18,390 --> 01:19:19,420
Just sit there, Ji Min.

1590
01:19:19,420 --> 01:19:20,960
- No, come here.
- We came by on the first day.

1591
01:19:21,320 --> 01:19:22,530
- Seriously.
- What's this?

1592
01:19:22,530 --> 01:19:25,400
- We stopped by on the first day.
- What... Take a seat.

1593
01:19:26,160 --> 01:19:27,930
- Is Team P2 somewhere else?
- Yes.

1594
01:19:28,030 --> 01:19:29,170
Is that so?

1595
01:19:29,730 --> 01:19:32,440
The item of this round is an item card.

1596
01:19:32,900 --> 01:19:35,210
It's the jacket Michael Jackson wore.

1597
01:19:35,340 --> 01:19:37,070
- How would you know that?
- It was won at an auction...

1598
01:19:37,240 --> 01:19:40,410
held by Propstore in London, UK,
in November 2023.

1599
01:19:41,950 --> 01:19:44,210
- Michael Jackson wore the jacket...
- A jacket?

1600
01:19:44,210 --> 01:19:47,380
for a Pepsi commercial in 1984.

1601
01:19:48,220 --> 01:19:50,020
This one's hard. How would you know it?

1602
01:19:50,750 --> 01:19:52,790
- Gosh.
- There are many Michael Jackson fans.

1603
01:19:52,790 --> 01:19:55,560
- How much could it be?
- I know the answer.

1604
01:19:55,560 --> 01:19:56,690
Sang Min must know how much it cost.

1605
01:19:56,690 --> 01:19:58,560
- I do, and it's worth buying.
- How much is it?

1606
01:19:58,560 --> 01:20:00,800
The one who won it was Lady Gaga.

1607
01:20:01,060 --> 01:20:03,230
Really? He knows for sure.

1608
01:20:03,800 --> 01:20:06,200
From what I know,
it was worth two million dollars.

1609
01:20:06,700 --> 01:20:08,840
- Two million?
- It wasn't ten million.

1610
01:20:09,010 --> 01:20:10,970
If it's two million dollars,
it's below average.

1611
01:20:10,970 --> 01:20:12,210
That's cheap, right?

1612
01:20:12,210 --> 01:20:14,580
I don't remember it clearly,

1613
01:20:14,940 --> 01:20:16,950
but what I do know is that
Lady Gaga won the auction.

1614
01:20:17,280 --> 01:20:19,320
Either way,
it's less than five million dollars.

1615
01:20:19,580 --> 01:20:21,250
- It's not ten million dollars.
- Is that so?

1616
01:20:21,920 --> 01:20:25,120
Michael Jackson is a big name.

1617
01:20:25,760 --> 01:20:27,020
He's the King of Pop.

1618
01:20:27,390 --> 01:20:28,990
Real estate is easy to guess,

1619
01:20:28,990 --> 01:20:29,990
- Right?
- but not this one.

1620
01:20:30,690 --> 01:20:33,730
I just know that it's really expensive.

1621
01:20:33,730 --> 01:20:37,030
It's over ten million dollars.
Michael Jackson's Pepsi jacket.

1622
01:20:37,430 --> 01:20:39,270
Even his gloves
were worth over ten million dollars.

1623
01:20:39,570 --> 01:20:43,370
Michael Jackson's diamond gloves
from his concert.

1624
01:20:43,940 --> 01:20:45,010
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1625
01:20:45,010 --> 01:20:47,480
You know those iconic gloves?
They were worth over ten million dollars.

1626
01:20:48,010 --> 01:20:49,550
That's why this jacket...

1627
01:20:50,580 --> 01:20:51,880
must be over nine million dollars.

1628
01:20:53,180 --> 01:20:55,950
How much do you think that jacket is?

1629
01:20:56,450 --> 01:20:57,450
Around 30 million dollars.

1630
01:20:57,450 --> 01:20:58,590
- Thirty million dollars?
- Yes.

1631
01:20:58,590 --> 01:20:59,860
- That much?
- Thirty million dollars?

1632
01:20:59,990 --> 01:21:01,360
- He's bluffing too much.
- The total...

1633
01:21:01,360 --> 01:21:02,660
is 181.8 million dollars,

1634
01:21:02,660 --> 01:21:03,960
so how can that be worth
30 million dollars?

1635
01:21:03,960 --> 01:21:05,960
No way. Don't you know Michael Jackson?

1636
01:21:06,660 --> 01:21:08,870
The bidding will now begin.

1637
01:21:09,400 --> 01:21:12,840
Team P1, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

1638
01:21:13,570 --> 01:21:15,340
You have three minutes to decide.

1639
01:21:18,540 --> 01:21:22,310
Honestly, I'm not all that interested...

1640
01:21:22,310 --> 01:21:24,480
in Michael Jackson.

1641
01:21:24,850 --> 01:21:26,550
That's why
I couldn't accurately assess its value.

1642
01:21:26,550 --> 01:21:29,220
Even so, I had to win it no matter what.

1643
01:21:29,550 --> 01:21:34,060
How many do you wish I'd submit?

1644
01:21:34,690 --> 01:21:35,690
One.

1645
01:21:36,030 --> 01:21:37,030
- One?
- One?

1646
01:21:38,060 --> 01:21:40,130
You're trying to win it for nothing.

1647
01:21:40,530 --> 01:21:43,500
I think Team P1
could go all in on this one.

1648
01:21:46,740 --> 01:21:47,770
Here's my bet.

1649
01:21:50,240 --> 01:21:52,510
Team P1 has submitted cube number 8.

1650
01:21:52,740 --> 01:21:53,840
How honest of him.

1651
01:21:54,210 --> 01:21:55,210
Eight?

1652
01:21:57,680 --> 01:22:01,150
Team P2, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

1653
01:22:02,420 --> 01:22:04,290
The average price is nine million dollars.

1654
01:22:04,750 --> 01:22:07,260
I simply have to judge whether it's more
or less than the average.

1655
01:22:07,520 --> 01:22:09,260
But does Michael Jackson's jacket...

1656
01:22:09,260 --> 01:22:10,990
have a value of more than
nine million dollars?

1657
01:22:10,990 --> 01:22:12,800
I was going to follow along
with the bidding.

1658
01:22:13,060 --> 01:22:14,360
If the numbers reached a high number,

1659
01:22:14,360 --> 01:22:17,300
it seemed like a good idea...

1660
01:22:17,300 --> 01:22:19,800
to keep bidding first and then drop out.

1661
01:22:23,210 --> 01:22:25,540
Team P2 has submitted cube number 10.

1662
01:22:27,810 --> 01:22:31,350
Team P3, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

1663
01:22:33,420 --> 01:22:34,920
It's a very famous commercial,

1664
01:22:35,120 --> 01:22:36,850
and the jacket was worn
in that very commercial.

1665
01:22:36,850 --> 01:22:40,190
There was a chance
that it could be expensive.

1666
01:22:44,430 --> 01:22:45,560
I'll pass on this bid.

1667
01:22:46,830 --> 01:22:48,770
Team P3 has passed on this bid.

1668
01:22:50,500 --> 01:22:52,500
But when I thought about it again,

1669
01:22:53,000 --> 01:22:55,100
Michael Jackson was a singer.

1670
01:22:55,840 --> 01:22:58,780
Just imagine how many outfits
he must've worn.

1671
01:22:59,210 --> 01:23:02,910
What really decides the value of something
is how rare it is.

1672
01:23:03,210 --> 01:23:05,280
So technically speaking,
could that be Michael Jackson's...

1673
01:23:05,280 --> 01:23:07,050
only legendary outfit?

1674
01:23:07,050 --> 01:23:10,120
So my conclusion was that
it couldn't be expensive.

1675
01:23:11,590 --> 01:23:12,620
I'll pass on this bid.

1676
01:23:13,160 --> 01:23:14,760
Since Nam Hee, who was later in the order,

1677
01:23:15,020 --> 01:23:17,330
was still alive,
it was fine even if I got eliminated.

1678
01:23:17,690 --> 01:23:20,230
So when Seong Beom passed on the bid,
I did too.

1679
01:23:20,330 --> 01:23:22,130
Team Challenger,
please submit the cubes...

1680
01:23:22,130 --> 01:23:23,900
if you would like to place a bid.

1681
01:23:24,570 --> 01:23:26,100
You have three minutes to decide.

1682
01:23:27,270 --> 01:23:30,510
The best strategy for our alliance
was for all of us to win the bids.

1683
01:23:31,110 --> 01:23:34,580
We wanted to win it with 12,

1684
01:23:34,880 --> 01:23:37,050
so Nam Hee only had to bid with 12.

1685
01:23:42,250 --> 01:23:43,750
I'll pass on this bid.

1686
01:23:44,990 --> 01:23:45,960
What?

1687
01:23:46,360 --> 01:23:48,360
Team Challenger has passed on this bid.

1688
01:23:49,730 --> 01:23:51,130
- Why did you pass?
- Why?

1689
01:23:51,890 --> 01:23:54,060
- Should I not?
- You can't take it back.

1690
01:23:54,560 --> 01:23:55,700
For real?

1691
01:23:55,900 --> 01:23:57,170
What were you thinking, Nam Hee?

1692
01:24:00,140 --> 01:24:01,200
For real?

1693
01:24:04,270 --> 01:24:05,580
Nam Hee.

1694
01:24:05,640 --> 01:24:06,710
For real?

1695
01:24:07,580 --> 01:24:09,250
Did I get this all wrong?

1696
01:24:10,080 --> 01:24:11,250
No, it's fine.

1697
01:24:11,680 --> 01:24:12,750
Sorry?

1698
01:24:14,280 --> 01:24:17,190
When Nam Hee passed the bid,
Tae Gyun glared at her and said,

1699
01:24:17,920 --> 01:24:19,060
"What were you thinking, Nam Hee?"

1700
01:24:19,890 --> 01:24:22,790
I don't know what just happened,
but there's been a hiccup in the alliance.

1701
01:24:23,060 --> 01:24:26,560
If that wasn't a highly trained
bluffing act,

1702
01:24:26,560 --> 01:24:28,160
it was an actual mistake.

1703
01:24:30,130 --> 01:24:31,230
For real?

1704
01:24:31,830 --> 01:24:34,800
Honestly,
I knew Michael Jackson's jacket...

1705
01:24:34,800 --> 01:24:37,010
wasn't that expensive,

1706
01:24:37,240 --> 01:24:38,840
so I wanted the others
to pass on the bidding.

1707
01:24:38,840 --> 01:24:40,210
But I had gotten it all wrong.

1708
01:24:40,210 --> 01:24:42,510
Tae Gyun's strategy
was to buy all of them.

1709
01:24:42,980 --> 01:24:44,280
We were to buy all of them.

1710
01:24:47,920 --> 01:24:49,750
Team P1, please submit the cubes...

1711
01:24:49,750 --> 01:24:51,390
- if you would like to place a bid.
- Gosh.

1712
01:24:54,120 --> 01:24:57,090
I made sure she understood the strategy
up until the moment...

1713
01:24:58,560 --> 01:25:00,060
we entered the gaming area.

1714
01:25:00,300 --> 01:25:02,500
Not letting the other teams win
even one round is what we should aim for.

1715
01:25:02,930 --> 01:25:07,740
(Tae Gyun explained the strategy
before heading to the main hall.)

1716
01:25:14,340 --> 01:25:15,680
I had to...

1717
01:25:16,810 --> 01:25:18,350
clean up the mess.

1718
01:25:18,980 --> 01:25:23,090
My cube number 8 was up against cube 10.

1719
01:25:25,920 --> 01:25:27,720
I started the auction
in an unfavorable state.

1720
01:25:28,560 --> 01:25:30,890
If I submitted cube six,

1721
01:25:30,890 --> 01:25:32,730
the opponent would counterattack
with the same cube six.

1722
01:25:33,260 --> 01:25:35,670
But to use up two low-number cubes,

1723
01:25:35,670 --> 01:25:37,970
I'd be using up too many cubes.

1724
01:25:39,200 --> 01:25:42,240
When I thought about which number
would put the opponent in a tough spot...

1725
01:25:48,640 --> 01:25:49,750
Here's my bet.

1726
01:25:51,450 --> 01:25:53,950
Team C has submitted cube number ten.

1727
01:25:54,920 --> 01:25:57,350
As we can't bid the same number,

1728
01:25:57,750 --> 01:26:00,390
the opponent had to bid
a higher number than eight.

1729
01:26:00,720 --> 01:26:04,190
But judging by
how he started the bid at ten,

1730
01:26:04,560 --> 01:26:09,400
I thought he didn't want to use...

1731
01:26:09,400 --> 01:26:11,070
a cube over 12.

1732
01:26:11,300 --> 01:26:12,670
With me submitting ten,

1733
01:26:12,670 --> 01:26:14,540
I believed they'd pass on the bid.

1734
01:26:17,470 --> 01:26:20,580
Team P2, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

1735
01:26:22,010 --> 01:26:23,550
Fifteen. Twelve.

1736
01:26:24,380 --> 01:26:26,380
Twenty-two.

1737
01:26:28,280 --> 01:26:30,220
How much is it?

1738
01:26:31,050 --> 01:26:32,190
Quite pricey, right?

1739
01:26:33,960 --> 01:26:35,290
To buy the item,

1740
01:26:35,960 --> 01:26:37,090
I couldn't submit eight.

1741
01:26:37,090 --> 01:26:38,900
I had to submit 11 and win with 22.

1742
01:26:39,260 --> 01:26:41,330
