2254
01:46:42,130 --> 01:46:44,130
Is it not? In that case, 18 is too much.

2255
01:46:44,130 --> 01:46:45,570
There are so many more items left.

2256
01:46:45,570 --> 01:46:48,140
- Team P1...
- They're spending recklessly.

2257
01:46:48,140 --> 01:46:49,240
Yes. They're going overboard.

2258
01:46:49,240 --> 01:46:51,670
They're just hoping
they'll end the rounds quickly.

2259
01:46:51,670 --> 01:46:52,910
- Team P1?
- Yes.

2260
01:46:53,640 --> 01:46:55,610
Why are the rest helping them?

2261
01:46:55,610 --> 01:46:56,610
I also don't get it.

2262
01:46:56,780 --> 01:46:58,110
I really don't understand.

2263
01:46:58,110 --> 01:46:59,710
- Bye.
- See you.

2264
01:47:04,890 --> 01:47:09,820
(Jin Ho runs to his room.)

2265
01:47:11,430 --> 01:47:12,690
Guys, how much is the watch worth?

2266
01:47:13,430 --> 01:47:15,460
It's definitely less than
ten million dollars.

2267
01:47:15,460 --> 01:47:17,000
It's less than ten million dollars, right?
It's fine, then.

2268
01:47:17,000 --> 01:47:18,470
- He...
- You passed, didn't you?

2269
01:47:18,470 --> 01:47:19,730
Team P1 bought it at 18 again.

2270
01:47:19,730 --> 01:47:21,740
- Team P1? They bought it at 18?
- Yes.

2271
01:47:22,040 --> 01:47:23,570
For the round...

2272
01:47:23,570 --> 01:47:26,470
- Each round is different.
- Team P1 submitted 6.

2273
01:47:26,810 --> 01:47:29,040
YunB from Team P2 submitted 8.

2274
01:47:29,040 --> 01:47:30,110
- And I submitted ten.
- Good job.

2275
01:47:30,110 --> 01:47:31,780
Ten was the maximum for me.

2276
01:47:32,080 --> 01:47:34,450
But Team Rookie submitted 12.

2277
01:47:34,450 --> 01:47:36,550
Then, Team Challenger submitted 15.

2278
01:47:37,190 --> 01:47:39,920
What's more interesting was,
listening to the bidding process,

2279
01:47:40,560 --> 01:47:44,630
all the teams under the alliance
took part in the bid.

2280
01:47:44,630 --> 01:47:45,660
They didn't pass.

2281
01:47:45,660 --> 01:47:48,660
They're not even helping their ally
buy it at a cheap price either.

2282
01:47:49,260 --> 01:47:50,800
Nor are they splitting the items
among themselves.

2283
01:47:51,430 --> 01:47:52,670
Team P1 just takes it all.

2284
01:47:52,670 --> 01:47:54,570
After submitting 18 again.

2285
01:47:55,870 --> 01:47:57,110
I'm even more confused.

2286
01:47:57,240 --> 01:47:59,070
I have no idea
what this alliance is doing.

2287
01:47:59,840 --> 01:48:01,540
Hong Jin Ho and YunB came.

2288
01:48:01,540 --> 01:48:02,580
Did you buy it?

2289
01:48:02,580 --> 01:48:04,110
They don't know the price. I bought it.

2290
01:48:04,110 --> 01:48:05,980
I got it at a really cheap price.

2291
01:48:05,980 --> 01:48:06,980
- How much?
- How much?

2292
01:48:06,980 --> 01:48:08,080
Eighteen.

2293
01:48:08,080 --> 01:48:09,880
- That's amazing.
- How much?

2294
01:48:09,880 --> 01:48:12,320
It's 25... It's 26.5 million dollars.

2295
01:48:13,390 --> 01:48:15,120
(Patek Philippe Perpetual
Calendar Chronograph, Reference 1518)

2296
01:48:15,120 --> 01:48:19,260
(26.55 million dollars)

2297
01:48:19,660 --> 01:48:21,400
It's 26.5 million dollars.

2298
01:48:21,400 --> 01:48:22,930
Wait, please.

2299
01:48:22,930 --> 01:48:25,130
Don't shout,
or they'll know it's expensive.

2300
01:48:25,330 --> 01:48:27,070
Don't shout,
or they'll know it's expensive.

2301
01:48:27,640 --> 01:48:28,640
Wait.

2302
01:48:28,800 --> 01:48:30,040
Let's express it with our movements.

2303
01:48:30,040 --> 01:48:32,810
She bought the item at 18 in total.

2304
01:48:33,140 --> 01:48:34,580
Eighteen cubes...

2305
01:48:34,580 --> 01:48:36,610
are exactly how much I paid...

2306
01:48:36,780 --> 01:48:39,680
for the 490,000-dollar jacket.

2307
01:48:40,150 --> 01:48:41,250
And the price...

2308
01:48:41,250 --> 01:48:42,820
is 26.5 million dollars.

2309
01:48:42,820 --> 01:48:44,090
She nailed it.

2310
01:48:44,090 --> 01:48:46,390
Ji Min did it big time.

2311
01:48:46,650 --> 01:48:48,560
It's 26.5 million dollars?

2312
01:48:49,390 --> 01:48:51,060
Oh, my gosh. I really thought...

2313
01:48:51,560 --> 01:48:53,660
it'd be 5 million dollars at most.

2314
01:48:53,660 --> 01:48:56,000
But it's 26.5 million dollars?

2315
01:48:56,260 --> 01:48:58,430
I finally played my part.

2316
01:48:59,200 --> 01:49:01,300
Watches are manufactured goods,

2317
01:49:01,300 --> 01:49:03,300
and there are a lot of limited editions...

2318
01:49:03,300 --> 01:49:04,510
and old watches.

2319
01:49:04,810 --> 01:49:06,510
I think...

2320
01:49:11,980 --> 01:49:12,980
It must be expensive.

2321
01:49:15,480 --> 01:49:19,520
(A roar and a shout
heard from Team P1's room)

2322
01:49:19,720 --> 01:49:21,490
I can't tell whose voice that was.
It was Sang Min, right?

2323
01:49:21,490 --> 01:49:24,060
It was Ji Min and Sang Min.

2324
01:49:24,060 --> 01:49:25,990
If they're that happy about it,
it means it's worth 30 million dollars.

2325
01:49:26,330 --> 01:49:27,330
No way.

2326
01:49:27,330 --> 01:49:29,530
But would Sang Min shout like that?

2327
01:49:30,200 --> 01:49:31,200
Wholeheartedly?

2328
01:49:31,200 --> 01:49:32,670
So loud for us to hear?

2329
01:49:32,670 --> 01:49:34,370
He could if he was really happy.

2330
01:49:34,370 --> 01:49:35,400
He doesn't fake it.

2331
01:49:35,400 --> 01:49:36,500
- He doesn't fake it.
- No.

2332
01:49:36,500 --> 01:49:38,040
Then it could really be a good one.

2333
01:49:39,910 --> 01:49:41,640
From Team P1's room, which was far away,

2334
01:49:41,640 --> 01:49:43,850
we heard someone scream suddenly.

2335
01:49:43,850 --> 01:49:45,550
Then, we heard a cheer.

2336
01:49:46,710 --> 01:49:51,190
We asked if the team acted like that
to fool others,

2337
01:49:51,190 --> 01:49:53,090
and Jin Ho said probably not.

2338
01:49:53,560 --> 01:49:54,720
Then it's either of the two.

2339
01:49:55,120 --> 01:49:57,360
Patek Philippe is ridiculously expensive,

2340
01:49:57,530 --> 01:49:58,990
or there was a bug in the room.

2341
01:50:00,460 --> 01:50:03,060
Expensive... Is it expensive?

2342
01:50:04,000 --> 01:50:05,170
But our stance is,

2343
01:50:05,170 --> 01:50:06,730
- it's good if we win,
- Let's not get swayed by them.

2344
01:50:06,730 --> 01:50:07,940
but we're fine as long as
we're in top three.

2345
01:50:07,940 --> 01:50:09,170
- That's right.
- So it doesn't matter.

2346
01:50:09,170 --> 01:50:10,410
The other teams are supporting Team P1,

2347
01:50:10,410 --> 01:50:12,540
- so in the end...
- They must be more pissed than us.

2348
01:50:12,540 --> 01:50:15,380
Teams Rookie and Challenger
will start to feel impatient.

2349
01:50:15,380 --> 01:50:16,950
- That's the same as us.
- They'll think they need to win the bids.

2350
01:50:16,950 --> 01:50:20,080
I thought it would be
less than ten million dollars.

2351
01:50:20,080 --> 01:50:22,150
I submitted cube number ten,
thinking I'm willing to pay that much.

2352
01:50:22,150 --> 01:50:25,190
But we should think beforehand,
and if it's worth cube number 12,

2353
01:50:25,190 --> 01:50:26,990
- we should...
- The maximum amount.

2354
01:50:26,990 --> 01:50:28,860
submit the cube closest to
the maximum value.

2355
01:50:28,860 --> 01:50:30,160
- So even if the three team up,
- They can't team up.

2356
01:50:30,160 --> 01:50:32,090
- we need to increase the bid.
- Because they submit big numbers.

2357
01:50:32,090 --> 01:50:33,290
So I submit the maximum number,

2358
01:50:33,290 --> 01:50:34,730
as if saying,
"Go ahead if you want to bid higher."

2359
01:50:34,730 --> 01:50:36,860
"Gosh, I'm out." And we can run away.

2360
01:50:36,860 --> 01:50:38,700
Increase the bid from the start.
That's better.

2361
01:50:38,700 --> 01:50:40,970
Let's submit 12 for 10 million dollars.

2362
01:50:40,970 --> 01:50:43,300
Maximum 15, maybe.

2363
01:50:43,300 --> 01:50:45,570
- Fifteen for ten million dollars.
- That sounds good.

2364
01:50:45,870 --> 01:50:47,510
In between 12 and 15.

2365
01:50:47,510 --> 01:50:50,980
YunB, I did talk about this
with Seung Jin just now.

2366
01:50:50,980 --> 01:50:53,850
The special cards which profits us,
like times two cards.

2367
01:50:54,150 --> 01:50:55,520
Multiplying a cheap item card by two...

2368
01:50:55,520 --> 01:50:56,650
is meaningless.

2369
01:50:56,650 --> 01:50:58,950
- Yes. We should prioritize the items.
- The items are a lot more important.

2370
01:50:58,950 --> 01:51:01,760
So we don't need to spend so much
on the special cards.

2371
01:51:01,960 --> 01:51:03,420
- That's what I want to say.
- Hear, hear.

2372
01:51:03,420 --> 01:51:06,460
The benefit cards or the loss cards
under the name special cards...

2373
01:51:06,460 --> 01:51:09,560
aren't exactly that beneficial
when you get it.

2374
01:51:09,830 --> 01:51:12,070
If you spend too many cubes to buy it,

2375
01:51:12,070 --> 01:51:14,570
you have a higher chance
to get the next loss card.

2376
01:51:14,570 --> 01:51:17,240
Most of the loss cards cancel out
the profits...

2377
01:51:17,240 --> 01:51:18,540
of the profit cards.

2378
01:51:18,540 --> 01:51:20,810
We decided to focus on buying...

2379
01:51:20,810 --> 01:51:22,410
the item cards with high values.

2380
01:51:22,740 --> 01:51:24,250
Don't shout,
or they'll know it's expensive.

2381
01:51:25,080 --> 01:51:26,080
- Wait.
- Be quiet.

2382
01:51:26,410 --> 01:51:27,480
Let's express it with our movements.

2383
01:51:27,480 --> 01:51:28,680
They'll know if we shout.

2384
01:51:28,680 --> 01:51:30,690
- Why didn't you win it?
- Because...

2385
01:51:30,690 --> 01:51:32,020
the round went like this.

2386
01:51:32,520 --> 01:51:34,320
If I had bought it...

2387
01:51:35,220 --> 01:51:36,220
I...

2388
01:51:36,290 --> 01:51:37,490
My turn was after theirs.

2389
01:51:37,760 --> 01:51:38,890
- So...
- Did you pass?

2390
01:51:39,390 --> 01:51:41,100
I asked why he didn't win it.

2391
01:51:41,100 --> 01:51:43,670
He said the situation didn't allow it,
and he had no choice.

2392
01:51:43,870 --> 01:51:45,670
I guess it can't be helped.

2393
01:51:46,870 --> 01:51:48,840
Thankfully,
Team Rookie didn't win it either.

2394
01:51:49,000 --> 01:51:50,810
We managed to avoid that.

2395
01:51:51,040 --> 01:51:53,470
You Hyun can go and win the next round.

2396
01:51:53,980 --> 01:51:55,940
It's the same situation as before.
We're just repeating it.

2397
01:51:55,940 --> 01:51:58,280
- Who is going next?
- Me.

2398
01:51:58,280 --> 01:51:59,650
You Hyun. And...

2399
01:51:59,650 --> 01:52:01,920
Keun Woo, and Beom.

2400
01:52:01,920 --> 01:52:02,980
(You Hyun, Keun Woo, and Kwak Beom
will play Round 3.)

2401
01:52:02,980 --> 01:52:05,690
If the card this round is an item card,
your team will win it.

2402
01:52:05,790 --> 01:52:08,260
Keun Woo, submit one cube.

2403
01:52:08,460 --> 01:52:10,160
Submit one cube, and...

2404
01:52:10,160 --> 01:52:12,990
You Hyun, tell him
what number he needs to submit.

2405
01:52:12,990 --> 01:52:14,500
You need to tell Keun Woo.

2406
01:52:14,500 --> 01:52:16,130
- What number to submit?
- Yes.

2407
01:52:16,660 --> 01:52:18,170
So for you...

2408
01:52:18,170 --> 01:52:19,870
For the first bid,

2409
01:52:19,870 --> 01:52:22,100
you can either submit 5 or 15,

2410
01:52:22,100 --> 01:52:24,240
or a total of 9
by submitting 5 and 4 together.

2411
01:52:24,240 --> 01:52:25,540
You can submit 5, 9, or 15.

2412
01:52:25,540 --> 01:52:26,970
You need to be aware of that.

2413
01:52:27,080 --> 01:52:28,410
You do that,

2414
01:52:28,510 --> 01:52:30,310
and Team R should pass.

2415
01:52:30,310 --> 01:52:31,650
- Team R. Where is Beom?
- Pass.

2416
01:52:31,650 --> 01:52:32,980
Yes, you need to pass.

2417
01:52:33,150 --> 01:52:34,950
Just pass if it's an item card.

2418
01:52:35,450 --> 01:52:36,780
Pass on the item card?

2419
01:52:37,290 --> 01:52:38,750
We need to pass so they can win it.

2420
01:52:39,190 --> 01:52:41,520
In most cases,

2421
01:52:41,520 --> 01:52:44,090
either my team or Team C
will win the items.

2422
01:52:44,090 --> 01:52:47,030
Team R will save up on the cubes,

2423
01:52:47,030 --> 01:52:50,530
and when an expensive item comes up,
win it even if you have to overspend.

2424
01:52:51,400 --> 01:52:52,630
From the alliance's perspective,

2425
01:52:53,070 --> 01:52:55,400
Team R winning the items...

2426
01:52:55,400 --> 01:52:57,270
is the worst scenario.

2427
01:52:57,270 --> 01:52:59,040
If Team R wins an item,

2428
01:52:59,040 --> 01:53:01,510
they'll become the first bidder
of the following round.

2429
01:53:01,910 --> 01:53:05,180
After we three teams bid in a row,

2430
01:53:05,550 --> 01:53:07,520
Teams P2 and P3 will bid.

2431
01:53:07,750 --> 01:53:11,190
On the other hand, if Team C or Team P1...

2432
01:53:11,190 --> 01:53:12,390
win an item,

2433
01:53:12,390 --> 01:53:15,390
one of the allied teams
will start the bid first,

2434
01:53:15,760 --> 01:53:18,630
Teams P2 and P3 are in the middle,

2435
01:53:18,630 --> 01:53:22,160
and after them, the allied teams
can join the bid.

2436
01:53:22,300 --> 01:53:24,700
That way, we can make them bid...

2437
01:53:24,700 --> 01:53:27,170
higher-numbered cubes.

2438
01:53:27,170 --> 01:53:30,400
But it's hard to make it happen
if Team R wins a bid.

2439
01:53:30,400 --> 01:53:31,670
So it isn't that great.

2440
01:53:31,740 --> 01:53:34,310
Beom. If it's a special card,

2441
01:53:34,410 --> 01:53:37,750
unless it's a crazy loss,
we'll take the fall.

2442
01:53:38,010 --> 01:53:39,780
We'll submit one.

2443
01:53:39,780 --> 01:53:42,950
You and Team C can submit two.

2444
01:53:43,220 --> 01:53:44,850
- When there's a loss card?
- For a loss card.

2445
01:53:44,850 --> 01:53:46,350
If there's a loss card, we'll take it.

2446
01:53:46,350 --> 01:53:48,890
If it's a profit card,
your team should win it.

2447
01:53:48,890 --> 01:53:52,160
My team and Team C will submit one...

2448
01:53:52,160 --> 01:53:55,100
But the chances of a profit card
coming up are slim.

2449
01:53:55,100 --> 01:53:57,670
I don't know if he said that
thinking we wouldn't notice...

2450
01:53:57,670 --> 01:54:00,430
or if he thinks of us as complete fools.

2451
01:54:00,770 --> 01:54:03,140
Blind Auction itself...

2452
01:54:03,300 --> 01:54:05,670
isn't exactly all that advantageous
for big groups.

2453
01:54:06,240 --> 01:54:08,940
There are many variables to consider.

2454
01:54:08,940 --> 01:54:10,810
What if we don't win any items
and the game ends?

2455
01:54:11,150 --> 01:54:14,420
What they want is
for Team C to submit a cube...

2456
01:54:14,420 --> 01:54:16,520
and for us to pass.

2457
01:54:18,220 --> 01:54:19,850
But if it's so tempting.

2458
01:54:20,120 --> 01:54:21,620
Let's say
it's a really expensive property.

2459
01:54:22,960 --> 01:54:25,190
Act for a bit, win the bid,

2460
01:54:25,190 --> 01:54:26,560
and say you were scared.

2461
01:54:29,400 --> 01:54:31,270
Won't that look way too foolish?

2462
01:54:31,270 --> 01:54:32,430
Should I act foolishly from now?

2463
01:54:34,070 --> 01:54:35,740
I don't know. Should I act?

2464
01:54:36,200 --> 01:54:38,170
This is a survival show.
Act like you're in it.

2465
01:54:38,240 --> 01:54:39,570
This is a survival show.

2466
01:54:39,740 --> 01:54:41,880
I have one Fool Card.

2467
01:54:41,880 --> 01:54:44,350
"If I think an item is expensive,"

2468
01:54:44,350 --> 01:54:45,450
"I'll buy it."

2469
01:54:45,450 --> 01:54:47,280
"I'll act like a fool and buy it."

2470
01:54:47,620 --> 01:54:49,180
But after buying it,

2471
01:54:49,180 --> 01:54:51,590
I'll say, "I made a mistake."

2472
01:54:51,590 --> 01:54:52,890
"I'm a fool."

2473
01:54:52,920 --> 01:54:54,090
I do feel anxious.

2474
01:54:54,460 --> 01:54:55,760
Once things start...

2475
01:54:55,760 --> 01:54:57,890
to play out in the way
which isn't safe for us,

2476
01:54:58,060 --> 01:55:00,460
let's win an item even if
we need to act like a loose cannon.

2477
01:55:00,900 --> 01:55:05,830
(Team C is also anxious.)

2478
01:55:05,830 --> 01:55:07,540
If we follow this strategy,

2479
01:55:08,070 --> 01:55:09,370
what are the chances of that team...

2480
01:55:09,370 --> 01:55:11,170
not winning any item in 14 rounds?

2481
01:55:11,440 --> 01:55:12,470
How many percent?

2482
01:55:12,470 --> 01:55:13,840
But this is what's important.

2483
01:55:13,910 --> 01:55:16,740
When a very expensive item comes up,

2484
01:55:16,940 --> 01:55:20,210
the opponent could use many cubes
to buy it.

2485
01:55:20,210 --> 01:55:22,750
In that case, they could...

2486
01:55:23,150 --> 01:55:24,350
win the game. It's possible.

2487
01:55:24,350 --> 01:55:26,350
You must know since you've been
on many survival shows,

2488
01:55:26,350 --> 01:55:28,320
but a big alliance always...

2489
01:55:28,320 --> 01:55:29,760
- Doesn't always win.
- That's right.

2490
01:55:29,760 --> 01:55:32,090
We're playing like this for now,

2491
01:55:32,330 --> 01:55:34,560
but honestly, if we win 1st and 2nd place,
1 of them place 3rd,

2492
01:55:34,560 --> 01:55:35,800
- Yes.
- and the 4th and 5th...

2493
01:55:35,800 --> 01:55:36,960
- Yes.
- Actually, the chances...

2494
01:55:36,960 --> 01:55:38,100
of that happening is higher.

2495
01:55:38,100 --> 01:55:40,670
You're right.
That's exactly what I'm worried about.

2496
01:55:40,670 --> 01:55:43,070
So I want us to plan in a way...

2497
01:55:43,840 --> 01:55:45,870
where my team can place second.

2498
01:55:46,140 --> 01:55:49,040
You don't know what will happen
in survival shows.

2499
01:55:49,110 --> 01:55:51,510
So we need a safety net...

2500
01:55:51,510 --> 01:55:52,880
not to get eliminated.

2501
01:55:52,880 --> 01:55:56,180
I asked Tae Gyun again.

2502
01:55:58,050 --> 01:56:00,290
The strategy meeting session is over.

2503
01:56:00,660 --> 01:56:02,660
Please gather in the main hall.

2504
01:56:02,920 --> 01:56:05,690
The auction for Round Three
will now begin.

2505
01:56:06,290 --> 01:56:08,800
Team P1, select the item.

2506
01:56:08,900 --> 01:56:11,570
Jeong Keun Woo's back number.
I choose eight.

2507
01:56:11,570 --> 01:56:13,630
Item number eight has been selected.

2508
01:56:13,630 --> 01:56:15,100
(Team P1 chooses item number 8.)

2509
01:56:18,640 --> 01:56:19,870
The item card.

2510
01:56:19,870 --> 01:56:22,910
It's Virgin Galactic
suborbital spaceflight ticket.

2511
01:56:23,380 --> 01:56:26,480
It's a round-trip ticket
from 80km altitude...

2512
01:56:26,480 --> 01:56:28,650
to the space boundary of 200km altitude.

2513
01:56:29,150 --> 01:56:33,190
Leonardo DiCaprio, Brad Pitt,
Justin Bieber,

2514
01:56:33,190 --> 01:56:34,720
and other famous celebrities
have purchased it.

2515
01:56:36,360 --> 01:56:37,760
- It doesn't cost a lot.
- It doesn't.

2516
01:56:37,760 --> 01:56:39,730
- Really?
- I'm guessing one million dollars.

2517
01:56:39,730 --> 01:56:41,400
The spaceflight ticket.

2518
01:56:41,400 --> 01:56:42,960
- Is it only one million dollars?
- It...

2519
01:56:42,960 --> 01:56:44,970
- Isn't it 10 million?
- Isn't it 5 to 10 million?

2520
01:56:44,970 --> 01:56:46,330
You can go to space so easily?

2521
01:56:46,730 --> 01:56:50,070
Do you think ten million dollars
grows on trees?

2522
01:56:50,170 --> 01:56:51,870
Since it's going to space,

2523
01:56:51,870 --> 01:56:54,180
I thought it'd cost
a few hundred million dollars.

2524
01:56:54,240 --> 01:56:56,640
(The first team to bid is Team P1.)

2525
01:56:56,640 --> 01:57:00,110
Team P1, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

2526
01:57:01,420 --> 01:57:02,520
(Glancing)

2527
01:57:05,290 --> 01:57:06,350
A minute, please.

2528
01:57:10,060 --> 01:57:11,930
We were supposed to win it.

2529
01:57:12,160 --> 01:57:15,360
I was supposed to tell Keun Woo
which cube to start with.

2530
01:57:15,360 --> 01:57:17,930
So I kept thinking about
how much I should spend...

2531
01:57:17,930 --> 01:57:19,200
to win it.

2532
01:57:20,670 --> 01:57:23,470
He kept thinking hard.

2533
01:57:23,470 --> 01:57:24,940
"Did they not plan this beforehand?"

2534
01:57:24,940 --> 01:57:28,040
I heard they'd whispered, outright talked,

2535
01:57:28,040 --> 01:57:30,640
and gave signals in the previous round.

2536
01:57:36,280 --> 01:57:38,350
But it isn't expensive.

2537
01:57:38,990 --> 01:57:41,890
Interestingly, the item is something...

2538
01:57:42,090 --> 01:57:43,120
that I know.

2539
01:57:43,360 --> 01:57:44,830
You can launch and retrieve it.

2540
01:57:44,830 --> 01:57:46,130
Technology has improved a lot.

2541
01:57:46,230 --> 01:57:50,400
So the price became a lot cheaper
from what I know.

2542
01:57:50,970 --> 01:57:54,340
This definitely can't be more expensive...

2543
01:57:54,340 --> 01:57:56,400
than three million dollars.

2544
01:57:56,740 --> 01:57:59,710
From what I know,

2545
01:57:59,840 --> 01:58:01,780
it's just 2 to 3 million dollars.

2546
01:58:01,780 --> 01:58:04,880
It's just zero-gravity.

2547
01:58:04,880 --> 01:58:06,350
It's that ticket.

2548
01:58:06,950 --> 01:58:09,920
Billionaires ride it once in a blue moon.

2549
01:58:10,250 --> 01:58:11,450
This isn't...

2550
01:58:11,590 --> 01:58:13,020
It's very cheap.

2551
01:58:13,990 --> 01:58:15,920
Right, this doesn't cost a lot.

2552
01:58:15,920 --> 01:58:17,530
He needs to win it
without spending too much.

2553
01:58:17,530 --> 01:58:18,790
It'll be bad if things get heated up here.

2554
01:58:18,790 --> 01:58:19,890
What's the item?

2555
01:58:19,890 --> 01:58:22,060
- A round-trip to the space.
- A round-trip ticket.

2556
01:58:22,060 --> 01:58:23,130
How much is it?

2557
01:58:23,130 --> 01:58:26,130
At most, it's one million dollars.

2558
01:58:26,130 --> 01:58:28,240
I was worried he'd unnecessarily buy it...

2559
01:58:28,240 --> 01:58:30,570
thinking it's expensive.

2560
01:58:30,840 --> 01:58:32,210
You don't need to buy this.

2561
01:58:32,210 --> 01:58:34,740
I knew it was cheap.

2562
01:58:34,840 --> 01:58:37,280
One of the singers was deciding...

2563
01:58:37,280 --> 01:58:38,980
whether to go or not.

2564
01:58:38,980 --> 01:58:40,950
So there were a lot of news articles
about it back then.

2565
01:58:40,950 --> 01:58:43,720
They'd revealed the price too.

2566
01:58:44,050 --> 01:58:45,990
You shouldn't buy it.

2567
01:58:50,360 --> 01:58:51,430
Submit 15.

2568
01:58:52,260 --> 01:58:53,330
- Fifteen?
- Yes.

2569
01:58:56,130 --> 01:58:59,130
Team P1 has submitted cube number 15.

2570
01:58:59,130 --> 01:59:00,130
(Team P1 submits 15.)

2571
01:59:00,730 --> 01:59:04,410
You Hyun told Keun Woo to submit 15.

2572
01:59:04,670 --> 01:59:06,710
That was already so strange.

2573
01:59:07,170 --> 01:59:08,680
Will Team P1 win this too?

2574
01:59:08,710 --> 01:59:11,380
If they want to win it,
shouldn't they win at a lower price?

2575
01:59:11,480 --> 01:59:12,950
Am I the only one who knows its price?

2576
01:59:13,380 --> 01:59:16,850
Team P2, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

2577
01:59:17,950 --> 01:59:19,690
A spaceflight ticket.

2578
01:59:19,690 --> 01:59:22,620
I've seen it on the news.

2579
01:59:22,760 --> 01:59:24,730
I don't remember the exact figure,

2580
01:59:24,730 --> 01:59:27,130
but I kind of had a gist...

2581
01:59:27,230 --> 01:59:28,800
that it wasn't crazy expensive.

2582
01:59:29,030 --> 01:59:30,060
I'll pass.

2583
01:59:30,760 --> 01:59:32,970
Team P2 has passed on this bid.

2584
01:59:33,470 --> 01:59:36,440
Passing means
we have that many cubes left.

2585
01:59:36,440 --> 01:59:39,140
Let's not bet on something
I'm not certain about.

2586
01:59:39,570 --> 01:59:43,380
Team P3, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

2587
01:59:48,920 --> 01:59:50,820
So their strategy is to prevent us
from winning items, after all.

2588
01:59:51,090 --> 01:59:53,450
I can't submit a cube higher than 15.

2589
01:59:54,290 --> 01:59:57,420
I thought I'd be revealing the information
to them if I passed right away,

2590
01:59:57,660 --> 01:59:58,860
so I pretended to think hard about it.

2591
02:00:00,560 --> 02:00:03,700
But I can't submit cube number 15. Never.

2592
02:00:03,830 --> 02:00:05,130
I can't submit cube number 16.

2593
02:00:10,140 --> 02:00:11,240
I'll pass.

2594
02:00:11,910 --> 02:00:14,180
Team P3 has passed on this bid.

2595
02:00:15,880 --> 02:00:16,940
I'll pass.

2596
02:00:17,410 --> 02:00:19,510
Team Rookie has passed on this bid.

2597
02:00:20,050 --> 02:00:23,150
I thought those who watched the news
would know about it.

2598
02:00:23,150 --> 02:00:24,920
I passed lightheartedly.

2599
02:00:25,020 --> 02:00:28,360
Team C, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

2600
02:00:34,930 --> 02:00:38,000
Team C has submitted cube number 20.

2601
02:00:39,630 --> 02:00:41,770
Team R passed right away,

2602
02:00:41,770 --> 02:00:44,310
and Team C bid cube number 20.

2603
02:00:44,740 --> 02:00:47,810
He could've won it at 16.

2604
02:00:48,010 --> 02:00:49,840
What's happening?

2605
02:00:49,940 --> 02:00:51,080
I'll pass.

2606
02:00:51,250 --> 02:00:53,510
Team P1 has passed on this bid.

2607
02:00:53,850 --> 02:00:56,720
Team C has won the item card.

2608
02:00:56,720 --> 02:00:58,350
(Team C has won the item card
for the suborbital spaceflight ticket.)

2609
02:00:58,520 --> 02:01:00,590
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

2610
02:01:01,660 --> 02:01:05,430
Actually, the item isn't worth
such a big cube number.

2611
02:01:05,830 --> 02:01:07,460
But he bid quite a big amount.

2612
02:01:07,460 --> 02:01:10,230
You Hyun must be unaware of its price.

2613
02:01:15,140 --> 02:01:16,770
You won such a cheap item.

2614
02:01:17,300 --> 02:01:18,370
I know.

2615
02:01:19,810 --> 02:01:20,870
I even know the price.

2616
02:01:21,140 --> 02:01:24,480
It's 500,000 dollars,
give or take 100,000 to 200,000 dollars.

2617
02:01:24,480 --> 02:01:26,210
That's the figure I remember.

2618
02:01:26,210 --> 02:01:29,320
Please bring the cubes you submitted
and take the card.

2619
02:01:29,420 --> 02:01:31,590
(He checks the price of the card he won.)

2620
02:01:31,650 --> 02:01:34,020
(Suborbital spaceflight ticket)

2621
02:01:34,020 --> 02:01:36,620
(650,000 dollars)

2622
02:01:39,190 --> 02:01:41,400
"They could win the item."

2623
02:01:41,630 --> 02:01:45,270
I thought I should start
with a big number.

2624
02:01:45,270 --> 02:01:47,870
I thought the priority was
to leave as many cubes as I could.

2625
02:01:47,870 --> 02:01:50,370
Even if I have to pay more than necessary,
I should just use one cube,

2626
02:01:50,370 --> 02:01:52,270
that is, cube number 20, to win the item.

2627
02:01:53,470 --> 02:01:55,910
(Lots Secured by Each Team)

2628
02:01:55,910 --> 02:01:59,110
(Team C: Spaceflight ticket,
650,000 dollars)

2629
02:01:59,180 --> 02:02:00,880
(Team P1's room)

2630
02:02:01,680 --> 02:02:03,720
So I won the item.

2631
02:02:03,720 --> 02:02:06,020
I know the exact price of the item.

2632
02:02:06,020 --> 02:02:07,620
- I read the news.
- You won it?

2633
02:02:07,620 --> 02:02:08,890
We won it.

2634
02:02:08,890 --> 02:02:10,620
- Isn't it around a million dollars?
- Sorry?

2635
02:02:10,620 --> 02:02:12,560
- Isn't it a million dollars?
- It's 650,000 dollars.

2636
02:02:13,030 --> 02:02:14,400
How much did you pay for it?

2637
02:02:14,400 --> 02:02:15,560
Just one cube, 20.

2638
02:02:15,560 --> 02:02:16,800
- Twenty?
- Yes.

2639
02:02:16,800 --> 02:02:18,270
- It's simple.
- Hold on.

2640
02:02:18,270 --> 02:02:20,330
What number did Team P3 submit?

2641
02:02:20,330 --> 02:02:21,540
None of them submitted. They passed.

2642
02:02:21,540 --> 02:02:23,500
- Three passes.
- Three teams passed?

2643
02:02:23,500 --> 02:02:25,010
Then you...

2644
02:02:25,010 --> 02:02:26,570
You could've submitted the smallest cube.

2645
02:02:26,570 --> 02:02:28,310
No. He submitted 15.

2646
02:02:28,310 --> 02:02:29,840
- Why did you submit 15?
- I did.

2647
02:02:29,840 --> 02:02:31,280
- Did you tell him to submit 15?
- Yes.

2648
02:02:31,480 --> 02:02:33,310
- Why didn't you go with five?
- Wasn't that too much?

2649
02:02:34,350 --> 02:02:35,950
He always has a reason.

2650
02:02:35,950 --> 02:02:37,480
He knew it was cheap,

2651
02:02:37,480 --> 02:02:39,590
but he could bid 20...

2652
02:02:39,590 --> 02:02:41,220
Sure.

2653
02:02:41,220 --> 02:02:42,860
You have everything planned out.

2654
02:02:43,360 --> 02:02:46,660
You bought it at 20. Great job.

2655
02:02:46,930 --> 02:02:49,660
Everything was executed well,
and you explained everything nicely.

2656
02:02:49,660 --> 02:02:51,500
Thank you so much.

2657
02:02:52,170 --> 02:02:53,470
I'm so tired.

2658
02:02:53,570 --> 02:02:55,070
Team C submitted 20.

2659
02:02:55,400 --> 02:02:57,170
- Twenty?
- And he won.

2660
02:02:57,170 --> 02:02:58,410
He won this at 20?

2661
02:02:58,410 --> 02:02:59,770
- What's wrong with him?
- This is cheap, though.

2662
02:02:59,770 --> 02:03:00,770
This is super cheap.

2663
02:03:01,010 --> 02:03:03,340
They're not focused on the value.

2664
02:03:03,340 --> 02:03:05,310
- They're focused on winning the items.
- They're focused on winning the items.

2665
02:03:05,350 --> 02:03:07,280
The opponents...

2666
02:03:07,410 --> 02:03:09,550
want the special cards to come up quickly.

2667
02:03:09,650 --> 02:03:11,590
Later, when the teams with little cubes
can't bid...

2668
02:03:11,790 --> 02:03:14,120
because they don't have the money,
we could win the items...

2669
02:03:14,120 --> 02:03:17,830
at a low price, which is cost-effective.
Before that happens,

2670
02:03:17,990 --> 02:03:20,990
they want three special cards
to come up at once and end the game.

2671
02:03:21,200 --> 02:03:24,700
We played thinking there would be
12 and more rounds,

2672
02:03:24,800 --> 02:03:26,000
so we played it very safe.

2673
02:03:26,170 --> 02:03:27,170
How did it go?

2674
02:03:27,800 --> 02:03:29,700
- Wasn't it around 20 million dollars?
- Not at all.

2675
02:03:30,100 --> 02:03:32,410
- Are you sure?
- It's one million dollars.

2676
02:03:32,670 --> 02:03:34,210
- Around 1.2 million?
- Yes, around that.

2677
02:03:34,210 --> 02:03:35,840
- They're doomed.
- What happened?

2678
02:03:35,840 --> 02:03:37,440
- Did you buy it?
- I passed on it.

2679
02:03:37,540 --> 02:03:38,580
Good job.

2680
02:03:38,710 --> 02:03:42,420
Then this... Team C is doomed.

2681
02:03:42,450 --> 02:03:45,190
- It's...
- Yes. Twenty is such a waste.

2682
02:03:45,190 --> 02:03:47,290
Twenty is a waste,
and they wasted two turns.

2683
02:03:47,420 --> 02:03:50,660
And when three special cards come up
in a row the game ends.

2684
02:03:51,360 --> 02:03:53,560
We could try and win the bid
in Round Four.

2685
02:03:53,560 --> 02:03:55,860
- You judge how much the next item is.
- Okay.

2686
02:03:56,030 --> 02:03:57,560
If you can win it at a cheap price,
go for it.

2687
02:03:57,560 --> 02:03:59,470
- Instead, don't buy...
- Okay.

2688
02:03:59,470 --> 02:04:00,470
- one or two million-dollar worth items.
- right.

2689
02:04:00,770 --> 02:04:03,400
- If you're unsure, don't risk it.
- I got it.

2690
02:04:03,400 --> 02:04:05,470
- I'll go straight down.
- Okay.

2691
02:04:05,470 --> 02:04:06,670
- Smoke time?
- Okay.

2692
02:04:07,270 --> 02:04:08,540
This game is fun.

2693
02:04:08,840 --> 02:04:12,580
- The seed of division...
- It's growing slowly.

2694
02:04:12,650 --> 02:04:14,820
Because Team C and...

2695
02:04:14,820 --> 02:04:17,950
- They made the wrong call.
- They...

2696
02:04:18,320 --> 02:04:21,460
They're under a dark magic spell.

2697
02:04:22,790 --> 02:04:23,960
Why do I feel so anxious?

2698
02:04:23,960 --> 02:04:26,490
There are eight special cards.

2699
02:04:27,260 --> 02:04:28,860
Don't be anxious. It's fine.

2700
02:04:29,300 --> 02:04:30,900
We're in the worst situation.

2701
02:04:31,030 --> 02:04:32,430
I'm worried about three special cards
coming up in a row.

2702
02:04:32,430 --> 02:04:34,770
We're in the worst situation.
We're screwed.

2703
02:04:35,040 --> 02:04:36,340
- We're not screwed.
- Why? You're not.

2704
02:04:36,400 --> 02:04:37,440
We're screwed.

2705
02:04:37,700 --> 02:04:39,770
The game could end way earlier
if we're unlucky.

2706
02:04:39,970 --> 02:04:41,140
- If we're unlucky?
- Yes.

2707
02:04:41,280 --> 02:04:44,580
At most, it'd be over in 15 rounds.

2708
02:04:44,750 --> 02:04:47,610
We won't have many rounds.
So we can win if we keep winning the bids.

2709
02:04:47,610 --> 02:04:50,920
At first, I was worried.
"Are they trying to stop us from buying?"

2710
02:04:51,220 --> 02:04:54,120
Because of where we stand,

2711
02:04:54,390 --> 02:04:55,920
we keep playing the support,

2712
02:04:56,090 --> 02:04:57,830
- No.
- but because of an unavoidable...

2713
02:04:57,830 --> 02:05:01,400
That was because
Ji Min went first just now.

2714
02:05:01,400 --> 02:05:02,560
- This time, we go first.
- Yes, it's changed.

2715
02:05:02,560 --> 02:05:04,400
Since the first and last bidders
have changed,

2716
02:05:04,500 --> 02:05:05,770
our positions have changed too.

2717
02:05:06,630 --> 02:05:07,940
Things got a bit messed up.

2718
02:05:08,100 --> 02:05:09,970
I can make mistakes sometimes.

2719
02:05:10,240 --> 02:05:11,410
If I end up making a mistake,

2720
02:05:11,410 --> 02:05:15,810
this isn't something
I can take responsibility for on my own.

2721
02:05:16,440 --> 02:05:17,950
I felt so pressured.

2722
02:05:18,110 --> 02:05:20,210
Hold on. Who is going this round?

2723
02:05:20,210 --> 02:05:22,220
- It's Ji Hoo. Ji Hoo, you,
- Sang Min.

2724
02:05:22,420 --> 02:05:23,750
- And...
- and Seung Yong.

2725
02:05:23,750 --> 02:05:24,890
Yes. Seung Yong...

2726
02:05:24,890 --> 02:05:26,920
For this round, you submit 15.

2727
02:05:26,920 --> 02:05:28,490
They'll submit a number in between.

2728
02:05:28,490 --> 02:05:29,790
You submit 20.

2729
02:05:29,890 --> 02:05:31,360
And Ji Hoo.

2730
02:05:31,690 --> 02:05:34,560
Submit 15 and 6, so 21 in total.

2731
02:05:34,560 --> 02:05:37,800
What if I recognize the item
and it's something...

2732
02:05:38,000 --> 02:05:39,130
we must buy?

2733
02:05:39,730 --> 02:05:41,200
You could give us a sign.

2734
02:05:41,200 --> 02:05:43,040
I'll do this and take off my hat.

2735
02:05:43,100 --> 02:05:44,640
Or why don't you wear your hat backward?

2736
02:05:46,040 --> 02:05:47,040
Less than ten million dollars.

2737
02:05:47,540 --> 02:05:48,610
More than ten million dollars.

2738
02:05:48,740 --> 02:05:50,440
- Looks good.
- Okay.

2739
02:05:50,780 --> 02:05:51,780
Okay, I got it.

2740
02:05:53,150 --> 02:05:55,050
My team must win this round.

2741
02:05:55,180 --> 02:05:56,850
You Hyun did win an item,

2742
02:05:56,850 --> 02:05:58,590
but it's only worth 600,000 dollars.

2743
02:05:58,590 --> 02:06:00,320
Team Rookie should win this round...

2744
02:06:00,720 --> 02:06:02,490
because they have no item,

2745
02:06:02,490 --> 02:06:04,220
but I'll win this round
even if I have to mess it up.

2746
02:06:04,660 --> 02:06:06,760
"I was too anxious to think straight.
I messed up."

2747
02:06:06,760 --> 02:06:08,960
I'll win no matter what,
even if I have to act.

2748
02:06:09,200 --> 02:06:10,960
(Lee Sang Min, Lee Jin Hyeong,)

2749
02:06:10,960 --> 02:06:12,570
(Choi Hye Seon,
Shin Seung Yong, Kang Ji Ho)

2750
02:06:12,670 --> 02:06:15,300
The auction for Round Four will now begin.

2751
02:06:20,140 --> 02:06:22,410
Team Challenger, select the item.

2752
02:06:28,280 --> 02:06:29,320
I choose number six.

2753
02:06:29,480 --> 02:06:31,250
Item number six has been selected.

2754
02:06:31,250 --> 02:06:34,020
(Team C chooses item number 6.)

2755
02:06:36,520 --> 02:06:39,560
It's a special card,
an item card exchange coupon.

2756
02:06:40,660 --> 02:06:42,560
(Gasp)

2757
02:06:42,560 --> 02:06:43,630
What's this?

2758
02:06:45,000 --> 02:06:47,530
You can choose one of your item cards...

2759
02:06:47,800 --> 02:06:50,570
and exchange it
with another team's item card.

2760
02:06:52,510 --> 02:06:55,580
The teams will enter the Voting Room
one by one...

2761
02:06:55,740 --> 02:06:57,240
for a blind bidding for the special card.

2762
02:06:58,850 --> 02:07:02,450
You must submit at least one cube.

2763
02:07:03,180 --> 02:07:04,720
Once all the teams have finished bidding,

2764
02:07:04,990 --> 02:07:07,320
the team who's won the card
will be revealed.

2765
02:07:09,160 --> 02:07:12,930
Once won, you can use the card
during the following rounds' auctions.

2766
02:07:19,300 --> 02:07:20,530
- Hold on.
- It's a special card,

2767
02:07:20,530 --> 02:07:22,340
an item card exchange coupon.

2768
02:07:23,100 --> 02:07:24,570
- We must buy this.
- We must buy this.

2769
02:07:24,670 --> 02:07:26,440
We can use it to defend ourselves...

2770
02:07:26,440 --> 02:07:28,180
- or attack the opponents.
- We must buy this.

2771
02:07:28,180 --> 02:07:29,510
Without a doubt.

2772
02:07:30,040 --> 02:07:31,680
- We should buy this.
- We must.

2773
02:07:32,880 --> 02:07:33,950
We must buy it no matter what.

2774
02:07:34,880 --> 02:07:37,990
Hye Seon,
listen to what your ancestors say.

2775
02:07:39,350 --> 02:07:40,650
Please give her wisdom.

2776
02:07:41,620 --> 02:07:45,730
In case a special card came up,

2777
02:07:46,060 --> 02:07:49,030
we told Hye Seon how much to bid
for each type of card.

2778
02:07:49,300 --> 02:07:50,930
If it's an item, I can just bid...

2779
02:07:50,930 --> 02:07:52,500
based on what others bid.

2780
02:07:52,630 --> 02:07:55,270
If it's a really good card
like stealing an item, maximum 27?

2781
02:07:55,270 --> 02:07:56,400
I say 31 max.

2782
02:07:56,840 --> 02:07:59,840
I think we should bid very high
for cards like stealing items.

2783
02:08:00,140 --> 02:08:02,980
They could submit 25 and 5 together,
which makes it 30 in total.

2784
02:08:03,180 --> 02:08:05,580
Will they discuss this in such detail?

2785
02:08:05,710 --> 02:08:08,050
- They don't have the time.
- Even if they do,

2786
02:08:08,250 --> 02:08:11,590
will they spend up to 25 or 30?

2787
02:08:11,790 --> 02:08:15,360
If the card allows us to destroy or steal
other teams' items, bid a lot.

2788
02:08:15,390 --> 02:08:18,560
For the rest of the cards,
we could just forego them.

2789
02:08:18,560 --> 02:08:22,800
Bid the highest amount
you think is okay to spend.

2790
02:08:24,800 --> 02:08:26,570
We don't have any items,

2791
02:08:26,570 --> 02:08:28,870
so we must get this special card.

2792
02:08:30,170 --> 02:08:31,200
I was very flustered.

2793
02:08:31,270 --> 02:08:34,210
I was going to win the bid no matter what
as long as it wasn't a special card,

2794
02:08:34,270 --> 02:08:35,980
but it turned out to be one.

2795
02:08:36,380 --> 02:08:38,680
I had different strategies
for different price ranges too.

2796
02:08:38,750 --> 02:08:41,250
I didn't expect an exchange coupon.

2797
02:08:41,820 --> 02:08:43,250
It was completely beyond my calculation.

2798
02:08:43,350 --> 02:08:46,290
It's worth a lot more than an item.

2799
02:08:47,050 --> 02:08:49,660
The bidding for the special card
begins now.

2800
02:08:51,220 --> 02:08:52,860
Is it good to buy the special card?

2801
02:08:53,030 --> 02:08:54,960
- The team with the highest bid...
- I'm considering.

2802
02:08:55,200 --> 02:08:56,330
wins the card.

2803
02:08:57,230 --> 02:08:59,000
Your team shouldn't buy it.

2804
02:08:59,970 --> 02:09:01,070
- Right.
- It's meaningless.

2805
02:09:01,070 --> 02:09:04,500
Your team can only use it for defense.

2806
02:09:04,770 --> 02:09:07,240
You might have the chance
to win a good item card.

2807
02:09:07,240 --> 02:09:09,280
We can give it to you then.

2808
02:09:09,410 --> 02:09:12,110
This is worth bidding 35.
It's worth more than that.

2809
02:09:12,110 --> 02:09:13,710
It's worth more than 40.

2810
02:09:13,850 --> 02:09:15,650
He should be aware of it, right?

2811
02:09:15,650 --> 02:09:17,650
He needs to overinvest for this.

2812
02:09:18,090 --> 02:09:20,320
Please. This is such an important round.

2813
02:09:23,290 --> 02:09:24,290
Should I buy it?

2814
02:09:25,730 --> 02:09:26,760
I think...

2815
02:09:27,390 --> 02:09:29,100
- they heard us shout.
- Starting with Team Challenger,

2816
02:09:29,100 --> 02:09:31,200
- each team will enter the Voting Room.
- Others have heard us.

2817
02:09:31,200 --> 02:09:32,670
Submit your cube.

2818
02:09:32,670 --> 02:09:33,730
They could steal the Patek Philippe.

2819
02:09:33,730 --> 02:09:35,440
- You cannot move from your position.
- So it's best...

2820
02:09:35,900 --> 02:09:37,100
if we win it.

2821
02:09:37,900 --> 02:09:40,240
When the special card came up,

2822
02:09:40,240 --> 02:09:43,110
we needed a team to take the damage.

2823
02:09:43,110 --> 02:09:47,380
In return for helping Team P1 win,

2824
02:09:47,380 --> 02:09:48,850
they promised to take all the damage.

2825
02:09:48,850 --> 02:09:51,720
But we didn't discuss
how much we should spend...

2826
02:09:51,720 --> 02:09:53,450
for such a card,

2827
02:09:53,650 --> 02:09:55,260
so I was shaken up.

2828
02:09:57,520 --> 02:09:59,660
Isn't this a must-buy card?

2829
02:10:00,530 --> 02:10:02,630
I think we should buy it.

2830
02:10:03,260 --> 02:10:05,630
But I personally think...

2831
02:10:05,800 --> 02:10:07,370
it's best if you buy it.

2832
02:10:07,370 --> 02:10:08,500
I'll buy it, then.

2833
02:10:16,740 --> 02:10:17,740
(Approaching)

2834
02:10:19,480 --> 02:10:21,010
Don't move from your position.

2835
02:10:21,010 --> 02:10:22,680
Don't move. I'll just say this.

2836
02:10:23,220 --> 02:10:24,950
- Let's buy it no matter what.
- Okay.

2837
02:10:25,490 --> 02:10:26,550
Yes.

2838
02:10:32,560 --> 02:10:33,560
Don't drop them.

2839
02:10:33,560 --> 02:10:35,130
I think I will.

2840
02:10:36,560 --> 02:10:38,000
But when you come back from the room,

2841
02:10:38,000 --> 02:10:40,130
- we can see how many cubes you have left.
- That's true.

2842
02:10:41,400 --> 02:10:42,470
I might drop them.

2843
02:10:56,180 --> 02:11:00,090
Team Challenger,
please submit the cubes to bid.

2844
02:11:07,890 --> 02:11:10,900
I'm preparing now...

2845
02:11:11,730 --> 02:11:12,930
in case the alliance breaks up.

2846
02:11:13,200 --> 02:11:15,170
Ji Hoo must be aware of it too.

2847
02:11:15,300 --> 02:11:16,640
Ji Hoo will definitely buy it.

2848
02:11:16,640 --> 02:11:18,840
Ji Hoo will try to buy it no matter what.

2849
02:11:18,840 --> 02:11:19,840
Isn't that good?

2850
02:11:20,140 --> 02:11:21,270
It is.

2851
02:11:21,270 --> 02:11:23,140
- After he buys it,
- We can end the game with it.

2852
02:11:23,510 --> 02:11:25,580
we need to convince them...

2853
02:11:25,810 --> 02:11:27,750
that it was agreed upon.

2854
02:11:28,010 --> 02:11:30,680
We can convince them when they come back.
It's okay.

2855
02:11:30,780 --> 02:11:32,350
- We can't convince them.
- We can.

2856
02:11:32,350 --> 02:11:34,320
- We can't.
- If he buys it...

2857
02:11:34,320 --> 02:11:35,360
We can't.

2858
02:11:36,020 --> 02:11:39,390
If we win this, the chance of my team
coming in last decreases significantly.

2859
02:11:39,730 --> 02:11:43,860
Ji Hoo might go above and beyond
to win the card, even risking...

2860
02:11:43,860 --> 02:11:45,730
the whole alliance.

2861
02:11:46,230 --> 02:11:48,300
Because he would know its worth.

2862
02:11:48,700 --> 02:11:50,400
If that happens,

2863
02:11:50,770 --> 02:11:53,040
things could become ugly.

2864
02:11:53,340 --> 02:11:55,340
That's a possibility,

2865
02:11:55,580 --> 02:11:58,080
so they must consider it before they bid.

2866
02:11:59,350 --> 02:12:00,380
What will you do?

2867
02:12:01,280 --> 02:12:02,920
- Do you want it?
- I must buy it no matter what.

2868
02:12:03,120 --> 02:12:04,320
But there's nothing to exchange with.

2869
02:12:04,480 --> 02:12:06,950
But as long as you have this,
you can win just any item card...

2870
02:12:06,950 --> 02:12:09,690
and exchange it with
a more expensive item.

2871
02:12:10,860 --> 02:12:13,790
If you think about it as buying
a valuable item card...

2872
02:12:13,790 --> 02:12:16,160
with this bid plus a cheap item card,
it's not too bad.

2873
02:12:16,360 --> 02:12:18,100
I think you should buy it.

2874
02:12:19,030 --> 02:12:22,000
I'll buy it. Should I submit everything?

2875
02:12:23,270 --> 02:12:26,570
But there's a risk to doing that.

2876
02:12:27,310 --> 02:12:31,010
When all the cards are used up,

2877
02:12:31,010 --> 02:12:32,950
the game could end.

2878
02:12:33,310 --> 02:12:38,720
(Ji Hoo exits the room
after bidding for the special card.)

2879
02:12:38,850 --> 02:12:40,590
What? Did he submit five cubes?

2880
02:12:41,090 --> 02:12:44,190
(Before going in, he had 11 cubes.)

2881
02:12:44,690 --> 02:12:47,330
(He left the room with 6 cubes.)

2882
02:12:47,330 --> 02:12:49,060
What? Did he submit five cubes?

2883
02:12:57,270 --> 02:12:58,670
Team P1, please enter...

2884
02:12:58,670 --> 02:12:59,940
- the Voting Room.
- That's pretty harsh.

2885
02:13:02,880 --> 02:13:04,740
(Nodding)

2886
02:13:08,450 --> 02:13:11,850
You could submit two high-numbered cubes.

2887
02:13:18,560 --> 02:13:20,860
Which cubes did you submit?

2888
02:13:25,830 --> 02:13:28,230
I didn't know you were someone
who played so dirty.

2889
02:13:28,230 --> 02:13:29,270
- Me?
- Yes.

2890
02:13:29,270 --> 02:13:30,570
It's fine to talk, right?

2891
02:13:31,570 --> 02:13:33,770
The rule didn't say we couldn't talk.

2892
02:13:34,240 --> 02:13:35,240
Am I wrong?

2893
02:13:40,110 --> 02:13:42,220
I think...

2894
02:13:42,220 --> 02:13:43,420
This...

2895
02:13:43,420 --> 02:13:46,190
I need to fool them. I'm sorry,

2896
02:13:46,190 --> 02:13:48,490
but please understand
why I'm playing dirty.

2897
02:13:49,890 --> 02:13:52,030
I need to go all in.

2898
02:13:53,730 --> 02:13:55,900
This was a mind game,

2899
02:13:56,460 --> 02:13:58,570
and I needed a very smart move.

2900
02:13:59,200 --> 02:14:01,430
- Please head to the main hall.
- Yes.

2901
02:14:01,570 --> 02:14:02,700
Okay.

2902
02:14:07,740 --> 02:14:08,740
Oh, no.

2903
02:14:10,410 --> 02:14:11,910
I hope I don't drop it.

2904
02:14:13,010 --> 02:14:15,350
I wanted them to think
that I spent a lot of money.

2905
02:14:15,720 --> 02:14:17,550
If they see
that I don't have that many cubes,

2906
02:14:17,920 --> 02:14:19,550
they'll think, "How much did he spend?"

2907
02:14:19,790 --> 02:14:22,860
"We shouldn't spend that much.
Let's give up on this round."

2908
02:14:23,220 --> 02:14:26,830
I hid those cubes to make them think that.

2909
02:14:30,630 --> 02:14:36,540
(Ji Hoo takes out the cubes that he hid.)

2910
02:14:40,070 --> 02:14:41,240
Are you insane?

2911
02:14:43,480 --> 02:14:45,680
(Sang Min came out
with the cubes in his crotch.)

2912
02:14:56,620 --> 02:14:57,820
Did you spend all of them?

2913
02:14:58,730 --> 02:14:59,860
Yes, they asked us to.

2914
02:15:00,960 --> 02:15:02,860
- Why is your pocket bulging, then?
- What?

2915
02:15:04,430 --> 02:15:05,800
What's clattering in your pocket?

2916
02:15:09,900 --> 02:15:11,340
I was going to check your pockets.

2917
02:15:15,480 --> 02:15:16,480
All right.

2918
02:15:24,450 --> 02:15:25,690
Sorry. Darn it.

2919
02:15:27,550 --> 02:15:28,590
I'll take them out.

2920
02:15:30,660 --> 02:15:33,260
In all good conscience, I couldn't...

2921
02:15:38,200 --> 02:15:39,230
That's funny.

2922
02:15:40,570 --> 02:15:42,570
It was sealed bidding,

2923
02:15:42,670 --> 02:15:45,370
so they still needed to share
their information.

2924
02:15:45,670 --> 02:15:47,240
But they couldn't move around,

2925
02:15:47,240 --> 02:15:49,780
so they had to talk
while I could still hear them.

2926
02:15:50,380 --> 02:15:52,850
Did I spend too much from the beginning?

2927
02:15:53,310 --> 02:15:55,180
It was cheap if you felt good about it.

2928
02:15:55,450 --> 02:15:56,650
- What?
- If you felt good about it,

2929
02:15:56,650 --> 02:15:57,720
it was cheap.

2930
02:15:58,420 --> 02:15:59,590
Who's going last?

2931
02:16:01,920 --> 02:16:02,990
Bet everything.

2932
02:16:06,560 --> 02:16:07,560
Okay?

2933
02:16:11,060 --> 02:16:12,230
I have this many.

2934
02:16:14,030 --> 02:16:16,840
Also, this is a small amount.

2935
02:16:18,510 --> 02:16:19,640
Hye Seon, are you going for it?

2936
02:16:21,010 --> 02:16:22,040
Are you?

2937
02:16:24,080 --> 02:16:25,210
Still thinking?

2938
02:16:27,810 --> 02:16:30,080
I thought about how much
of what Sang Min was saying...

2939
02:16:30,320 --> 02:16:32,150
was true...

2940
02:16:32,150 --> 02:16:34,990
because he was speaking,
knowing that I was listening.

2941
02:16:41,060 --> 02:16:42,430
We're at a disadvantage...

2942
02:16:42,430 --> 02:16:44,800
if the other team has the exchange coupon.

2943
02:16:45,170 --> 02:16:47,770
But Teams P1, C, and R will bet...

2944
02:16:47,770 --> 02:16:49,470
as a team,

2945
02:16:49,470 --> 02:16:51,840
so they can share the price information.

2946
02:16:51,840 --> 02:16:55,880
So, Team P3 and I had no choice...

2947
02:16:55,880 --> 02:16:58,110
but to make them buy it at a higher price.

2948
02:17:01,080 --> 02:17:02,580
When you trade,

2949
02:17:02,580 --> 02:17:04,650
it's safe to say
that it's worth twice as much...

2950
02:17:04,650 --> 02:17:07,590
because I'm dropping my cheap blocks
and bringing expensive ones.

2951
02:17:07,950 --> 02:17:10,890
So, I realized I could make bolder bets.

2952
02:17:14,430 --> 02:17:17,530
I have 2. Just put down 2.

2953
02:17:17,660 --> 02:17:18,900
I play dirty...

2954
02:17:19,570 --> 02:17:21,230
- and nasty.
- Okay.

2955
02:17:21,630 --> 02:17:23,100
I'll be sneaky.

2956
02:17:25,240 --> 02:17:26,310
Dirty and nasty.

2957
02:17:29,710 --> 02:17:31,980
Let's check it out.

2958
02:17:31,980 --> 02:17:33,510
Oh, dear.

2959
02:17:34,010 --> 02:17:35,150
Goodness.

2960
02:17:36,880 --> 02:17:38,520
Look at your belly.

2961
02:17:39,720 --> 02:17:41,350
It's bulging out.

2962
02:17:41,990 --> 02:17:43,660
Take them all out. I did.

2963
02:17:43,720 --> 02:17:46,360
Hye Seon, this is all I have.

2964
02:17:49,930 --> 02:17:52,070
What's the point of hiding them?

2965
02:17:56,700 --> 02:18:02,710
(Team R goes last
in betting special cards.)

2966
02:18:04,910 --> 02:18:06,150
I'll make a bet.

2967
02:18:09,380 --> 02:18:12,050
You've submitted block number one.

2968
02:18:13,690 --> 02:18:16,760
We agreed to have Team P1 win it,

2969
02:18:16,890 --> 02:18:18,320
so the best option was...

2970
02:18:18,490 --> 02:18:21,760
to submit 1 or 2
without spending too many coins.

2971
02:18:22,100 --> 02:18:24,660
Ji Hoo and I were
going to get rid of low numbers.

2972
02:18:24,830 --> 02:18:25,900
We'll let Sang Min handle it...

2973
02:18:25,900 --> 02:18:28,070
and get rid of 1, 2 and 3.

2974
02:18:28,530 --> 02:18:29,940
And we thought...

2975
02:18:30,070 --> 02:18:32,710
we could guarantee a win
if Sang Min combined...

2976
02:18:32,710 --> 02:18:34,710
two numbers.

2977
02:18:35,070 --> 02:18:36,780
I think you should combine...

2978
02:18:37,010 --> 02:18:38,650
two high numbers.

2979
02:18:40,250 --> 02:18:41,410
Number 25...

2980
02:18:42,020 --> 02:18:44,020
Fine. And number 15.

2981
02:18:44,180 --> 02:18:47,590
You've submitted cards 15 and 25.

2982
02:18:47,920 --> 02:18:49,160
(He bet 40 with 2 high numbers,)

2983
02:18:49,160 --> 02:18:50,520
(following Seung Yong's plan.)

2984
02:18:50,690 --> 02:18:53,330
I'll announce the result
of the special card bid.

2985
02:18:59,470 --> 02:19:01,170
Round Four has ended.

2986
02:19:02,570 --> 02:19:03,740
This is the most nerve-racking moment.

2987
02:19:04,900 --> 02:19:06,040
I'm worried they might not have bought it.

2988
02:19:07,670 --> 02:19:08,740
Did you buy it?

2989
02:19:09,240 --> 02:19:10,640
- It's game over.
- First,

2990
02:19:10,780 --> 02:19:12,080
we have to get him out.

2991
02:19:12,450 --> 02:19:13,480
It's game over.

2992
02:19:13,480 --> 02:19:15,050
- You bought it?
- With 25...

2993
02:19:15,050 --> 02:19:16,150
Shush.

2994
02:19:16,220 --> 02:19:18,250
- Number 25?
- Who did?

2995
02:19:18,280 --> 02:19:20,650
- I did.
- Sang Min!

2996
02:19:21,020 --> 02:19:23,420
- I did.
- Sang Min.

2997
02:19:24,620 --> 02:19:27,730
Our strategy was to buy all the offers...

2998
02:19:27,890 --> 02:19:31,230
so that Teams P2 and P3 ended up
with nothing.

2999
02:19:31,330 --> 02:19:33,230
If they got it,

3000
02:19:33,630 --> 02:19:36,800
Team P1 would be losing
their Patek Philippe.

3001
02:19:38,300 --> 02:19:41,840
Team C has submitted cube number one.

3002
02:19:43,080 --> 02:19:44,840
That would have shaken up
the entire alliance,

3003
02:19:44,840 --> 02:19:46,750
so I didn't take it away.

3004
02:19:47,110 --> 02:19:48,880
Team P1 is the strongest right now.

3005
02:19:49,250 --> 02:19:50,420
How many did you bet?

3006
02:19:50,420 --> 02:19:52,250
I just bet one. I gave up.

3007
02:19:52,250 --> 02:19:53,590
- Which one?
- Number one.

3008
02:19:55,790 --> 02:19:58,260
Team P2 has submitted cube number 1.

3009
02:19:58,830 --> 02:20:02,560
I had a feeling that Team P1 bought it
at a high price.

3010
02:20:02,560 --> 02:20:04,200
And it wasn't a card
that I desperately needed.

3011
02:20:04,330 --> 02:20:06,130
I don't want to spend too much
on a special card either.

3012
02:20:06,470 --> 02:20:09,800
But one team made a bid
at a pretty high price,

3013
02:20:10,100 --> 02:20:12,210
so I had no reason to spend money on that.

3014
02:20:14,540 --> 02:20:15,540
I folded.

3015
02:20:15,910 --> 02:20:17,110
- Okay.
- With number one.

3016
02:20:17,110 --> 02:20:18,140
- Number 1
- Number 1?

3017
02:20:18,140 --> 02:20:19,310
- Yes.
- Who got it?

3018
02:20:19,310 --> 02:20:20,350
Team P1.

3019
02:20:23,820 --> 02:20:25,520
(Team P3 submitted 1.)

3020
02:20:25,520 --> 02:20:29,520
Team P3 has submitted cube number 1.

3021
02:20:30,320 --> 02:20:33,190
I thought they spent a lot of cubes.

3022
02:20:33,530 --> 02:20:36,630
So, there was a chance that I might lose,

3023
02:20:36,630 --> 02:20:39,000
even with number 33.

3024
02:20:39,170 --> 02:20:42,800
I'd rather give up on it,

3025
02:20:42,800 --> 02:20:44,570
so I submitted number one,
the lowest number.

3026
02:20:44,940 --> 02:20:47,940
It's an amazing card
to be able to take one away from them,

3027
02:20:48,170 --> 02:20:50,580
but we also need an exchange coupon.

3028
02:20:50,840 --> 02:20:52,510
Funnily enough,

3029
02:20:52,780 --> 02:20:55,950
this card became a white elephant for us.

3030
02:20:56,220 --> 02:20:59,320
But when we heard that Team P1 won it,

3031
02:21:00,750 --> 02:21:02,720
we thought that they really didn't save
their cubes.

3032
02:21:02,990 --> 02:21:04,560
Sang Min!

3033
02:21:04,820 --> 02:21:06,390
- I did.
- Sang Min.

3034
02:21:06,690 --> 02:21:09,830
It was the best insurance we could have.

3035
02:21:10,000 --> 02:21:12,170
It was especially good
if Team P1 had bought it.

3036
02:21:12,570 --> 02:21:14,930
Why? Because we had the lowest number.

3037
02:21:15,270 --> 02:21:17,440
Even if the other team wins
an expensive item,

3038
02:21:17,870 --> 02:21:20,370
we can exchange it
with the 490,000-dollar card,

3039
02:21:20,570 --> 02:21:22,480
which is lower than 650,000,

3040
02:21:22,480 --> 02:21:24,280
to ensure the survival of Team C.

3041
02:21:24,380 --> 02:21:26,180
It didn't matter whether it was 35 or 40.

3042
02:21:26,250 --> 02:21:29,480
We needed that card, even if it meant
spending number 60.

3043
02:21:29,820 --> 02:21:31,380
Sang Min has done it this time.

3044
02:21:32,190 --> 02:21:34,020
(Lots Secured by Each Team)

3045
02:21:34,020 --> 02:21:36,960
(Exchange coupon)

3046
02:21:37,190 --> 02:21:39,360
At this point,

3047
02:21:39,690 --> 02:21:42,460
unless there's an incredibly good lot,

3048
02:21:42,460 --> 02:21:45,030
it doesn't mean much for us to go first.

3049
02:21:45,030 --> 02:21:47,130
It's gotten harder to attack them
from both sides.

3050
02:21:47,870 --> 02:21:50,370
(Team P3 visited the alliance.)

3051
02:21:50,370 --> 02:21:51,870
Congrats on winning it all.

3052
02:21:52,170 --> 02:21:53,570
- Thank you.
- Hey.

3053
02:21:53,570 --> 02:21:54,710
I thought he was on our team.

3054
02:21:54,810 --> 02:21:58,310
Hye Seon, I honestly told you everything.

3055
02:21:59,480 --> 02:22:01,250
Has this become the main hall?

3056
02:22:02,280 --> 02:22:04,450
How many are you trying to win?

3057
02:22:04,950 --> 02:22:07,550
You even won the special card.

3058
02:22:08,190 --> 02:22:10,060
But we needed this one.

3059
02:22:10,890 --> 02:22:12,430
But you already won two lots.

3060
02:22:12,430 --> 02:22:13,430
- Us?
- Yes.

3061
02:22:13,430 --> 02:22:16,900
But we don't know
what the other team will get.

3062
02:22:17,330 --> 02:22:19,170
It's safer to secure it now.

3063
02:22:19,900 --> 02:22:22,500
- But...
- You're off to a strong start.

3064
02:22:22,500 --> 02:22:26,010
But the value of the hidden cards
must be determined...

3065
02:22:26,110 --> 02:22:27,570
- by the people downstairs.
- Right.

3066
02:22:27,570 --> 02:22:28,910
- That's true.
- Yes.

3067
02:22:29,640 --> 02:22:31,210
We didn't know
what would be up for auction.

3068
02:22:32,480 --> 02:22:33,550
Right.

3069
02:22:34,780 --> 02:22:36,420
No one will talk to us.

3070
02:22:37,780 --> 02:22:39,690
It didn't feel so good to be marginalized.

3071
02:22:40,650 --> 02:22:43,160
Aren't you working with Team P2?

3072
02:22:43,160 --> 02:22:45,260
- No.
- No one's working with us.

3073
02:22:45,260 --> 02:22:46,630
If I'm being honest,

3074
02:22:46,630 --> 02:22:48,860
I believed that you and Team P2...

3075
02:22:48,860 --> 02:22:50,430
were tight.

3076
02:22:50,500 --> 02:22:51,500
No.

3077
02:22:51,560 --> 02:22:53,800
Team P2 bought... What was it called?
Median value?

3078
02:22:53,970 --> 02:22:55,170
They bought that.

3079
02:22:55,300 --> 02:22:57,240
They should have told us
if we were working together.

3080
02:22:57,240 --> 02:22:58,670
- But they didn't. Yes.
- Really?

3081
02:22:59,110 --> 02:23:01,240
Then, Jin Hyeong cut in line.

3082
02:23:01,240 --> 02:23:02,610
- Jin Hyeong...
- Exactly.

3083
02:23:02,940 --> 02:23:05,010
Seung Yong even shed blood.

3084
02:23:05,180 --> 02:23:06,380
- Why?
- He bled.

3085
02:23:06,380 --> 02:23:07,580
- He got into another fight.
- Seriously?

3086
02:23:07,580 --> 02:23:08,580
- He ran into him.
- Just now?

3087
02:23:08,580 --> 02:23:09,580
Just now.

3088
02:23:09,580 --> 02:23:10,720
Jin Hyeong did this...

3089
02:23:10,720 --> 02:23:12,150
to his hand.

3090
02:23:12,150 --> 02:23:13,820
- Look.
- I'm fine.

3091
02:23:13,820 --> 02:23:16,160
All five teams could buy the hidden items,

3092
02:23:16,160 --> 02:23:17,560
but he ran before even listening.

3093
02:23:17,720 --> 02:23:19,760
How successful does Jin Hyeong want to be?

3094
02:23:20,430 --> 02:23:22,230
(Right after Round 4)

3095
02:23:22,900 --> 02:23:24,360
- The hidden items will be up for auction.
- Okay.

3096
02:23:24,360 --> 02:23:25,430
You have to run immediately.

3097
02:23:25,430 --> 02:23:26,570
But we're broke.

3098
02:23:26,900 --> 02:23:28,100
Still, we need to run.

3099
02:23:28,870 --> 02:23:30,440
After a special card bidding,

3100
02:23:30,440 --> 02:23:33,470
the hidden items are available
during the strategy meeting.

3101
02:23:33,570 --> 02:23:35,540
So, I believed that our alliance...

3102
02:23:35,710 --> 02:23:37,180
should win it.

3103
02:23:37,410 --> 02:23:40,250
We ran to the Voting Room
right after the round ended.

3104
02:23:41,380 --> 02:23:42,580
Is the round over?

3105
02:23:43,480 --> 02:23:44,580
Can we go?

3106
02:23:45,020 --> 02:23:46,650
Round Four has ended.

3107
02:23:47,050 --> 02:23:48,390
Why are they running?

3108
02:23:48,390 --> 02:23:49,460
(Seung Yong, Ji Hoo,
and Jin Hyeong ran...)

3109
02:23:49,460 --> 02:23:50,690
(before the hidden item was revealed.)

3110
02:23:54,090 --> 02:23:56,800
- Please wait.
- Okay.

3111
02:23:56,800 --> 02:23:58,360
- You're not hurt, are you?
- Buddy, you hurt me.

3112
02:23:58,360 --> 02:23:59,830
- Again?
- Gosh.

3113
02:23:59,830 --> 02:24:01,530
- What's the matter with you?
- I apologize.

3114
02:24:01,970 --> 02:24:04,840
It was such a mess,
so I don't exactly remember.

3115
02:24:04,940 --> 02:24:06,640
But I remember one thing.
I feel so bad for this.

3116
02:24:06,640 --> 02:24:09,510
He ran into the door...

3117
02:24:09,680 --> 02:24:11,110
and got a scratch.

3118
02:24:12,140 --> 02:24:13,210
I feel terrible for that.

3119
02:24:13,210 --> 02:24:16,050
I was struggling next to him,

3120
02:24:16,150 --> 02:24:18,680
and they announced it.
"There will be five hidden items."

3121
02:24:19,050 --> 02:24:21,250
The hidden item in the Blind Auction is...

3122
02:24:22,020 --> 02:24:25,020
the item card value check coupon.

3123
02:24:26,260 --> 02:24:28,960
Five coupons are available.

3124
02:24:30,200 --> 02:24:31,230
Gosh.

3125
02:24:31,930 --> 02:24:33,670
- I'm sorry.
- That's okay.

3126
02:24:33,670 --> 02:24:34,670
What happened?

3127
02:24:34,970 --> 02:24:36,040
It was embarrassing.

3128
02:24:36,240 --> 02:24:37,540
I thought it was limited,

3129
02:24:37,840 --> 02:24:39,140
and everyone could buy it.

3130
02:24:39,140 --> 02:24:42,880
And it wasn't even a coupon
that I needed at the moment.

3131
02:24:42,880 --> 02:24:44,310
I could buy it later,

3132
02:24:44,680 --> 02:24:46,480
so I just came back.

3133
02:24:46,810 --> 02:24:48,280
Jin Hyeong hasn't changed.

3134
02:24:49,320 --> 02:24:50,520
(Sighing)

3135
02:24:50,520 --> 02:24:51,920
That was supposed to be ours.

3136
02:24:51,920 --> 02:24:52,920
Right.

3137
02:24:53,090 --> 02:24:55,620
This season proceeds as teams,

3138
02:24:55,620 --> 02:24:58,160
so an individual's action...

3139
02:24:58,520 --> 02:25:01,390
affects the whole team.

3140
02:25:01,460 --> 02:25:03,430
Those unnecessary actions by Jin Hyeong...

3141
02:25:03,430 --> 02:25:08,570
caused Team P2 to be alienated.

3142
02:25:08,570 --> 02:25:09,570
That's my opinion.

3143
02:25:09,570 --> 02:25:10,570
Did you buy any items?

3144
02:25:10,570 --> 02:25:12,100
There were five, so I didn't.

3145
02:25:12,100 --> 02:25:14,310
- They...
- Yes.

3146
02:25:14,370 --> 02:25:16,940
Isn't Team C in the worst situation
in the alliance?

3147
02:25:17,010 --> 02:25:19,750
But Team R didn't win anything either.

3148
02:25:19,750 --> 02:25:21,010
I don't think...

3149
02:25:21,110 --> 02:25:23,080
we'll be able to beat Team P1.

3150
02:25:23,080 --> 02:25:25,380
And Team P3 is
in the same situation as us.

3151
02:25:25,480 --> 02:25:28,990
I think we should start bidding
more aggressively.

3152
02:25:29,020 --> 02:25:31,290
We should start buying.

3153
02:25:31,320 --> 02:25:33,430
It's Round Four,
and they offered another special card.

3154
02:25:33,430 --> 02:25:35,060
- We should start buying now.
- Yes.

3155
02:25:35,130 --> 02:25:36,530
- We have to make bold bids.
- Yes.

3156
02:25:36,660 --> 02:25:38,730
Everything is going
according to Team P1's plan.

3157
02:25:40,430 --> 02:25:43,500
Players for Round Five,
please gather in the main hall.

3158
02:25:44,000 --> 02:25:46,940
(Tae Gyun, YunB, Seong Beom,
Sung Joo, and Nam Hee)

3159
02:25:49,140 --> 02:25:50,310
We run into each other a lot.

3160
02:25:50,340 --> 02:25:51,440
This is good.

3161
02:25:51,580 --> 02:25:52,950
We have three members, so...

3162
02:25:52,950 --> 02:25:54,910
Yes. We're assigned...

3163
02:25:54,910 --> 02:25:56,880
- to the same rounds.
- You guys are busy.

3164
02:25:56,950 --> 02:25:58,950
You have to come downstairs more.

3165
02:25:59,220 --> 02:26:00,290
It's good.

3166
02:26:00,920 --> 02:26:03,820
Round Five's bidding will begin now.

3167
02:26:04,060 --> 02:26:06,430
Team P1, please pick your lot.

3168
02:26:09,500 --> 02:26:10,860
Number 27.

3169
02:26:10,860 --> 02:26:13,430
You've selected lot number 27.

3170
02:26:15,940 --> 02:26:17,400
Item card.

3171
02:26:17,540 --> 02:26:20,870
Kobe Bryant's NBA debut match jersey.

3172
02:26:21,340 --> 02:26:24,510
It was auctioned at Sotheby's in 2025.

3173
02:26:25,010 --> 02:26:27,580
This is the game-worn jersey...

3174
02:26:27,580 --> 02:26:31,080
from Kobe Bryant's 1996 LA Lakers debut.

3175
02:26:31,920 --> 02:26:34,420
Kobe Bryant has been a star
since high school.

3176
02:26:34,420 --> 02:26:36,120
He's a basketball player, right?

3177
02:26:36,120 --> 02:26:37,820
Is it worth more than 650,000?

3178
02:26:37,890 --> 02:26:39,090
It is.

3179
02:26:39,560 --> 02:26:41,160
I don't think so.

3180
02:26:41,390 --> 02:26:44,030
One thing I know for sure is
a pair of his shoes...

3181
02:26:44,030 --> 02:26:45,500
was sold at 400,000 to 500,000 dollars.

3182
02:26:45,500 --> 02:26:47,170
Tell me exactly what it is.

3183
02:26:47,170 --> 02:26:50,440
It was the jersey that he wore
during his debut game.

3184
02:26:50,540 --> 02:26:53,240
- And?
- It was auctioned at Sotheby's in 2025.

3185
02:26:53,240 --> 02:26:54,740
It was auctioned after his death.

3186
02:26:54,870 --> 02:26:57,540
So, we have to determine
if it's over or under 600,000.

3187
02:26:57,540 --> 02:26:58,880
Are you insane?
That's ten million dollars.

3188
02:26:58,980 --> 02:27:00,080
There's no way.

3189
02:27:00,450 --> 02:27:01,550
There's no way.

3190
02:27:01,880 --> 02:27:03,550
- It's ten million dollars?
- I doubt it.

3191
02:27:03,550 --> 02:27:04,580
It might.

3192
02:27:04,580 --> 02:27:07,250
The market size of the US is
incredibly large.

3193
02:27:07,250 --> 02:27:08,990
Yes, and Kobe is...

3194
02:27:08,990 --> 02:27:11,220
- considered a supreme being in LA.
- That's true.

3195
02:27:11,490 --> 02:27:13,160
(Xitsuh gasping)

3196
02:27:13,160 --> 02:27:15,030
- What?
- It was at Sotheby's?

3197
02:27:15,030 --> 02:27:16,660
- What's Showdub?
- Sotheby's.

3198
02:27:16,660 --> 02:27:18,200
It's the largest auction.

3199
02:27:18,430 --> 02:27:20,100
And it was in 2025?

3200
02:27:20,200 --> 02:27:22,330
If what Seung Jin said is true,

3201
02:27:22,330 --> 02:27:23,500
it's worth over ten million dollars.

3202
02:27:23,500 --> 02:27:24,740
- Really?
- Yes.

3203
02:27:24,940 --> 02:27:27,910
Seung Jin told me about this item.

3204
02:27:27,910 --> 02:27:29,410
Seung Jin precisely said,

3205
02:27:29,410 --> 02:27:31,940
"One of Kobe Bryant's jerseys was sold..."

3206
02:27:32,080 --> 02:27:33,310
"at more than ten million dollars."

3207
02:27:33,410 --> 02:27:36,320
Shoes and jerseys
worn by Michael Jordan and Kobe Bryant...

3208
02:27:36,320 --> 02:27:38,580
are worth like ten million dollars.

3209
02:27:40,420 --> 02:27:42,090
Plus, Kobe Bryant...

3210
02:27:42,720 --> 02:27:43,760
passed away.

3211
02:27:43,760 --> 02:27:44,960
- It's a well-known fact.
- Yes.

3212
02:27:44,960 --> 02:27:47,560
And he wore it at his debut game.
That means a lot.

3213
02:27:47,560 --> 02:27:49,530
- So, it's higher than 10 million, right?
- It's higher than 10 million.

3214
02:27:50,230 --> 02:27:51,560
Buy it, YunB.

3215
02:27:51,900 --> 02:27:53,030
You have to.

3216
02:27:53,630 --> 02:27:55,700
I knew it was definitely over ten million.

3217
02:27:55,700 --> 02:27:59,040
There are various types of merch
for a professional athlete.

3218
02:27:59,040 --> 02:28:02,780
One of the most valuable ones is...

3219
02:28:02,780 --> 02:28:06,250
the jersey they wore
during their debut game.

3220
02:28:06,350 --> 02:28:09,250
After Kobe Bryant passed away
a few years back,

3221
02:28:09,250 --> 02:28:11,020
all of his items...

3222
02:28:11,020 --> 02:28:12,950
worth more now.

3223
02:28:13,050 --> 02:28:15,020
(Kobe Bryant's NBA debut match jersey)

3224
02:28:15,020 --> 02:28:17,960
(10.15 million dollars)

3225
02:28:17,960 --> 02:28:20,230
I thought there was a chance...

3226
02:28:20,230 --> 02:28:23,560
that the other teams wouldn't expect it
to be worth so much.

3227
02:28:23,560 --> 02:28:27,270
I thought we might win it
at a lower price.

3228
02:28:27,300 --> 02:28:29,740
I just don't understand...

3229
02:28:29,770 --> 02:28:31,900
A jersey is worth ten million dollars?

3230
02:28:32,270 --> 02:28:34,010
That's why it could be over ten million.

3231
02:28:34,010 --> 02:28:35,270
"Ten million dollars for a jersey?"

3232
02:28:35,270 --> 02:28:37,340
"Ta-da, it's 20 million."

3233
02:28:37,340 --> 02:28:39,710
We ended up talking about ten million.

3234
02:28:39,780 --> 02:28:40,780
How much would you pay?

3235
02:28:40,780 --> 02:28:42,210
I couldn't pay ten million.

3236
02:28:42,310 --> 02:28:44,280
I can't pay ten million dollars
for a tank top.

3237
02:28:44,880 --> 02:28:47,250
I can't pay ten million dollars
for a yellow tank top.

3238
02:28:47,250 --> 02:28:49,190
I also think ten million is too much.

3239
02:28:49,190 --> 02:28:51,760
I'd pay two million dollars at best.

3240
02:28:51,760 --> 02:28:54,390
I think a million is enough.

3241
02:28:54,390 --> 02:28:56,360
Is Seung Jin playing in this round?

3242
02:28:56,400 --> 02:28:58,030
- No, YunB.
- YunB?

3243
02:28:58,030 --> 02:29:01,070
And YunB is wearing a tank top.

3244
02:29:02,530 --> 02:29:03,700
I have to buy it.

3245
02:29:03,700 --> 02:29:07,210
And I lived in the US for a long time.

3246
02:29:07,210 --> 02:29:10,580
I know that
it's at least ten million dollars.

3247
02:29:11,410 --> 02:29:13,710
The bidding will begin now.

3248
02:29:14,880 --> 02:29:16,650
Team P1, please submit the cubes...

3249
02:29:16,650 --> 02:29:18,650
if you wish to make a bid.

3250
02:29:23,960 --> 02:29:28,230
Team R hasn't won any lots,

3251
02:29:28,230 --> 02:29:29,660
so I wanted Team R...

3252
02:29:29,660 --> 02:29:32,900
to secure one in this round.

3253
02:29:34,970 --> 02:29:38,940
Team P1 has submitted
cube numbers 5 and 3.

3254
02:29:39,570 --> 02:29:41,110
The total is eight.

3255
02:29:41,110 --> 02:29:42,640
I love the Lakers.

3256
02:29:52,580 --> 02:29:55,750
Team P2 has submitted
cube numbers 5 and 4.

3257
02:29:56,190 --> 02:29:59,390
I played it safe.

3258
02:29:59,390 --> 02:30:01,460
I only increased it by one.

3259
02:30:02,330 --> 02:30:03,760
Ten.

3260
02:30:05,560 --> 02:30:07,500
Team P3, please submit the cubes...

3261
02:30:07,500 --> 02:30:09,470
if you would like to place a bid.

3262
02:30:10,640 --> 02:30:11,770
It looked expensive.

3263
02:30:11,770 --> 02:30:15,980
In countries like the US,
sports hold immense value.

3264
02:30:16,140 --> 02:30:19,180
I knew it was easily over ten million.

3265
02:30:26,850 --> 02:30:29,860
Team P3 has submitted cube number 15.

3266
02:30:35,460 --> 02:30:37,530
Bidding and betting are pretty similar.

3267
02:30:37,530 --> 02:30:38,960
If you make small, incremental raises
in an auction,

3268
02:30:38,960 --> 02:30:40,400
it makes your opponent
want to keep calling.

3269
02:30:40,400 --> 02:30:43,240
And we were using number cubes
to place bids.

3270
02:30:43,400 --> 02:30:46,270
If I submit small numbers to keep calling,

3271
02:30:46,440 --> 02:30:48,970
such as 2 or 3,

3272
02:30:48,970 --> 02:30:50,280
I'll be left with number ten.

3273
02:30:50,310 --> 02:30:52,680
That would affect my gameplay,

3274
02:30:52,680 --> 02:30:55,250
so I thought it was better
to use big numbers first.

3275
02:30:55,280 --> 02:30:57,480
So, my strategy was
to submit number 15 from the get-go.

3276
02:30:58,650 --> 02:31:02,090
Team R, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3277
02:31:07,560 --> 02:31:10,300
I was determined to win this one.

3278
02:31:10,300 --> 02:31:13,230
I knew it was worth
more than what I was feeling.

3279
02:31:15,000 --> 02:31:18,500
Team C has submitted
cube numbers 10 and 6.

3280
02:31:18,900 --> 02:31:22,540
Team C, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3281
02:31:25,140 --> 02:31:28,410
(Shaking his head)

3282
02:31:30,050 --> 02:31:31,420
I'll pass.

3283
02:31:31,650 --> 02:31:33,850
Team C has passed on this bid.

3284
02:31:39,160 --> 02:31:40,560
Is it 16 right now?

3285
02:31:44,300 --> 02:31:45,630
Pass.

3286
02:31:45,630 --> 02:31:47,670
Team P1 has passed on this bid.

3287
02:31:47,670 --> 02:31:48,730
(Team P1 opts out.)

3288
02:31:49,670 --> 02:31:52,770
Team P2, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3289
02:32:05,850 --> 02:32:09,220
Team P2 has added cube number 10.

3290
02:32:09,820 --> 02:32:11,560
The total is 19.

3291
02:32:13,190 --> 02:32:15,290
"Oh, he's calling."

3292
02:32:15,290 --> 02:32:18,360
"He knows this item is valuable."

3293
02:32:18,460 --> 02:32:20,400
But I thought he'd call again...

3294
02:32:20,400 --> 02:32:23,270
if I made a small raise.

3295
02:32:25,640 --> 02:32:29,110
Team P3, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3296
02:32:30,080 --> 02:32:32,310
You've submitted cube number ten.

3297
02:32:32,310 --> 02:32:34,180
The total is 25.

3298
02:32:36,050 --> 02:32:39,320
Team R, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3299
02:32:39,450 --> 02:32:40,650
Twelve?

3300
02:32:41,790 --> 02:32:43,390
Twelve.

3301
02:32:46,960 --> 02:32:48,230
(Team R raises 12.)

3302
02:32:48,230 --> 02:32:51,360
Team R has added cube number 12.

3303
02:32:51,430 --> 02:32:53,170
The total is 28.

3304
02:32:53,170 --> 02:32:54,730
(Team R bid 28 in total.)

3305
02:32:55,470 --> 02:32:58,070
I didn't think they'd call.

3306
02:32:58,170 --> 02:33:01,370
Because we agreed to spend 10
for 10 million.

3307
02:33:01,370 --> 02:33:04,680
That means it's worth
more than 20 million dollars.

3308
02:33:05,280 --> 02:33:06,510
I thought it was overinvestment.

3309
02:33:06,910 --> 02:33:08,180
But...

3310
02:33:08,180 --> 02:33:09,780
we haven't secured anything yet,

3311
02:33:09,780 --> 02:33:12,320
so I wanted to win something.

3312
02:33:12,420 --> 02:33:14,990
I assumed that we had to...

3313
02:33:15,390 --> 02:33:16,790
secure this one.

3314
02:33:17,560 --> 02:33:20,730
Team P2, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3315
02:33:20,730 --> 02:33:23,960
Team P3, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3316
02:33:24,460 --> 02:33:26,300
(Kobe Bryant's NBA debut match jersey)

3317
02:33:34,570 --> 02:33:36,740
Round Five has ended.

3318
02:33:37,080 --> 02:33:39,710
Seong Beom, what news will you bring us?

3319
02:33:40,180 --> 02:33:42,180
Now, it feels like it was cheap...

3320
02:33:42,180 --> 02:33:43,920
when Team P1 took it for 18.

3321
02:33:43,950 --> 02:33:46,320
Yes, it's starting to feel that way.

3322
02:33:46,390 --> 02:33:48,350
It's just mental pressure.

3323
02:33:48,350 --> 02:33:49,590
It is.

3324
02:33:50,720 --> 02:33:52,190
- Hi.
- Hi.

3325
02:33:52,190 --> 02:33:53,260
Tell us.

3326
02:33:53,260 --> 02:33:54,430
Did Team P2 win it?

3327
02:33:54,830 --> 02:33:55,990
No.

3328
02:33:56,260 --> 02:33:57,330
Team R did.

3329
02:33:57,700 --> 02:33:59,570
- Team R? Really?
- They must have spent a lot.

3330
02:33:59,570 --> 02:34:01,270
I considered calling, but I folded.

3331
02:34:01,670 --> 02:34:04,800
Team P2, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

3332
02:34:04,800 --> 02:34:06,870
(They would have to bid more than 28,
Team R's total.)

3333
02:34:08,910 --> 02:34:10,140
I'll pass.

3334
02:34:10,440 --> 02:34:12,580
Team P2 has passed on this bid.

3335
02:34:14,080 --> 02:34:17,920
We missed the exchange coupon
in the previous round.

3336
02:34:18,120 --> 02:34:21,850
Bidding more than 28 for this...

3337
02:34:21,950 --> 02:34:23,190
sounded like too much.

3338
02:34:23,190 --> 02:34:27,790
Until we see a lot
that's worth tens of millions of dollars,

3339
02:34:27,790 --> 02:34:30,330
I thought it was wise to take a step back.

3340
02:34:31,730 --> 02:34:33,900
I wanted to win something,

3341
02:34:33,900 --> 02:34:35,900
so I really wanted this item.

3342
02:34:37,140 --> 02:34:40,540
I would be bidding 30 if I made a raise.

3343
02:34:41,340 --> 02:34:43,380
Then, it would affect the team members...

3344
02:34:43,380 --> 02:34:47,280
that will play next to me,
even if I won it.

3345
02:34:48,180 --> 02:34:49,450
I'll pass.

3346
02:34:49,550 --> 02:34:51,980
So, I thought rationally
and decided to stop there.

3347
02:34:51,980 --> 02:34:53,420
And I don't think...

3348
02:34:53,420 --> 02:34:56,890
it will be that expensive.

3349
02:34:57,490 --> 02:35:00,330
Team R has won the item card.

3350
02:35:00,330 --> 02:35:02,660
(Team R wins the bid.)

3351
02:35:02,660 --> 02:35:04,160
It was a little over ten million
in real life,

3352
02:35:04,160 --> 02:35:05,960
but I expected it to be around 15 million.

3353
02:35:05,960 --> 02:35:07,770
It was still over ten million,

3354
02:35:07,870 --> 02:35:09,030
so it went well.

3355
02:35:12,370 --> 02:35:13,510
(Kobe Bryant's NBA debut match jersey)

3356
02:35:13,510 --> 02:35:14,840
Kobe, is this the best you can do?

3357
02:35:15,270 --> 02:35:16,680
No, it must be pretty expensive.

3358
02:35:17,640 --> 02:35:18,810
He passed away.

3359
02:35:19,580 --> 02:35:24,680
(Kobe Bryant's NBA debut match jersey,
10.15 million dollars)

3360
02:35:24,720 --> 02:35:26,350
- It's 10 million?
- It's 10 million.

3361
02:35:27,120 --> 02:35:28,820
You got it exactly right.

3362
02:35:28,820 --> 02:35:30,060
Who won it?

3363
02:35:30,060 --> 02:35:32,760
- It was exactly ten million dollars.
- See?

3364
02:35:32,760 --> 02:35:34,330
- I knew it.
- We...

3365
02:35:34,330 --> 02:35:36,460
have to listen to Sang Min in this game.

3366
02:35:37,160 --> 02:35:39,530
You ought to listen.

3367
02:35:41,500 --> 02:35:44,000
I thought, "The US is an awesome country."

3368
02:35:44,000 --> 02:35:46,570
"They pay ten million dollars
for a tank top."

3369
02:35:47,270 --> 02:35:50,380
And I was so impressed by Sang Min.

3370
02:35:50,680 --> 02:35:53,050
How did he guess it so precisely?

3371
02:35:53,550 --> 02:35:54,810
I think I got it at a low price.

3372
02:35:54,810 --> 02:35:55,980
We did.

3373
02:35:55,980 --> 02:35:57,180
Why did they fold?

3374
02:35:57,180 --> 02:35:58,820
Why aren't they buying anything?

3375
02:35:59,020 --> 02:36:00,490
They must be trying to go all in.

3376
02:36:00,790 --> 02:36:02,820
- Good work.
- What?

3377
02:36:02,820 --> 02:36:04,160
How did it go?

3378
02:36:04,160 --> 02:36:06,060
I opted out.

3379
02:36:06,060 --> 02:36:07,290
Why?

3380
02:36:08,030 --> 02:36:10,330
Sung Joo's team got it.

3381
02:36:10,460 --> 02:36:12,760
What did Sung Joo's team write?

3382
02:36:12,860 --> 02:36:15,070
Let's write it down.
Sung Joo, Team Rookie.

3383
02:36:15,230 --> 02:36:16,230
- What?
- What?

3384
02:36:16,230 --> 02:36:17,270
It was very disappointing.

3385
02:36:17,270 --> 02:36:19,870
It wasn't a card
that we couldn't predict the price of.

3386
02:36:20,070 --> 02:36:23,440
Seung Jin and I already predicted
an estimate of the price.

3387
02:36:23,680 --> 02:36:26,410
We would've taken advantage
if we had won it,

3388
02:36:26,710 --> 02:36:29,250
but what's done is done.
There's nothing that can be done.

3389
02:36:29,250 --> 02:36:31,780
One positive is that we saved money.

3390
02:36:31,780 --> 02:36:33,650
"From the next round,"

3391
02:36:33,650 --> 02:36:35,820
"let's win a good item card
when we get the chance to."

3392
02:36:35,820 --> 02:36:36,890
"No matter what."

3393
02:36:36,890 --> 02:36:37,990
"Please."

3394
02:36:38,060 --> 02:36:40,330
- Let's surely win the next one.
- Let's surely win the next one.

3395
02:36:40,330 --> 02:36:41,490
I'll try to make it happen.

3396
02:36:41,490 --> 02:36:43,100
Make it happen with what you've got.

3397
02:36:43,560 --> 02:36:44,760
Team Rookie will go first.

3398
02:36:45,200 --> 02:36:47,330
- Right.
- It's R, C, P1, and P2.

3399
02:36:47,330 --> 02:36:48,530
- Right. We're fourth.
- Right.

3400
02:36:48,800 --> 02:36:49,800
We have an advantage...

3401
02:36:49,800 --> 02:36:50,800
- when it comes to the bet.
- Right.

3402
02:36:50,800 --> 02:36:52,840
- We don't have cube one, right?
- That's the only one we don't have.

3403
02:36:52,840 --> 02:36:54,010
- We have the rest.
- We have the rest.

3404
02:36:54,010 --> 02:36:55,410
We have the greatest advantage.

3405
02:36:55,410 --> 02:36:56,880
The only one we abandoned was cube one.

3406
02:36:57,140 --> 02:36:58,740
We should try to win this one.

3407
02:36:58,740 --> 02:37:00,950
Right. We should try to win this one.

3408
02:37:01,880 --> 02:37:04,920
This round is really important.

3409
02:37:04,920 --> 02:37:06,420
If we do well here,

3410
02:37:06,420 --> 02:37:09,290
around 90 percent of our teams
will survive.

3411
02:37:09,490 --> 02:37:11,020
The hidden item wasn't bought yet, right?

3412
02:37:11,160 --> 02:37:13,090
- It was bought.
- It was bought.

3413
02:37:13,090 --> 02:37:14,530
Whose turn is it now?

3414
02:37:14,530 --> 02:37:15,760
- Ji Min.
- It's Ji Min.

3415
02:37:15,760 --> 02:37:17,900
Then, we have to use it.

3416
02:37:18,430 --> 02:37:19,430
- Right away?
- Right.

3417
02:37:19,630 --> 02:37:23,840
But for example,
something like the space shuttle...

3418
02:37:24,400 --> 02:37:27,110
can be known by everyone
that it's not worth much.

3419
02:37:27,110 --> 02:37:28,570
Let's say, Ji Min wasn't able to
make the judgment.

3420
02:37:28,570 --> 02:37:29,940
The ones going with her.

3421
02:37:29,940 --> 02:37:31,140
- Kyoung Hoon and...
- Right.

3422
02:37:31,140 --> 02:37:33,580
- I'll be there as well.
- The older members...

3423
02:37:33,580 --> 02:37:36,250
- I'm pretty good with prices.
- Right.

3424
02:37:36,250 --> 02:37:39,420
Right. Kyoung Hoon and Beom
will be standing beside her.

3425
02:37:39,420 --> 02:37:41,390
Never put your hands on the table.

3426
02:37:41,390 --> 02:37:42,450
While you're standing there,

3427
02:37:42,650 --> 02:37:44,820
if you think you know the price,

3428
02:37:44,820 --> 02:37:46,090
place one hand on the table.

3429
02:37:46,090 --> 02:37:47,760
- Stay still if you don't know.
- Right.

3430
02:37:48,360 --> 02:37:49,630
If no one's hand is on the table,

3431
02:37:49,630 --> 02:37:51,530
you can use
the item card value check coupon.

3432
02:37:51,530 --> 02:37:53,400
If there's a single hand,
you don't have to use it.

3433
02:37:53,400 --> 02:37:54,770
- Okay? Got it, right?
- Right.

3434
02:37:54,770 --> 02:37:56,270
So hands up if you know,
and hands down if you don't know.

3435
02:37:56,270 --> 02:37:57,540
Right. You keep them down
if you don't know it.

3436
02:37:57,540 --> 02:37:59,200
- They go up if you know it.
- Okay.

3437
02:37:59,200 --> 02:38:01,270
If it isn't properly on the table,
that person probably forgot.

3438
02:38:01,270 --> 02:38:02,910
- Right.
- It has to be placed accurately.

3439
02:38:02,910 --> 02:38:04,080
- Right.
- Right.

3440
02:38:04,180 --> 02:38:06,210
The hidden item was bought...

3441
02:38:06,810 --> 02:38:08,510
for Jin Ho to use anyway.

3442
02:38:08,510 --> 02:38:09,750
Use it if you feel like you need it.

3443
02:38:09,750 --> 02:38:12,450
Just go for a betting game
with your information.

3444
02:38:13,990 --> 02:38:16,660
I'm sure you'll bring the advantage
with the bet.

3445
02:38:17,890 --> 02:38:19,460
If I don't know,

3446
02:38:20,230 --> 02:38:21,530
- I should ask.
- Just use the item.

3447
02:38:21,530 --> 02:38:22,560
"How much is this?"

3448
02:38:22,560 --> 02:38:25,400
And everyone follows me with their bets.

3449
02:38:25,400 --> 02:38:27,300
That could be better.

3450
02:38:27,700 --> 02:38:28,700
Well,

3451
02:38:29,200 --> 02:38:30,440
as that moment came,

3452
02:38:30,440 --> 02:38:32,470
I couldn't but help...

3453
02:38:33,570 --> 02:38:34,570
feel rushed.

3454
02:38:35,140 --> 02:38:36,640
The current situation...

3455
02:38:37,240 --> 02:38:38,710
is like the era of scarcity.

3456
02:38:38,710 --> 02:38:40,050
Items are so precious,

3457
02:38:40,050 --> 02:38:41,550
so it would be better...

3458
02:38:42,150 --> 02:38:43,250
to obtain at least one item.

3459
02:38:44,150 --> 02:38:46,180
Team P1 is taking everything. Gosh.

3460
02:38:46,180 --> 02:38:47,550
- Exactly.
- Right.

3461
02:38:49,490 --> 02:38:52,160
Why form an alliance like that?

3462
02:38:55,090 --> 02:38:57,800
The auction for Round Six will now begin.

3463
02:38:59,200 --> 02:39:02,670
(Team P3: Hong Jin Ho, Team R: Kwak Beom,
Team C: Kim Kyoung Hoon)

3464
02:39:02,970 --> 02:39:05,470
(Team P1: Park Ji Min,
Team P2: Ha Seung Jin)

3465
02:39:06,370 --> 02:39:08,510
Team Rookie, select the item.

3466
02:39:09,510 --> 02:39:11,240
I will select number 13.

3467
02:39:11,540 --> 02:39:13,710
- Okay.
- Item 13 has been selected.

3468
02:39:13,710 --> 02:39:14,710
Let's go.

3469
02:39:15,010 --> 02:39:18,720
Item card. It's a lunch ticket
with Warren Buffett.

3470
02:39:19,280 --> 02:39:22,250
It was auctioned off in eBay in June 2022.

3471
02:39:22,750 --> 02:39:25,060
After the event,

3472
02:39:25,060 --> 02:39:28,130
Warren Buffett announced the end
of the lunch event.

3473
02:39:36,100 --> 02:39:39,770
(Alliance team signal:
Putting one hand up if price is known)

3474
02:39:40,070 --> 02:39:41,710
- Stay still if you don't know.
- Right.

3475
02:39:45,780 --> 02:39:48,650
A lunch ticket with Warren Buffett?

3476
02:39:48,980 --> 02:39:50,150
This must be really cheap.

3477
02:39:50,580 --> 02:39:52,250
This was planted in for the show.

3478
02:39:52,250 --> 02:39:53,350
It's a fool's card.

3479
02:39:53,850 --> 02:39:56,560
I thought it was 1,000,000 dollars
at first.

3480
02:39:56,560 --> 02:39:58,760
I had a brief memory
of hearing about it...

3481
02:39:58,760 --> 02:40:01,730
and I thought it was
around 1,000,000 dollars.

3482
02:40:02,630 --> 02:40:05,360
I didn't expect it to be that expensive.

3483
02:40:06,700 --> 02:40:09,200
As someone
who loves making stock investments,

3484
02:40:09,570 --> 02:40:11,800
I highly respect Warren Buffett.

3485
02:40:12,270 --> 02:40:13,440
However,

3486
02:40:14,010 --> 02:40:18,310
grabbing lunch with him...

3487
02:40:19,080 --> 02:40:20,080
doesn't feel that necessary.

3488
02:40:20,780 --> 02:40:22,250
So...

3489
02:40:23,450 --> 02:40:25,280
I expected it to be around 50,000 dollars.

3490
02:40:25,620 --> 02:40:27,890
I decided to go with some bluffing.

3491
02:40:28,090 --> 02:40:30,120
It must be quite expensive.

3492
02:40:30,120 --> 02:40:32,720
Only one person got to do this.

3493
02:40:32,720 --> 02:40:33,790
How expensive would...

3494
02:40:35,130 --> 02:40:37,430
eating with someone cost?

3495
02:40:38,160 --> 02:40:41,170
It would be expensive
to have a meal with Warren Buffett.

3496
02:40:41,270 --> 02:40:43,400
Right.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

3497
02:40:44,400 --> 02:40:45,400
This?

3498
02:40:46,370 --> 02:40:47,440
First of all,

3499
02:40:47,970 --> 02:40:49,470
it felt really cheap.

3500
02:40:50,140 --> 02:40:52,310
How expensive would a lunch ticket be?

3501
02:40:53,210 --> 02:40:54,450
But inside,

3502
02:40:54,650 --> 02:40:56,210
I thought that I should try to buy it
at a cheap price.

3503
02:40:57,550 --> 02:41:00,150
It's a lunch ticket with Warren Buffett.

3504
02:41:00,150 --> 02:41:02,290
- Darn it. This is really cheap.
- It was auctioned off in eBay...

3505
02:41:02,290 --> 02:41:04,320
in June 2022.

3506
02:41:04,890 --> 02:41:08,390
Wait. This should've been
quite pricey, though.

3507
02:41:08,990 --> 02:41:11,760
Wasn't it around 2,000,000 dollars?

3508
02:41:12,460 --> 02:41:13,730
It's the last one?

3509
02:41:13,830 --> 02:41:14,830
Right.

