02:51:31,380 --> 02:51:34,490
After Jin Ho got the card
and checked the price,

3762
02:51:36,220 --> 02:51:38,620
he forced a laugh.

3763
02:51:38,860 --> 02:51:40,830
He looked flustered and said,
"This is a shock."

3764
02:51:40,830 --> 02:51:43,290
- Right.
- Did he not know the price?

3765
02:51:43,290 --> 02:51:45,800
- He might not have known the price.
- Right.

3766
02:51:45,800 --> 02:51:47,430
- He might've thought it was expensive.
- Right.

3767
02:51:47,430 --> 02:51:48,970
That's less than 1,000,000 dollars.

3768
02:51:49,170 --> 02:51:51,470
So, in a way,

3769
02:51:51,470 --> 02:51:52,900
Team P3 bought a poop card.

3770
02:51:53,000 --> 02:51:55,110
Are we the only team without a card?

3771
02:51:55,110 --> 02:51:56,140
- Yes.
- They all have one, right?

3772
02:51:56,140 --> 02:51:58,310
- Yes.
- Jin Ho's team has a poop card.

3773
02:51:59,480 --> 02:52:00,950
We should hope that...

3774
02:52:00,950 --> 02:52:02,410
- the special card doesn't appear.
- Right.

3775
02:52:02,410 --> 02:52:04,080
- We must hope that it becomes a long war.
- Right.

3776
02:52:04,580 --> 02:52:06,880
- The item wasn't used, right?
- It wasn't used.

3777
02:52:06,880 --> 02:52:10,290
Just like the previous round,

3778
02:52:10,290 --> 02:52:12,490
we should try to predict the price...

3779
02:52:12,490 --> 02:52:13,520
and put our hands up if we know the price.

3780
02:52:13,520 --> 02:52:15,260
We'll keep our hands down
if we don't know the price.

3781
02:52:15,260 --> 02:52:18,230
If you know the price, Keun Woo,

3782
02:52:18,230 --> 02:52:19,230
don't use the item.

3783
02:52:19,230 --> 02:52:21,570
You can use it
if you don't know the price.

3784
02:52:21,770 --> 02:52:24,470
I want to mention this
to Keun Woo and You Hyun.

3785
02:52:24,470 --> 02:52:26,670
I will make the bet
when the good card appears.

3786
02:52:26,670 --> 02:52:28,910
You must make the bet
when the bad card appears, Keun Woo.

3787
02:52:29,770 --> 02:52:32,110
If the good card appears,
your team will make the bet.

3788
02:52:32,110 --> 02:52:33,940
- We'll play the lowest number.
- Right.

3789
02:52:33,940 --> 02:52:34,980
- And for that team,
- When the bad card appears,

3790
02:52:34,980 --> 02:52:36,450
- when the bad card appears,
- he will tank it for us.

3791
02:52:36,450 --> 02:52:37,920
- Keun Woo.
- We'll both play two.

3792
02:52:37,920 --> 02:52:39,820
It's easy for you, Keun Woo.

3793
02:52:39,820 --> 02:52:41,820
Whether it's a good or bad card,
you just have to play one.

3794
02:52:41,820 --> 02:52:43,490
- Right.
- Okay.

3795
02:52:44,490 --> 02:52:46,720
We even established an alliance.

3796
02:52:48,160 --> 02:52:49,890
I hope it ends as a perfect win.

3797
02:52:50,060 --> 02:52:52,800
Team C needs to come up a bit.

3798
02:52:53,430 --> 02:52:54,470
Right.

3799
02:52:54,930 --> 02:52:57,370
Players for the auction of Round Seven,

3800
02:52:57,570 --> 02:52:59,240
please gather in the main hall.

3801
02:53:00,840 --> 02:53:03,510
The auction for Round Seven
will now begin.

3802
02:53:04,240 --> 02:53:06,310
Team P3, select the item.

3803
02:53:06,480 --> 02:53:08,450
I will select number nine.

3804
02:53:08,680 --> 02:53:09,950
Please be an item.

3805
02:53:10,880 --> 02:53:13,020
Item number nine has been selected.

3806
02:53:18,460 --> 02:53:22,160
Special card.
It's the top price item return card.

3807
02:53:22,490 --> 02:53:25,100
The item card with the highest price
in possession...

3808
02:53:25,100 --> 02:53:26,630
will be returned right away.

3809
02:53:27,030 --> 02:53:29,700
The returned card
will be removed from the game...

3810
02:53:29,700 --> 02:53:31,870
and the price will not be revealed.

3811
02:53:32,370 --> 02:53:34,970
When no item cards are possessed,

3812
02:53:34,970 --> 02:53:37,210
the loss card effect will occur...

3813
02:53:37,310 --> 02:53:39,240
as soon as an item card gets won.

3814
02:53:40,540 --> 02:53:42,810
Out of the special cards,

3815
02:53:43,380 --> 02:53:46,750
the loss card will be won
by the player with the lowest number.

3816
02:53:49,550 --> 02:53:50,860
"Are we cursed?"

3817
02:53:51,220 --> 02:53:53,090
"Why did that card have to appear?"

3818
02:53:53,090 --> 02:53:54,290
But it's okay.

3819
02:53:54,290 --> 02:53:56,260
I prepared myself.

3820
02:53:56,260 --> 02:53:58,560
I decided the number of cubes...

3821
02:53:58,560 --> 02:54:00,360
that will be used.

3822
02:54:00,460 --> 02:54:02,230
"I will go with what I prepared."

3823
02:54:02,570 --> 02:54:04,800
I felt comfortable
in the midst of the discomfort.

3824
02:54:05,200 --> 02:54:06,700
You'll have to spend quite a lot.

3825
02:54:08,510 --> 02:54:10,070
You have two expensive cards.

3826
02:54:10,310 --> 02:54:11,740
I heard the watch was really expensive.

3827
02:54:12,840 --> 02:54:15,880
Gosh, a terrible card appeared.

3828
02:54:16,010 --> 02:54:20,680
I was going to play cube one
if a special item appeared.

3829
02:54:21,120 --> 02:54:22,450
The special item actually appeared,

3830
02:54:22,450 --> 02:54:28,330
but I had to give up
a really expensive card.

3831
02:54:28,330 --> 02:54:30,660
It's a difficult situation,

3832
02:54:31,060 --> 02:54:32,500
but I'll have to see how things go.

3833
02:54:32,730 --> 02:54:35,100
This card makes our card...

3834
02:54:35,100 --> 02:54:37,070
a negative card.

3835
02:54:37,400 --> 02:54:40,300
We must never get this card.

3836
02:54:40,500 --> 02:54:42,010
Gosh, this actually came out.

3837
02:54:42,010 --> 02:54:43,170
What happens when
there are no items possessed?

3838
02:54:43,170 --> 02:54:44,910
- The next item.
- The next item gets taken away.

3839
02:54:44,910 --> 02:54:46,880
- Gosh.
- We must never get this.

3840
02:54:46,980 --> 02:54:48,850
Why did this appear
right after we got this card?

3841
02:54:48,850 --> 02:54:50,510
- Gosh, this is so scary.
- Gosh.

3842
02:54:51,580 --> 02:54:54,150
The other teams must feel scared as well.

3843
02:54:54,390 --> 02:54:57,120
Team P1 might get it...

3844
02:54:57,120 --> 02:54:58,690
because everyone else wants to avoid it.

3845
02:54:58,690 --> 02:55:01,190
Team C might tank for it.

3846
02:55:01,760 --> 02:55:04,630
Team C will be in danger from the tanking.

3847
02:55:04,860 --> 02:55:06,200
This will be hard to tank.

3848
02:55:07,160 --> 02:55:09,070
Team C must tank this for us.

3849
02:55:09,630 --> 02:55:12,100
Team C must tank this
and win an expensive card.

3850
02:55:12,100 --> 02:55:13,770
We must switch the card
that's worth 490,000 dollars.

3851
02:55:14,910 --> 02:55:18,040
A very devastating loss card appeared.

3852
02:55:18,040 --> 02:55:19,740
The moment we get that card,

3853
02:55:20,440 --> 02:55:22,050
we will be in last place.

3854
02:55:22,280 --> 02:55:25,920
Team P1's highest item card
is worth 26.5 million dollars.

3855
02:55:26,050 --> 02:55:29,750
Team C should discard
the item card of 650,000 dollars.

3856
02:55:29,990 --> 02:55:31,990
It's right for Team C to tank.

3857
02:55:32,890 --> 02:55:33,890
It's tough.

3858
02:55:33,890 --> 02:55:35,690
After we tank,

3859
02:55:35,690 --> 02:55:37,830
there's one-third of a chance
that a special card appears.

3860
02:55:38,400 --> 02:55:40,360
There's one-third of a chance
that we'll end up last.

3861
02:55:40,460 --> 02:55:42,930
There are 23 cards. It's 6 out of 23.

3862
02:55:43,270 --> 02:55:46,070
- It's one-quarter of a chance.
- It's closer to one-quarter.

3863
02:55:46,070 --> 02:55:48,240
(There's 1-quarter of a chance
that the game will end in Round 8.)

3864
02:55:48,240 --> 02:55:49,940
What will happen if we don't tank?

3865
02:55:49,940 --> 02:55:51,840
We will be in big danger.

3866
02:55:52,510 --> 02:55:53,940
It seems like You Hyun will decide
not to do that.

3867
02:55:54,550 --> 02:55:56,480
The game might end...

3868
02:55:56,780 --> 02:55:58,480
if the special card appears again.

3869
02:55:58,480 --> 02:56:00,520
We must definitely avoid the card.

3870
02:56:00,920 --> 02:56:02,450
That got me a bit worried.

3871
02:56:03,220 --> 02:56:06,390
As You Hyun is really conservative
and tight-minded,

3872
02:56:06,760 --> 02:56:09,930
I thought that You Hyun went out
at the right time to be stubborn.

3873
02:56:10,630 --> 02:56:12,230
The two of us should talk.

3874
02:56:12,230 --> 02:56:14,900
Starting with Team P3,
enter the Voting Room...

3875
02:56:14,900 --> 02:56:16,370
and submit the cubes.

3876
02:56:17,100 --> 02:56:18,240
Just a moment.

3877
02:56:18,970 --> 02:56:21,510
The safest way...

3878
02:56:21,840 --> 02:56:23,310
is for that team to tank.

3879
02:56:23,510 --> 02:56:27,240
Even if they get it
with the lowest number,

3880
02:56:27,240 --> 02:56:29,150
it ends with giving up
1 out of 2 item cards.

3881
02:56:30,080 --> 02:56:33,880
If not, one person must take the risk.

3882
02:56:33,980 --> 02:56:36,690
You can't take the risk.

3883
02:56:36,690 --> 02:56:38,920
Without caring about the price,

3884
02:56:38,920 --> 02:56:40,620
we both only have one card.

3885
02:56:40,620 --> 02:56:41,990
It's the same risk for both of us.

3886
02:56:43,230 --> 02:56:45,460
If I decide to tank,

3887
02:56:45,460 --> 02:56:48,400
and the special item appears again,
that will be the end for our team.

3888
02:56:48,430 --> 02:56:50,670
It's the same risk for both of us.

3889
02:56:50,800 --> 02:56:53,900
Team P1 decided to tank for us.

3890
02:56:54,100 --> 02:56:56,970
The one with two item cards
must tank first.

3891
02:56:56,970 --> 02:56:58,710
I believe this is the best way.

3892
02:57:00,280 --> 02:57:02,180
That's the best way, right?

3893
02:57:02,180 --> 02:57:03,580
What else could there be?

3894
02:57:04,350 --> 02:57:06,050
It happened to be...

3895
02:57:06,150 --> 02:57:09,220
that most expensive card
that had to be returned.

3896
02:57:09,590 --> 02:57:12,820
You Hyun's card was less expensive
than ours.

3897
02:57:13,160 --> 02:57:15,660
I did think that it would be
more reasonable...

3898
02:57:15,660 --> 02:57:17,830
for Team C to get the card.

3899
02:57:18,030 --> 02:57:20,860
Team P1 or Team C.

3900
02:57:20,860 --> 02:57:23,100
It was hard to decide
on who should get the card.

3901
02:57:25,000 --> 02:57:27,710
- I believe that's the best way.
- Right.

3902
02:57:28,140 --> 02:57:30,140
I believe that's the best way.

3903
02:57:31,310 --> 02:57:32,480
This is tough.

3904
02:57:32,510 --> 02:57:33,910
Should we go with that, then?

3905
02:57:33,910 --> 02:57:35,450
Okay. Let's do that.

3906
02:57:38,020 --> 02:57:40,480
Starting with Team P3,
please enter the Voting Room.

3907
02:57:43,920 --> 02:57:45,190
My pockets are loaded.

3908
02:57:45,290 --> 02:57:46,360
What?

3909
02:57:47,630 --> 02:57:48,830
Hye Seon kept some by her belly as well.

3910
02:57:51,630 --> 02:57:52,730
Put them all in.

3911
02:57:54,570 --> 02:57:55,930
I can't fit in anymore.
Put them in my underwear.

3912
02:57:56,470 --> 02:57:57,570
My back pockets.

3913
02:57:57,570 --> 02:57:58,700
Just don't take them out.

3914
02:58:13,150 --> 02:58:14,920
Gosh, I knew this one was going to
come out.

3915
02:58:32,440 --> 02:58:33,800
Gosh, 28 is a lot.

3916
02:58:37,510 --> 02:58:39,980
When the time came, I wondered
how much the others would spend.

3917
02:58:39,980 --> 02:58:42,310
"Am I spending too much
compared to the others?"

3918
02:58:42,310 --> 02:58:43,910
I felt these different worries.

3919
02:58:45,320 --> 02:58:47,220
(Sighing)

3920
02:58:47,220 --> 02:58:49,120
My head had a lot to think about.

3921
02:58:50,450 --> 02:58:51,560
That's a lot.

3922
02:58:55,560 --> 02:58:56,860
(Team P3 submits...)

3923
02:58:56,860 --> 02:58:59,800
Team P3, please head to the main hall.

3924
02:59:03,000 --> 02:59:05,100
Team Rookie, please enter the Voting Room.

3925
02:59:20,350 --> 02:59:23,690
Team Rookie has submitted cube number two.

3926
02:59:24,860 --> 02:59:27,120
When I come out, Keun Woo,

3927
02:59:28,060 --> 02:59:29,990
you can bring in everything you have.

3928
02:59:29,990 --> 02:59:31,430
That's when this happens.

3929
02:59:32,430 --> 02:59:33,460
Right.

3930
02:59:33,460 --> 02:59:35,470
Bring in everything you have
and spend everything.

3931
02:59:36,400 --> 02:59:37,430
That's what you need to do.

3932
02:59:38,240 --> 02:59:39,540
Bring in everything and...

3933
02:59:39,540 --> 02:59:42,040
Hey, are you seeing me as a fool?

3934
02:59:42,310 --> 02:59:43,340
That was close.

3935
02:59:43,340 --> 02:59:45,640
Why are you trying to send
someone away, Xitsuh?

3936
02:59:45,640 --> 02:59:46,640
That was close.

3937
02:59:48,710 --> 02:59:50,510
Gosh, this is driving me insane.

3938
02:59:55,420 --> 02:59:59,360
Team C has submitted cube number 2.

3939
03:00:07,830 --> 03:00:08,870
I'll be back.

3940
03:00:09,670 --> 03:00:11,200
Hurry up and come down.

3941
03:00:11,770 --> 03:00:13,140
You must be trying to
start a conversation.

3942
03:00:13,840 --> 03:00:16,110
The moment we met at the staircase,

3943
03:00:16,540 --> 03:00:17,880
I went, "One."

3944
03:00:18,380 --> 03:00:19,980
- I'll submit cube one.
- Right.

3945
03:00:24,750 --> 03:00:28,420
Team P1, please submit the cubes.

3946
03:00:29,720 --> 03:00:31,560
To be honest, I was a bit torn.

3947
03:00:31,760 --> 03:00:33,120
I felt that...

3948
03:00:33,190 --> 03:00:35,860
our team was in danger.

3949
03:00:37,060 --> 03:00:39,560
Team P1, please head to the main hall.

3950
03:00:44,100 --> 03:00:45,540
Aren't you thinking about taking it?

3951
03:00:48,970 --> 03:00:50,470
Ask your ancestors.

3952
03:00:51,210 --> 03:00:53,680
Is your card that awful?

3953
03:00:53,680 --> 03:00:54,780
It's a secret.

3954
03:00:55,080 --> 03:00:56,550
I think it's something
that can be shared between us.

3955
03:00:57,410 --> 03:00:58,420
Don't you think?

3956
03:00:58,850 --> 03:01:00,250
- That's not true.
- No?

3957
03:01:01,890 --> 03:01:03,090
It was a relief...

3958
03:01:03,090 --> 03:01:05,490
because I went last to make the bet.

3959
03:01:05,790 --> 03:01:07,520
I checked what Xitsuh played...

3960
03:01:07,790 --> 03:01:10,990
and he had cubes in his back pocket.

3961
03:01:10,990 --> 03:01:12,300
He placed the cubes...

3962
03:01:12,800 --> 03:01:14,200
without keeping them by his belly.

3963
03:01:16,070 --> 03:01:17,330
He submitted just two cubes.

3964
03:01:18,270 --> 03:01:20,700
I thought of the worst-case scenario...

3965
03:01:20,900 --> 03:01:23,010
before making my decision.

3966
03:01:23,910 --> 03:01:24,940
Here you are.

3967
03:01:24,940 --> 03:01:26,140
(Team P2 submits...)

3968
03:01:29,910 --> 03:01:31,010
I will use an item.

3969
03:01:33,550 --> 03:01:35,120
I will use the item card exchange coupon.

3970
03:01:35,790 --> 03:01:39,920
Team P1 suddenly decided to use
the item card exchange coupon.

3971
03:01:41,260 --> 03:01:44,160
Team C actually has...

3972
03:01:44,360 --> 03:01:47,030
a very cheap item card.

3973
03:01:47,200 --> 03:01:50,930
"Are they going to trade it off
to help the other team?"

3974
03:01:50,930 --> 03:01:54,000
"Will Team C tank the special card?"

3975
03:01:54,910 --> 03:01:58,210
Team P1 has used
the item card exchange coupon.

3976
03:01:59,840 --> 03:02:02,950
Please name the item card
you wish to trade off.

3977
03:02:03,150 --> 03:02:05,520
I will trade off
the Michael Jackson jacket.

3978
03:02:06,880 --> 03:02:10,250
Please name the item card you wish to get.

3979
03:02:12,120 --> 03:02:16,530
I will select Team P3's
lunch ticket with Warren Buffett.

3980
03:02:19,960 --> 03:02:21,060
"He got me."

3981
03:02:22,570 --> 03:02:24,400
"Does he know the worth
of the lunch ticket?"

3982
03:02:29,170 --> 03:02:31,710
How would I know the price
of the lunch ticket with Warren Buffett?

3983
03:02:32,280 --> 03:02:34,110
Sang Min is someone
who can be aware of those things.

3984
03:02:35,180 --> 03:02:37,610
(Around 1 hour ago)

3985
03:02:37,710 --> 03:02:39,120
Hold on. Tell me what it is.

3986
03:02:39,650 --> 03:02:40,820
Warren Buffett?

3987
03:02:41,250 --> 03:02:43,890
- A lunch ticket with Warren Buffett.
- A lunch ticket with Warren Buffett.

3988
03:02:43,890 --> 03:02:45,690
- It's the last lunch ticket.
- The last one.

3989
03:02:45,690 --> 03:02:46,690
There won't be any more of them.

3990
03:02:46,920 --> 03:02:49,990
That started from around
500,000 dollars to 1,000,000 dollars.

3991
03:02:50,560 --> 03:02:51,560
We must buy that.

3992
03:02:52,060 --> 03:02:53,560
I don't think we have to.

3993
03:02:53,560 --> 03:02:55,100
How much is that?

3994
03:02:55,870 --> 03:02:56,870
This?

3995
03:02:57,770 --> 03:02:59,000
This is over 20 million dollars.

3996
03:02:59,000 --> 03:03:00,040
Really?

3997
03:03:00,440 --> 03:03:01,440
How much? It's 20 million dollars?

3998
03:03:02,810 --> 03:03:04,710
It was originally five million dollars.

3999
03:03:05,580 --> 03:03:07,680
But it became the last one.

4000
03:03:08,080 --> 03:03:09,780
The last one holds more meaning.

4001
03:03:10,010 --> 03:03:12,580
As it's the last one,

4002
03:03:12,580 --> 03:03:16,690
it can be used at any time.

4003
03:03:17,090 --> 03:03:18,260
It's the last one.

4004
03:03:18,360 --> 03:03:20,560
It can actually be
over 50 million dollars for me.

4005
03:03:21,390 --> 03:03:24,290
Even if it's half the price,

4006
03:03:24,430 --> 03:03:27,030
it should be over 20 million dollars.

4007
03:03:27,300 --> 03:03:28,370
Gosh.

4008
03:03:28,670 --> 03:03:30,530
I got surprised when I heard him say that.

4009
03:03:30,800 --> 03:03:33,440
I thought he was bluffing.

4010
03:03:33,640 --> 03:03:34,970
Warren Buffett...

4011
03:03:35,810 --> 03:03:38,140
is someone who correctly predicted...

4012
03:03:38,180 --> 03:03:41,040
