4501
03:25:37,260 --> 03:25:40,030
I bid a 5 so that
the gap would be exactly 3.

4502
03:25:40,260 --> 03:25:43,900
Team P3, please submit the cubes
if you would like to place a bid.

4503
03:25:46,840 --> 03:25:50,440
I did a rough count of
the remaining cubes,

4504
03:25:50,470 --> 03:25:52,270
and Team C was richer than us.

4505
03:25:52,940 --> 03:25:55,640
(The blind bidding for special cards
in Round 7)

4506
03:25:55,640 --> 03:25:57,650
If it came to that,
I'd have to avoid it no matter what.

4507
03:25:57,650 --> 03:25:59,010
At that point, I would have to back off.

4508
03:25:59,010 --> 03:26:00,320
So then, how much should I spend?

4509
03:26:00,320 --> 03:26:01,880
That was all I could think about.

4510
03:26:06,490 --> 03:26:11,260
(After giving it a lot of thought,
Xitsuh placed his bid on 27 cubes.)

4511
03:26:11,260 --> 03:26:12,290
Okay.

4512
03:26:12,290 --> 03:26:16,030
I'll use up to 27 cubes
to defend this lunch.

4513
03:26:18,000 --> 03:26:21,640
I guess I was only thinking
about the possibilities.

4514
03:26:22,170 --> 03:26:25,210
That team has about this many cubes left.

4515
03:26:26,010 --> 03:26:27,810
How far can they keep going?

4516
03:26:29,040 --> 03:26:33,220
(Team C has more cubes left than Team P3.)

4517
03:26:36,290 --> 03:26:37,590
I'll pass.

4518
03:26:38,050 --> 03:26:40,290
Team P3 has passed on this bid.

4519
03:26:40,460 --> 03:26:42,830
It looked like Team C could...

4520
03:26:42,830 --> 03:26:44,890
easily take it if he wanted to.

4521
03:26:45,660 --> 03:26:48,400
Team Challenger has won the item card.

4522
03:26:48,800 --> 03:26:50,400
Please come forward
with the cubes you submitted...

4523
03:26:50,400 --> 03:26:51,900
and collect your card.

4524
03:26:56,410 --> 03:26:58,840
Cards can only be checked
in the Main Hall.

4525
03:26:59,810 --> 03:27:02,080
It felt so futile.

4526
03:27:03,210 --> 03:27:04,450
Gosh.

4527
03:27:04,950 --> 03:27:07,080
The moment I failed to get that,

4528
03:27:07,080 --> 03:27:10,050
my strategy shifted to...

4529
03:27:10,420 --> 03:27:12,720
playing the long game and just...

4530
03:27:12,720 --> 03:27:14,260
trying to scrape into 3rd place.

4531
03:27:14,460 --> 03:27:15,990
The auction has ended.

4532
03:27:15,990 --> 03:27:17,490
Please return to your rooms.

4533
03:27:17,990 --> 03:27:21,430
You're clever, Hye Seon.
You drove the price way up.

4534
03:27:22,330 --> 03:27:23,670
Gosh, all right.

4535
03:27:23,670 --> 03:27:25,000
(29 million dollars)

4536
03:27:25,000 --> 03:27:26,500
I see.

4537
03:27:26,500 --> 03:27:28,100
(29 million dollars)

4538
03:27:28,100 --> 03:27:30,540
I didn't realize housing in Seoul
was this expensive.

4539
03:27:30,540 --> 03:27:34,110
It wasn't that the entire building
was 29 billion dollars.

4540
03:27:34,540 --> 03:27:38,080
Just one unit in that high-rise
costs 29 million dollars.

4541
03:27:38,080 --> 03:27:39,620
If I ever want to live
somewhere like that,

4542
03:27:39,680 --> 03:27:41,780
I'd better work really hard.

4543
03:27:42,220 --> 03:27:47,260
(Lots secured by each team)

4544
03:27:49,120 --> 03:27:50,230
Did you get it?

4545
03:27:50,990 --> 03:27:53,230
- He got it. Look at his face.
- He got it.

4546
03:27:53,500 --> 03:27:55,060
- Nice.
- I'll let the winner talk.

4547
03:27:55,160 --> 03:27:56,530
- Ji Hoo.
- Ji Hoo.

4548
03:27:56,530 --> 03:27:58,000
How much did you spend?

4549
03:27:58,000 --> 03:27:59,330
- You spent a lot, right?
- I spent a lot.

4550
03:27:59,440 --> 03:28:00,870
It's a huge amount of money, isn't it?

4551
03:28:00,900 --> 03:28:02,300
Yes, 29 million dollars.

4552
03:28:02,300 --> 03:28:03,670
- What?
- Gosh.

4553
03:28:04,110 --> 03:28:05,510
- I told you.
- I knew it.

4554
03:28:06,140 --> 03:28:08,510
Since this was a round where
anyone could've gone all in,

4555
03:28:08,510 --> 03:28:10,680
the psychological pressure
must have been intense.

4556
03:28:10,680 --> 03:28:12,680
Deciding what to submit first...

4557
03:28:12,680 --> 03:28:13,920
was probably a real headache too.

4558
03:28:13,980 --> 03:28:15,850
But compared to spending 20 cubes
on a 450,000-dollar property,

4559
03:28:15,850 --> 03:28:18,220
it was a much safer
and more reliable move.

4560
03:28:19,120 --> 03:28:20,820
As expected, Ji Hoo is amazing.

4561
03:28:21,160 --> 03:28:22,560
He's the best.

4562
03:28:23,030 --> 03:28:25,130
- Team C bought it.
- Gosh, C bought it?

4563
03:28:25,130 --> 03:28:26,400
He spent 56.

4564
03:28:26,400 --> 03:28:27,960
- He spent 56?
- He did?

4565
03:28:27,960 --> 03:28:29,300
- Who was he up against?
- Me.

4566
03:28:29,970 --> 03:28:31,570
- You know how much it's worth, right?
- Yes.

4567
03:28:31,670 --> 03:28:33,270
So, even if it drops to half price...

4568
03:28:33,270 --> 03:28:35,070
If we take 1st place
and it ends up at half price...

4569
03:28:35,070 --> 03:28:36,240
Good job.

4570
03:28:36,310 --> 03:28:38,710
I went all-in because I thought
we'd at least make it into 3rd place.

4571
03:28:38,710 --> 03:28:40,380
I would've given up at 35.

4572
03:28:41,040 --> 03:28:42,640
- You did great. You raised the price.
- So then,

4573
03:28:42,640 --> 03:28:43,910
how high did you go?

4574
03:28:43,910 --> 03:28:45,380
I think it was 51.

4575
03:28:45,380 --> 03:28:47,480
You did great.

4576
03:28:47,580 --> 03:28:48,950
Since we used way too many blocks...

4577
03:28:48,950 --> 03:28:51,250
in the special card auction earlier,

4578
03:28:51,250 --> 03:28:53,190
they had a lot more left than we did.

4579
03:28:53,190 --> 03:28:55,860
If it came down to the end,
Team C were bound to win.

4580
03:28:55,860 --> 03:28:58,860
The funny thing is that
Team P2 dropped out early on.

4581
03:28:59,090 --> 03:29:01,460
Before the bidding even properly started,

4582
03:29:01,460 --> 03:29:02,560
he apparently tested the waters once...

4583
03:29:02,560 --> 03:29:04,500
and decided to sit it out.

4584
03:29:05,130 --> 03:29:06,370
I wonder if...

4585
03:29:07,340 --> 03:29:09,740
he didn't know how much ACRO Forest...

4586
03:29:10,310 --> 03:29:11,510
is worth.

4587
03:29:17,250 --> 03:29:18,650
Ultimately, I decided to pass.

4588
03:29:18,650 --> 03:29:19,720
Why?

4589
03:29:20,150 --> 03:29:21,880
- The bidding price was insane.
- What do you mean?

4590
03:29:21,880 --> 03:29:23,390
I just left it to fate.

4591
03:29:24,020 --> 03:29:25,420
- Here, I'll show you.
- Why?

4592
03:29:27,920 --> 03:29:29,260
In the end...

4593
03:29:30,160 --> 03:29:31,660
No, but why? Why?

4594
03:29:31,690 --> 03:29:34,230
We're at 69.

4595
03:29:34,700 --> 03:29:36,160
- Yes, we're at 69.
- Yes.

4596
03:29:36,670 --> 03:29:38,270
Honestly, I bet on this.

4597
03:29:38,270 --> 03:29:39,570
Since Team P3...

4598
03:29:40,200 --> 03:29:42,800
was coming on so strong, I thought...

4599
03:29:43,470 --> 03:29:44,910
if we got this, we'd take 1st place.

4600
03:29:44,910 --> 03:29:46,910
That's what I was hoping for.

4601
03:29:46,910 --> 03:29:48,080
But at the end...

4602
03:29:48,240 --> 03:29:49,380
Why, though?

4603
03:29:49,380 --> 03:29:50,580
Why didn't he buy it?

4604
03:29:51,380 --> 03:29:53,720
Was I not clear enough?

4605
03:29:53,820 --> 03:29:56,290
Was there a misunderstanding? A mistake?

4606
03:29:56,290 --> 03:29:57,920
I even considered that...

4607
03:29:58,150 --> 03:30:00,160
maybe he knew it was an older apartment...

4608
03:30:00,160 --> 03:30:02,120
that wasn't worth much.
Practically nothing.

4609
03:30:02,220 --> 03:30:03,460
I thought maybe he was privy to this.

4610
03:30:03,760 --> 03:30:04,960
But no, that wasn't the reason.

4611
03:30:05,660 --> 03:30:06,900
He just didn't buy it.

4612
03:30:09,200 --> 03:30:10,370
How much is ACRO Forest?

4613
03:30:10,370 --> 03:30:12,170
- About 10 million dollars.
- At least 10 million dollars.

4614
03:30:12,170 --> 03:30:13,200
At least 10 million dollars.

4615
03:30:13,200 --> 03:30:14,340
The unit was around 340㎡.

4616
03:30:14,340 --> 03:30:15,840
After it was over, Sang Min said...

4617
03:30:16,570 --> 03:30:17,870
it's 25 million dollars.

4618
03:30:17,870 --> 03:30:19,270
- Really?
- Yes.

4619
03:30:20,240 --> 03:30:21,410
(Gosh)

4620
03:30:22,440 --> 03:30:23,780
It was a fatal mistake.

4621
03:30:24,450 --> 03:30:27,850
The median price for Ohtani Shohei
is 4.3 million dollars.

4622
03:30:27,950 --> 03:30:29,650
But this was 25 million dollars.

4623
03:30:29,650 --> 03:30:31,790
I just missed out on a property
worth at least 25 million dollars.

4624
03:30:33,290 --> 03:30:34,620
I should have gotten it.

4625
03:30:34,890 --> 03:30:36,560
- That's true,
- Yes.

4626
03:30:36,560 --> 03:30:39,130
but talking about it now
doesn't really change anything.

4627
03:30:39,130 --> 03:30:40,800
If you'd gotten it,

4628
03:30:40,830 --> 03:30:42,400
- it would've been huge.
- Right.

4629
03:30:42,530 --> 03:30:43,730
We were hoping for that too.

4630
03:30:43,730 --> 03:30:45,200
- It's unfortunate,
- Okay.

4631
03:30:45,200 --> 03:30:46,570
- Let's go have a smoke.
- but there's nothing we can do now.

4632
03:30:48,000 --> 03:30:50,540
YunB is usually very confident...

4633
03:30:50,540 --> 03:30:52,570
and straightforward,

4634
03:30:52,570 --> 03:30:54,380
but he was blaming himself,

4635
03:30:54,380 --> 03:30:56,110
apologizing, looked completely flustered.

4636
03:30:56,550 --> 03:30:58,080
So I comforted him.

4637
03:30:58,080 --> 03:30:59,250
I said, "YunB, it's fine."

4638
03:30:59,250 --> 03:31:00,350
"We'll just buy everything from now on."

4639
03:31:00,350 --> 03:31:01,450
"I'll go all-in."

4640
03:31:01,450 --> 03:31:02,650
"I'll go all-in."

4641
03:31:02,880 --> 03:31:04,550
"We've still got one bullet left."

4642
03:31:05,920 --> 03:31:07,160
It's all right, YunB.

4643
03:31:07,160 --> 03:31:08,760
- Stop blaming yourself.
- It's okay, YunB.

4644
03:31:08,760 --> 03:31:09,960
- Yes.
- I made mistakes too.

4645
03:31:09,960 --> 03:31:11,630
- Everyone makes mistakes.
- Yes, I made mistakes too. We all did.

4646
03:31:11,790 --> 03:31:13,260
The important thing is that
our team sticks together...

4647
03:31:13,260 --> 03:31:15,030
- and never gives up.
- That's right.

4648
03:31:15,030 --> 03:31:16,200
It's really okay. Seriously.

4649
03:31:16,200 --> 03:31:17,370
- It's really okay.
- Thanks.

4650
03:31:17,570 --> 03:31:19,030
Not at all.

4651
03:31:19,640 --> 03:31:21,200
Still, this is...

4652
03:31:21,300 --> 03:31:22,800
Of course, it's a shame.

4653
03:31:23,010 --> 03:31:24,440
- But once something has happened,
- Right.

4654
03:31:24,440 --> 03:31:26,980
I try not to dwell on it.

4655
03:31:28,110 --> 03:31:29,480
We still have plenty of money.

4656
03:31:29,480 --> 03:31:31,480
We have lots of money,
and there are still more cards to come.

4657
03:31:31,480 --> 03:31:32,680
Expensive cards could show up,

4658
03:31:32,680 --> 03:31:35,450
like an F-16 fighter jet or something.

4659
03:31:35,650 --> 03:31:36,990
The game isn't over,

4660
03:31:37,250 --> 03:31:38,720
and there is still hope.

4661
03:31:38,750 --> 03:31:42,660
As long as we get special cards
within the next three rounds,

4662
03:31:42,760 --> 03:31:44,690
we'll be fine.

4663
03:31:44,690 --> 03:31:46,260
The worst-case scenario is that...

4664
03:31:46,260 --> 03:31:49,560
another ridiculously expensive item
comes up next round,

4665
03:31:49,560 --> 03:31:52,830
and another team goes all in
with more than what we have.

4666
03:31:52,930 --> 03:31:54,140
What should I do?

4667
03:31:54,140 --> 03:31:56,510
- Should I just go do my own thing too?
- If...

4668
03:31:56,510 --> 03:31:58,010
Just use the hidden item if necessary.

4669
03:31:58,010 --> 03:31:59,510
Use it if you have to. At this point...

4670
03:31:59,510 --> 03:32:01,180
Whether I use it or not,
I'll still catch up to them.

4671
03:32:01,180 --> 03:32:03,480
At this point, what's there to lose?
Just go for it.

4672
03:32:03,480 --> 03:32:05,950
We just need one more item like this.

4673
03:32:06,250 --> 03:32:08,420
Like the Warren Buffett one.

4674
03:32:08,420 --> 03:32:10,020
At this point,
there's nothing left to strategize about.

4675
03:32:10,020 --> 03:32:11,790
We're the chip leader no matter what,
so we'll just take everything we can.

4676
03:32:11,790 --> 03:32:13,120
- We'll use everything we've got.
- Let's use everything we've got.

4677
03:32:13,120 --> 03:32:14,890
Now, Nam Hee, you'll go and...

4678
03:32:15,320 --> 03:32:18,190
say either 15 or 17,

4679
03:32:18,190 --> 03:32:19,390
and win a special card. That's it.

4680
03:32:19,800 --> 03:32:20,830
I'll try to get us a good card.

4681
03:32:20,830 --> 03:32:22,200
I'm usually good at drawing cards.

4682
03:32:22,730 --> 03:32:25,000
The strategy meeting session is over.

4683
03:32:26,000 --> 03:32:29,340
All players participating in the auction,
please gather in the main hall.

4684
03:32:30,210 --> 03:32:33,040
We will begin Round Nine of the auction.

4685
03:32:33,410 --> 03:32:35,740
Team Challenger, select the item.

4686
03:32:38,580 --> 03:32:41,420
(Thinking)

4687
03:32:43,120 --> 03:32:45,520
Gosh, I'm torn between two choices.
Should I do 12...

4688
03:32:47,390 --> 03:32:48,390
or 15...

4689
03:32:49,220 --> 03:32:50,230
or 14?

4690
03:32:57,430 --> 03:32:58,630
I'll go with 18.

4691
03:32:59,000 --> 03:33:01,070
Item number 18 has been selected.

4692
03:33:05,510 --> 03:33:07,710
(Owned item cards are reduced by 50%)

4693
03:33:09,710 --> 03:33:12,280
(The third special card is revealed.)

4694
03:33:12,280 --> 03:33:14,320
The third special card has been revealed.

4695
03:33:14,320 --> 03:33:16,020
- This is insane.
- I think...

4696
03:33:16,120 --> 03:33:17,720
The game is over.

4697
03:33:17,720 --> 03:33:18,720
Good work, everyone.

4698
03:33:18,990 --> 03:33:21,120
I was so, so happy.

4699
03:33:21,120 --> 03:33:22,990
I felt like I was floating.

4700
03:33:23,290 --> 03:33:24,760
Gosh, it's over.

4701
03:33:25,260 --> 03:33:26,660
This is it,

4702
03:33:27,200 --> 03:33:28,200
just as planned.

4703
03:33:28,360 --> 03:33:29,830
It was our worst-case scenario.

4704
03:33:29,830 --> 03:33:32,830
Of all days, today is
the team elimination match,

4705
03:33:32,830 --> 03:33:34,900
and we ended up losing.

4706
03:33:35,200 --> 03:33:38,140
Fate can be so cruel.

4707
03:33:39,540 --> 03:33:42,180
The auction ended just like that.

4708
03:33:42,180 --> 03:33:44,750
Without us buying a single item,

4709
03:33:45,080 --> 03:33:46,850
or even firing our last bullet.

4710
03:33:47,480 --> 03:33:50,120
The third special card has been revealed.

4711
03:33:50,790 --> 03:33:52,650
The game is over.

4712
03:33:53,920 --> 03:33:56,630
Nothing could be more unfair than this.
This is really unfair.

4713
03:33:57,160 --> 03:33:58,960
I literally want to die.

4714
03:34:00,400 --> 03:34:02,530
(Gosh)

4715
03:34:04,330 --> 03:34:06,270
- Goodness.
- Jin Hyeong, I'm sorry.

4716
03:34:06,270 --> 03:34:07,800
No, YunB. It's totally fine.

4717
03:34:08,900 --> 03:34:10,540
It's fine.

4718
03:34:10,740 --> 03:34:12,140
The three special cards
showed up way too early.

4719
03:34:12,140 --> 03:34:14,210
Yes. Seriously, it's fine.

4720
03:34:14,210 --> 03:34:16,310
I'd be lying if I said
I'm not disappointed.

4721
03:34:16,310 --> 03:34:18,150
But there's nothing we can do about it.
What's done is done.

4722
03:34:18,410 --> 03:34:19,920
We just have to do better
from here on out.

4723
03:34:21,020 --> 03:34:22,020
Let's do this.

4724
03:34:22,880 --> 03:34:23,890
Let's do this.

4725
03:34:25,690 --> 03:34:28,120
Because of my mistake,

4726
03:34:28,720 --> 03:34:30,760
we couldn't even take a proper shot...

4727
03:34:31,460 --> 03:34:36,100
at the ray of hope
that appeared at the end...

4728
03:34:36,400 --> 03:34:39,430
before we lost our chance.

4729
03:34:39,840 --> 03:34:42,100
And that weighs heavily on me.

4730
03:34:43,610 --> 03:34:47,810
Even though a massive stroke of luck
came our way when we got that...

4731
03:34:47,810 --> 03:34:49,710
lunch ticket with Warren Buffett
halfway through,

4732
03:34:49,710 --> 03:34:51,150
we still overlooked some things.

4733
03:34:51,450 --> 03:34:53,680
When we saw Team P1 take the card,

4734
03:34:53,680 --> 03:34:56,420
we wondered why they were taking
the special card...

4735
03:34:56,920 --> 03:34:58,520
when they already had two items.

4736
03:34:58,950 --> 03:35:03,260
We should've been more careful
and focused on that.

4737
03:35:03,390 --> 03:35:06,030
Because they have Lee Sang Min,
the human appraiser, on that team.

4738
03:35:06,030 --> 03:35:09,430
Their rush strategy worked.

4739
03:35:09,430 --> 03:35:13,500
More than anything, it really came down to
the fact that they have Sang Min.

4740
03:35:13,500 --> 03:35:16,400
Thank you for your hard work.

4741
03:35:16,840 --> 03:35:20,110
You completely carried us.

4742
03:35:20,110 --> 03:35:22,040
(Sang Min is the key contributor
to the alliance team's victory.)

4743
03:35:22,110 --> 03:35:23,610
Well, I got lucky too.

4744
03:35:23,610 --> 03:35:26,720
I'm grateful that the item exchange coupon
came to me in the first place.

4745
03:35:27,080 --> 03:35:29,380
And it was the best day because...

4746
03:35:29,380 --> 03:35:31,890
I finally earned the kids' recognition.

4747
03:35:32,520 --> 03:35:35,420
The results of the Money Challenge
will be announced.

4748
03:35:35,420 --> 03:35:37,360
Please gather in the main hall.

4749
03:35:39,030 --> 03:35:41,830
The results of the Blind Auction
will be announced.

4750
03:35:42,730 --> 03:35:44,730
The winner of
today's Money Challenge is...

4751
03:35:45,970 --> 03:35:47,240
Team P1.

4752
03:35:51,440 --> 03:35:55,080
A representative of Team P1 should
enter the Voting Room immediately...

4753
03:35:55,080 --> 03:35:57,650
to receive the 50,000 dollars
in team funds.

4754
03:35:58,650 --> 03:36:01,250
Here is the 50,000-dollar prize for
winning the Money Challenge.

4755
03:36:01,250 --> 03:36:04,190
The acquired funds will be stored
in the team safe.

4756
03:36:04,190 --> 03:36:05,320
Thank you.

4757
03:36:07,120 --> 03:36:10,030
To be honest, it wasn't easy
for all of us to win.

4758
03:36:10,030 --> 03:36:12,390
So it felt great that we were able to
earn a true victory.

4759
03:36:12,390 --> 03:36:15,930
Today, we protected our team
together once again.

4760
03:36:16,260 --> 03:36:17,370
It's the best.

4761
03:36:17,370 --> 03:36:21,070
We'd never finished 1st before that.

4762
03:36:21,070 --> 03:36:22,840
Our goal was never just to...

4763
03:36:22,840 --> 03:36:25,870
be exempt from elimination or come in 2nd.

4764
03:36:25,870 --> 03:36:27,480
We were always aiming for 1st place,

4765
03:36:27,480 --> 03:36:29,980
and this time, we finally got it.

4766
03:36:29,980 --> 03:36:32,310
And it was under Team P1's leadership.

4767
03:36:32,450 --> 03:36:37,090
Team R and Team C
basically got a free ride.

4768
03:36:38,120 --> 03:36:39,720
We had the perfect balance of teamwork.

4769
03:36:39,720 --> 03:36:43,220
Sang Min guessed almost all the prices...

4770
03:36:43,220 --> 03:36:45,460
correctly with his incredible intuition,

4771
03:36:45,460 --> 03:36:47,960
while Tae Gyun and Ji Hoo...

4772
03:36:47,960 --> 03:36:50,300
calculated every possible scenario.

4773
03:36:50,300 --> 03:36:52,200
I had the best night's sleep that day.

4774
03:36:52,370 --> 03:36:53,500
Coming in 4th or 5th is basically
the same as finishing last anyway,

4775
03:36:53,500 --> 03:36:54,940
and coming in 1st, 2nd, or 3rd is
basically the same as winning.

4776
03:36:55,700 --> 03:36:56,770
So we won.

4777
03:36:57,870 --> 03:37:01,080
Next, today's Deathmatch players
will be announced.

4778
03:37:01,880 --> 03:37:04,010
The team that will face
the Deathmatch today is...

4779
03:37:04,650 --> 03:37:05,650
the 5th-place team.

4780
03:37:07,450 --> 03:37:08,520
Team P2.

4781
03:37:16,590 --> 03:37:19,630
I started feeling slightly uneasy
halfway through the game,

4782
03:37:19,630 --> 03:37:21,460
and sure enough...

4783
03:37:21,760 --> 03:37:25,470
We thought that for this game at least,

4784
03:37:25,470 --> 03:37:28,640
we could definitely pull it off
even without an alliance.

4785
03:37:29,000 --> 03:37:31,670
But in the end, I realized that...

4786
03:37:31,670 --> 03:37:33,640
no individual is greater than his team.

4787
03:37:33,880 --> 03:37:36,780
Every time we've come across
a good opportunity,

4788
03:37:36,780 --> 03:37:38,710
we've let it all slip away.

4789
03:37:38,710 --> 03:37:40,050
This time was no exception,

4790
03:37:40,480 --> 03:37:41,750
and it was driving me insane.

4791
03:37:42,080 --> 03:37:43,790
I don't want to blame anyone,

4792
03:37:44,390 --> 03:37:46,760
but I can't help myself from doing so.

4793
03:37:47,090 --> 03:37:49,690
It's not like anyone's going to give us
a break because we feel it's unfair.

4794
03:37:49,890 --> 03:37:51,530
So the three of us
just have to work together...

4795
03:37:51,530 --> 03:37:52,760
and somehow pull through.

4796
03:37:52,760 --> 03:37:54,100
We have to make it through this somehow.

4797
03:37:57,070 --> 03:37:58,830
ACRO Forest.

4798
03:37:59,130 --> 03:38:01,500
I can't get it out of my head.

4799
03:38:02,240 --> 03:38:04,410
However, every crisis is an opportunity.

4800
03:38:04,610 --> 03:38:06,510
We've finished in last place
twice in a row,

4801
03:38:06,840 --> 03:38:09,880
and there's nothing scarier than
someone with nothing left to lose.

4802
03:38:11,580 --> 03:38:13,150
- You good?
- Yes, of course.

4803
03:38:14,520 --> 03:38:15,780
And the 4th-place team.

4804
03:38:17,790 --> 03:38:19,290
Team P3.

4805
03:38:27,560 --> 03:38:28,800
I was pretty annoyed.

4806
03:38:28,800 --> 03:38:31,430
Losing a game is one thing.

4807
03:38:31,530 --> 03:38:33,170
If we're able to say, "We did our best."

4808
03:38:33,330 --> 03:38:34,770
"We'll just do a good job
in the Deathmatch,"

4809
03:38:34,970 --> 03:38:36,100
it would be fine.

4810
03:38:36,400 --> 03:38:37,810
But this time,
the loss itself was frustrating,

4811
03:38:37,810 --> 03:38:40,140
and the way we lost the game
was frustrating too.

4812
03:38:40,440 --> 03:38:42,340
Watching our opponent outplay us
and take the win away from us...

4813
03:38:43,980 --> 03:38:45,250
left me feeling empty and bitter.

4814
03:38:45,250 --> 03:38:46,780
I had a lot of mixed feelings.

4815
03:38:46,780 --> 03:38:48,650
Maybe because it was
basically 3 against 1.

4816
03:38:48,650 --> 03:38:51,290
We'd been in 1st place all along,
but on the exact day of...

4817
03:38:51,290 --> 03:38:53,020
the team elimination battle,

4818
03:38:53,390 --> 03:38:55,060
we ended up going to the Deathmatch.

4819
03:38:57,530 --> 03:38:58,760
What I wanted was...

4820
03:38:58,760 --> 03:39:02,530
for 1 of those 3 allied teams
to end up there.

4821
03:39:02,830 --> 03:39:03,830
But that didn't happen,

4822
03:39:03,830 --> 03:39:06,900
so seeing those three teams
acting so triumphant irritated me.

4823
03:39:07,040 --> 03:39:11,170
I kept wondering if, after Round 1,

4824
03:39:11,170 --> 03:39:12,270
I had seen the median value check coupon,

4825
03:39:12,270 --> 03:39:14,140
the game would have
turned out differently.

4826
03:39:14,140 --> 03:39:16,280
I felt even more resentful toward Team P2.

4827
03:39:16,280 --> 03:39:19,780
They made such a huge fuss
to buy that hint.

4828
03:39:19,780 --> 03:39:21,150
The least they could do was to play well.

4829
03:39:21,380 --> 03:39:24,190
I actually started to feel
genuine disgust...

4830
03:39:24,520 --> 03:39:26,520
toward Team P2's style of play.

4831
03:39:27,760 --> 03:39:29,490
They lost too.

4832
03:39:30,190 --> 03:39:31,530
I thought they'd never lose.

4833
03:39:32,490 --> 03:39:33,960
There's no way to beat being outnumbered.

4834
03:39:36,700 --> 03:39:39,400
Gosh, tomorrow's going to be a bloodbath
with team elimination on the line.

4835
03:39:39,400 --> 03:39:42,140
Yes, and whoever makes it back...

4836
03:39:42,140 --> 03:39:43,970
- will hold a massive grudge against us.
- Yes.

4837
03:39:43,970 --> 03:39:45,740
They'll see us as
the core of the alliance,

4838
03:39:45,740 --> 03:39:47,640
so they're going to come for us.

4839
03:39:47,640 --> 03:39:49,880
Everyone thought Team P3...

4840
03:39:49,880 --> 03:39:53,050
was the strongest team,

4841
03:39:53,250 --> 03:39:55,950
so having them go to the Deathmatch...

4842
03:39:56,350 --> 03:39:58,250
and finish in last place...

4843
03:39:58,590 --> 03:40:00,320
would be the ideal outcome.

4844
03:40:00,520 --> 03:40:03,990
I'm still hurt from being betrayed
by Seong Beom on the first day,

4845
03:40:03,990 --> 03:40:06,190
so I really hope Team P3 gets eliminated.

4846
03:40:06,290 --> 03:40:09,060
I heard that Jin Hyeong...

4847
03:40:09,060 --> 03:40:13,170
pushed his way into the Voting Room
during this round.

4848
03:40:13,170 --> 03:40:15,670
So the others would be against them.

4849
03:40:15,670 --> 03:40:17,440
That means, from our perspective,

4850
03:40:18,140 --> 03:40:21,310
it'd be way more advantageous for us
if Jin Hyeong's team came back.

4851
03:40:22,710 --> 03:40:25,680
Deathmatch players,
please gather in the main hall.

4852
03:40:33,420 --> 03:40:34,820
I wanted to fight...

4853
03:40:34,820 --> 03:40:37,690
one of those allied teams that
we'd been at odds with today.

4854
03:40:37,690 --> 03:40:39,030
I didn't want to face Team P2,

4855
03:40:39,030 --> 03:40:41,160
but we didn't have a choice.

4856
03:40:41,160 --> 03:40:44,300
I hated the fact that the two non-allied
teams were going to the Deathmatch.

4857
03:40:44,300 --> 03:40:47,770
But since our opponent was Team P2,
who had kept getting on our nerves...

4858
03:40:48,040 --> 03:40:51,140
We'll just have to
eliminate them ourselves.

4859
03:40:51,140 --> 03:40:53,040
At this point, we just have to win.

4860
03:40:53,040 --> 03:40:56,310
Winning the Deathmatch is a given.

4861
03:40:56,310 --> 03:40:59,210
If it comes down to physical ability,
we'll just have to push through.

4862
03:40:59,210 --> 03:41:01,380
We seriously just have to
give it everything we've got.

4863
03:41:01,380 --> 03:41:03,450
Team P2? We're beating them
no matter what.

4864
03:41:03,450 --> 03:41:05,150
Everyone's underestimating us.

4865
03:41:05,150 --> 03:41:07,390
Especially Team P3.

4866
03:41:07,390 --> 03:41:11,060
They've been enjoying
the high ground in this game,

4867
03:41:11,060 --> 03:41:13,760
so they don't know how dangerous...

4868
03:41:13,760 --> 03:41:15,860
people with nothing left to lose can be.

4869
03:41:15,860 --> 03:41:18,970
They were the one team I absolutely
didn't want to face in the Deathmatch.

4870
03:41:18,970 --> 03:41:21,170
They're scary. They're good. But...

4871
03:41:21,170 --> 03:41:23,170
Whether it's war or sports,

4872
03:41:23,170 --> 03:41:26,110
no one goes in expecting to lose.

4873
03:41:26,340 --> 03:41:27,740
Even if it means going back into the wild,

4874
03:41:27,740 --> 03:41:28,910
even if I have to roll through the mud,

4875
03:41:28,910 --> 03:41:29,940
the wild is still better.

4876
03:41:29,940 --> 03:41:31,580
Of course we have to make it back
from the Deathmatch.

4877
03:41:31,580 --> 03:41:32,810
Going home isn't an option.

4878
03:41:32,810 --> 03:41:35,220
We can't back down like this.

4879
03:41:35,520 --> 03:41:38,820
We're finally going to
bare our teeth and claws...

4880
03:41:38,820 --> 03:41:40,190
and go all out.

4881
03:41:43,890 --> 03:41:45,760
We'll make sure everyone knows...

4882
03:41:46,460 --> 03:41:47,730
not to underestimate Team P2.
